n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n[https://futeboldaselecaobrasileira.blogspot.com/ Brazil National Team All Matches]\n\n[[Category:Kirin Cup]]\n[[Category:2012 in Brazilian women's football|Kirin]]\n[[Category:2012 in Japanese women's football|Kirin]]\n[[Category:2012 United States women's national soccer team|Kirin]]\n[[Category:2012 in women's association football|Kirin]]\n[[Category:International women's association football competitions hosted by Japan|2012]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox International Football Competition\n| tourney_name   = Women's Kirin Challenge Cup\n| year           = 2012\n| other_titles   = \n| image          = \n| size           = \n| caption        = \n| country        = Japan\n| dates          = 1 April \u2013 5 April\n| confederations = 3\n| num_teams      = 3\n| venues         = 3\n| cities         = 3\n| champion_other = {{fbw|Japan}}\n| count          = 1\n| second_other   = {{fbw|United States}}\n| third_other    = {{fbw|Brazil}}\n| matches        = 3\n| goals          = 10\n| attendance     = \n| top_scorer     = \n| player         = \n| prevseason     = \n| nextseason     = [[2020 Women's Kirin Soccer Cup|2020]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2012 Women's Kirin Challenge Cup''' was an [[association football]] tournament organized in [[Japan]].<ref name=\"U.S. Soccer\">[http://www.ussoccer.com/News/Womens-National-Team/2012/02/WNT-Travel-to-Japan.aspx] U.S. Soccer Website</ref> It was held from 1\u20135 April 2012 in [[Japan]] and included 3 teams: [[Brazil women's national football team|Brazil]], [[Japan women's national football team|Japan]] and the [[United States Women's National Soccer Team|United States]]. Japan won the tournament on [[goal difference|goals scored]] after tying with the United States and beating Brazil 4\u20131.<ref>[http://espn.go.com/sports/soccer/story/_/id/7778169/japanese-women-beat-brazil-win-kirin-cup Japanese women beat Brazil to win Kirin Cup]. [[ESPN]]</ref>\n\n==Results==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:cent