uda while they built two new ships to continue the voyage to Jamestown. During the building, ''Sea Venture'''s longboat was fitted with a mast and sent to find Jamestown. Neither it, nor its crew, was ever seen again. When [[Sea Venture|''Deliverance'' and ''Patience'']] set sail for Jamestown, they left several people behind, some to maintain Somers' claim to the islands for [[Kingdom of England|England]], some dead. Those aboard the two ships included [[Sir Thomas Gates]], the military commander and future governor of Jamestown, [[William Strachey]], whose account of the wrecking may later have inspired [[William Shakespeare|Shakespeare's]] ''[[The Tempest (play)|The Tempest]]'', and [[John Rolfe]], who would found Virginia's tobacco industry, and who left a wife and child buried in Bermuda. Rolfe would find a new bride in the [[Powhatan]] princess [[Pocahontas]].\n\nJamestown, and the sixty survivors of its original five hundred settlers, were found in such a poor state that it was decided to abandon the Jamestown settlement and return everyone to England. The timely [[Jamestown supply missions|arrival of another relief fleet]] under Thomas West from England granted the colony a reprieve. However, the food shortage was made more critical by the new arrivals. Somers returned to Bermuda on ''Patience'', captained by his nephew, Matthew, to gather provisions for the Jamestown colony, but died on Bermuda in 1610. Matthew Somers was keen to receive his inheritance (Sir George and his wife were childless, but had raised his two nephews), and took ''Patience'' to Somers' hometown, [[Lyme Regis]], and not to Virginia.\n\nWhen news reached England of the adventures of ''Sea Venture'''s survivors, the royal charter of the Virginia Company was extended to include Bermuda on the 12th of March, 1612, at Westminster, with the archipelago granted by the Crown unto the ''Treasurer and Company of Aduenturers and Planters of the Cittie of London for the first colony in Virginia''. The new colony was officially named ''Virgineola'', although this was soon changed to ''The Somers Isles'' or ''The Somers Islands'' in honour of Sir George Somers.\n\nA [[Governor of Bermuda|Governor]], Richard Moore, arrived in 1612 with settlers, aboard ''Plough'', to join those left behind by ''Sea Venture'' and ''Patience''. The new settlers were primarily tenant farmers, who gave seven years of indentured servitude to the Company in exchange for the cost of transport. Although the primary industry was envisioned to be agriculture, the early Governors enthusiastically, if mostly unsuccessfully, attempted to develop other industries also. These included pearl diving (there are no pearls in Bermuda) and [[ambergris]]. The first two slaves to arrive in Bermuda, one black, one Native American, were brought in for their skills as pearl divers.\n\nFree of the endemic warfare and other hardships which plagued the continental settlement, Bermuda thrived from the beginning, though it was never to be particularly profitable for its investors. Its population quickly surpassed that of Jamestown, and consideration was given to abandoning the North American continent and evacuating its settlers to Bermuda.\n\n==Formation of the Somers Isles Company==\nThe Virginia Company ran Bermuda until 1613, when the colony was transferred to Sir [[William Wade (English politician)|William Wade]] et cetera in exchange for \u00a32,000, who then resigned to the Crown in 1614. The Crown briefly adminstered the Colony directly before the adventurers (shareholders) of the Virginia Company formed a second company, the Somers Isles Company, to which Bermuda was transferred in 1615. The Virginia Company was dissolved in 1622, with the administration of its continental colony passing to [[the Crown]]. The Somers Isles Company, with its separate charter, continued to administer Bermuda for another six decades.\n\nThe original Adventurers of the Somers Isles Company listed in the letters patent were essentially the same as those of the Virginia Company. Major-General Sir [[John Henry Lefroy]], Governor of Bermuda from 1871 to 1877, transcribed the list which was ordered by social rank, but commented that the original list began with Henry, Earl of Southampton:<ref>J. H. Lefroy, [https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=wu.89080098932&view=1up&seq=145 ''Memorials of the Discovery and Early Settlement of The Bermudas or Somers Islands'', vol. 1 (London, 1877), p. 99].</ref>\n\n*[[Lucy Russell, Countess of Bedford|Bedford, Lucie, Countess of]]\n*[[William Cavendish, 2nd Earl of Devonshire|Cavendish, William, Lord]]\n*[[William Paget, 4th Baron Paget|William, Lord Paget]]\n*[[William Herbert, 3rd Earl of Pembroke|Pembroke, William, Earl of]]\n*Southampton, Henrie, Earl of\n*[[Anthony Aucher (the elder)|Auger (Aucher) Sir Anthoine]]\n*[[Lionel Cranfield, 1st Earl of Middlesex|Cranfield, Sir Lionard]]\n*[[Dudley Digges|Diggs, Sir Dudlie]]\n*Grobham, Sir Richard\n*Hide, Sir Lawrence\n*Hogan, Sir Thomas\n*Howard, Sir John\n*[[Robert Mansell|Mansell, Sir Richard (Robert)]]\n*Mericke, Sir John\n*Rich, Sir Robert\n*[[Edwin Sandys (died 1629)|Sandys, Sir Edwin]]\n*Sandys, Sir Samuel\n*Smith, Sir Richard\n*Smith, Sir Thomas\n*Watts, Sir John\n*[[Ralph Winwood|Winwood, Sir Ralphe]]\n*Caraway, William Esq.\n*Chamberlaine, Richard Esq.\n*Heydon, Jeremie Esq.\n*Hide, Nicholas Esq.\n*Martin, Richard Esq.\n*Thorpe, George Esq.\n*Walter, John Esq.\n*Westenholm, John Esq.\n*Wrath, John Esq.\n*Abbott, Maurice, merchant\n*Abby, Anthony\n*Adderlie, William\n*Anthonie, Charles, goldsmith\n*Banks, John, mercer\n*Barnard, John\n*Barkeley, George, merchant\n*Baron, Christopher\n*Benson, Nicholas\n*Bretton, John\n*Bishop, Edward\n*Brainfield, Arthur\n*Campage, William, merchant\n*Cartwright, Abraham\n*Casewell, Richard\n*Chamberlaine, Abraham\n*Chamberlaine, George, merchant\n*Church, Thomas\n*Clitherow, Christopher\n*Cotton, Allen\n*Conell, Thomas\n*Dawes, Abraham\n*De Laurie, Gideon\n*Delbridge, John\n*Dike, John\n*Ditchfield, Edward, salter\n*Edwards, Richard\n*Etheridge, George\n*Exton, Nicholas\n*Farrer, Nicholas, merchant\n*Ffellgate, William\n*Fletcher, John\n*Fletcher, Edward\n*Gearing, John\n*Giles, Ffrancis\n*Gore, Robert, merchant tailor\n*Greenwell, William, merchant tailor\n*Haleman, George\n*Hamer, Ralphe, merchant taylor\n*Harwood, Leonard\n*Herne, John\n*Heyward, John, clarke (clerk? Cleric?)\n*Hinton, Anthonie, doctor of physicke\n*Hodges, John\n*Jacobson, Philip\n*Jadwin, Thomas\n*John, Thomas\n*Johnson, Robert, grocer\n*Kerell, John\n*Kinge, Ralphe\n*Leuis, Thomas\n*Lukin, Edward\n*Maplesdon, Richard\n*Martin, Edward\n*Mercer, Richard\n*Nicholls, William\n*Norcott, Thomas\n*Offley, Robert, merchant\n*Osborn, John\n*Palmer, William\n*Payne, William Esquire\n*Phipps, Robert\n*Poulson, Richard\n*Prason, Hildebrand\n*Quick, William\n*Rich, George\n*Roberts, Elias, merchant tailor\n*Rogers, Richard\n*Scott, Edmon\n*Scott, George\n*Shepheard, Matthew\n*Smith, Cleophas\n*Smith, George, grocer\n*Smith, Robert\n*Smith, Waren\n*[[Dorothy Speckard|Speckhardie, Abraham]]\n*Swinow, George\n*Tomlins, Richard\n*Tymberdale, Henry\n*Wale, Thomas\n*Webb, Rice, haberdasher\n*Webb, Thomas\n*Webster, William\n*Weld, John\n*Welby, William, stationer\n*West, John, grocer\n*Wheatley, Thomas\n*Woddall, John\n\n==Bermuda as a company colony==\n[[Image:Somers Isles Map - John Speed 1676.jpg|right|200px|Map by John Speed, 1676.]]\nMost of Bermuda was subdivided into eight equally sized ''tribes'', later called ''parishes''. These were named for shareholders in the Company, and were further divided (by ''tribe roads'') into lots which equated to shares in the Company. The Company's return on investment came specifically from cash crops raised on that land. A ninth subdivision, now the eastern-most parish, was [[St. George's Parish, Bermuda|Saint George's]], comprising [[St. George's Island, Bermuda|Saint George's Island]], [[St. David's Island, Bermuda|Saint David's Island]], part of the Main Island, and various smaller islands and islets around [[Castle Harbour, Bermuda|Castle Harbour]] (then known as Southampton Harbour) and [[St. George's Harbour, Bermuda|Saint George's Harbour]]. This area was held as ''common'', or ''King's'' land, and was not subdivided for exploitation by the Company. This was where the capital, [[St. George's, Bermuda|Saint George's Town]] was located. The choice of this location followed the original settlement created by ''Sea Venture'' survivors, and was also determined by the two eastern harbours being the only ones then readily accessible to shipping.\n\nA surveyor, [[Richard Norwood]], was hired to produce a survey of the colony, which also served as a census. This was completed in 1616, although he made later updates. In the process, he discovered that the total landmass of the eight commercial parishes was greater than originally estimated. His superior, [[Daniel Tucker (Governor)|Daniel Tucker]], the [[Governor of Bermuda]], appropriated a choice piece of land, equivalent to the excess, for himself.\n\n==Local government==\nThe Company continued to appoint governors until its dissolution in 1684. In 1620, however, a colonial parliament was created, the [[House of Assembly of Bermuda|House of Assembly]]. Suffrage was restricted to male land owners, and there was no upper house. An appointed council, composed primarily from the leading merchant families of the Colony, came to fill a role similar to both an upper house, and a cabinet, and often proved the true repository of power in Bermuda.\n\nThe immediate concern of the first governors was for the colony's protection from a feared Spanish or Dutch attack, and the building of fortifications, and the raising of [[Bermuda Militias 1612-1815|militias]], was sustained throughout the company's administration, and beyond. A review of the colony's defences was carried out by [[John Smith of Jamestown|Captain John Smith]].\n\n==Immigration, slavery, and demographics==\nImmigration of indentured servants continued throughout the Company's administration, and this pool of cheap labour meant that Bermuda never developed the slavery-based economy that came to characterise other English agricultural colonies. Although the bulk of the population remained [[Anglo-Saxons|Anglo-Saxon]] at the end of the 17th century, a number of minority groups were established under the Company's management. As England began to challenge Spain's supremacy in [[Florida]] and the [[West Indies]], Spanish-speaking Blacks began to emigrate from territories taken from [[Spain]]. These immigrants arrived under the same conditions of indenture as most English immigrants, but the white majority soon became uneasy with the increasing numbers of blacks. The terms of indenture for black West Indian immigrants were consequently raised successively from seven years to ninety-nine. An attempt was also made to encourage Blacks to emigrate under threat of being enslaved. Numbers of Black slaves were also being imported to Bermuda, primarily as the result of shipwrecks, or as part of the prizes taken by [[privateers]], although Bermudian vessels went as far as Africa specifically to acquire slaves. As England's settlements in [[New England]] expanded, large areas were ethnically cleansed to make way for European expansion. This resulted in various [[Algonquian peoples|Algonquian]] peoples being shipped to Bermuda and sold into slavery, notably after the [[Pequot War]] and [[King Philip's War|Metacomet's War]]. A great many [[Indigenous peoples of the Americas|Native American]] slaves were being brought to Bermuda by other means, also, possibly from as far as [[Mexico]]. The third main minority group was composed of Irish [[Prisoner of war|prisoners-of-war]] (POW), and ethnically cleansed civilians, shipped to the Colony and sold into slavery following [[Oliver Cromwell|Cromwell's]] bloody adventure in [[Ireland]] in the 1650s (see [[Cromwellian conquest of Ireland]]). Smaller numbers of Scottish POWs were also sent as a result of Cromwell's forcing his 'protectorship' on [[Scotland]].\n\nBermuda had tended towards the [[Cavalier|Royalist]] side in the [[English Civil War]], perhaps because the shareholders of the Somers Isles Company were primarily [[Nobility|nobles]], but was largely spared the effects and the aftermath of that conflict. Bermuda's [[republic]]an element, which (as in England) was largely identical to the [[Puritan]], anti-[[Episcopal polity|episcopalian]] demographic, was forced into exile, becoming the [[Eleutheran Adventurers]] who began England's settlement of the [[Bahamas]] in the 1640s.\n\n==Economy and industry==\n[[File:Historic Bermuda Hog Money.png|thumb|right|Coins minted by the Sommer Isles Company]]\n[[Agriculture]] remained the mainstay of the [[Economic system|economy]] under the Somers Isles Company. The primary cash crop was [[tobacco]], but the quantity and quality produced were very poor. The [[Bermuda cedar]] boxes in which the tobacco was shipped to England were said to be worth more than their contents, and much of the tobacco was destroyed on arrival. The Colony also had little success with other export crops. Additionally, the several acres of arable land that had been cut from the forest meant that each farmer had only a very small area under cultivation, by comparison to the {{convert|50|acre|m2}} granted to each settler in Virginia. Bermudian farmers had to raise as many as three crops a year in order to be economically viable. This meant that they could not allow fields to lie fallow, and the soil, already high in [[Alkali#Alkaline soil|alkaline]] and low in [[magnesium]] (used by plants to form [[chlorophyll]]), became depleted. By the 1620s, Virginia's tobacco exports were increasing, and newer English colonies in the West Indies were also emulating Bermuda by focusing on growing tobacco for export, with the result of drastically reducing the profitability of growing tobacco for Bermudian farmers. Bermudian farmers increasingly turned to growing food crops and rearing livestock, both to reduce their dependence on overpriced imports, and to sell to other colonies. This growing trade created a need for Bermudian-owned ships to deliver their exports.\n\nBermudians began to turn away from agriculture quite early, building boats and developing the [[Bermuda sloop]] to pursue maritime trades. As the Company derived no income, except from tobacco sent to England aboard the company's magazine ships, it acted to stymie these activities. The building of vessels was banned without its license, and the first laws to protect the [[Bermuda cedar]], which were passed early in the seventeenth century, may have been intended more to restrict shipbuilding than to conserve the resource.\n\n==Civil War==\nBy the 1630s, the company had ceased sending Governors to Bermuda and began appointing a string of prominent Bermudians, such as [[William Sayle]], to the role. As few Adventurers actually settled in Bermuda, with their properties instead managed by poorer relatives or tenants, the local House of Assembly was necessarily elected without a property qualification, unlike the [[House of Commons of England]]. This meant it was far more concerned with the interests of the islanders, rather than the Adventurers in England. By the mid-17th century, with tobacco exports failing, many Adventurers in England eagerly cut their losses by selling their shares to the tenants who occupied. Bermudians quickly became the majority of landowners, but the Adventurers who remained in England maintained control of the Company by barring any shareholder who did not personally attend meetings in England from the decision-making process. Many of those English shareholders belonged to the [[gentry]] and anti-[[Episcopal polity|Episcopalian]] sects within the [[Church of England]], and sided with the [[Parliament of England|Parliamentarians]] during the 1642-1651 [[English Civil War|Civil War]]. Given the increasingly hostile relationship between Bermudians and the Company, the majority of Bermudians sided with the Crown. With control of the military forces in Bermuda as well as the Assembly, the Royalists deposed the Company appointed Governor, Captain Thomas Turner, and elected John Trimigham in his stead. The colony's Independents, who sided with Parliament, were forced into exile, settling the [[Bahamas]] under the Cromwell-loyalist [[William Sayle]] as the [[Eleutheran Adventurers]].\n\nThe response of Parliament to what was characterised as the rebellion of Bermuda (and of other colonies, particularly Virginia, [[Barbados]], and [[Antigua]]) was the passage of [[An Act for prohibiting Trade with the Barbadoes, Virginia, Bermuda and Antego]] in October, 1650. This called for ''due punishment [to be] inflicted upon the said Delinquents, do Declare all and every the said persons in Barbada's, Antego, Bermuda's and Virginia, that have contrived, abetted, aided or assisted those horrid Rebellions, or have since willingly joyned with them, to be notorious Robbers and Traitors, and such as by the Law of Nations are not to be permitted any maner of Commerce or Traffique with any people whatsoever; and do forbid to all maner of persons, Foreiners, and others, all maner of Commerce, Traffique and Correspondency whatsoever, to be used or held with the said Rebels in the Barbada's, Bermuda's, Virginia and Antego, or either of them.''{{cn|date=September 2018}}\n\nParliamentary privateers were authorised to act against English vessels trading with these colonies: {{lang|enm|All Ships that Trade with the Rebels may be surprized. Goods and tackle of such ships not to be embezeled, till judgement in the Admiralty.; Two or three of the Officers of every ship to be examined upon oath.}}{{cn|date=September 2018}} Parliament made preparations to invade the Royalist colonies, but the outbreak of the [[Second Anglo-Dutch War]] in 1651 was to engulf the British West Indies in war with France and Holland. A thousand miles distant, Bermuda was untouched by that war and reached a compromise with Parliament.\n\nWith the [[Restoration (England)|Restoration]], Bermudians found they had a powerful ally in the Crown, which had its own interest in wresting control of the English Empire from corporations like the Somers Isles Company.\n\n==Revocation of charter and dissolution==\nIt was worsening interference by the Company into the livelihoods of the islanders which led to its dissolution. A protest to the Crown resulting initially from the treatment of [[Perient Trott]] and his heirs, but expanding to include the Company's wider mismanagement of the colony, was directed to the Crown. This led to a lengthy court case in which the Crown championed Bermudians against the Company. This resulted in the Company's Royal Charter being revoked in 1684, and from then on the Crown assumed responsibility for appointing the Colony's governors (it first re-appointed the last company governor). Freed of the Company's restraints, the local merchant class came to dominate and shape Bermuda's progress, as Bermudians abandoned agriculture en masse and turned to the sea.\n\n==See also==\n{{portal|Companies}}\n* [[History of Bermuda]]\n* [[History of Virginia]]\n* [[Jamestown, Virginia]]\n* [[List of trading companies]]\n* [[London Company|Virginia Company of London]]\n* [[Sea Venture]]\n* [[Virginia Company]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* Roots Web [http://www.rootsweb.com/~bmuwgw/norwoodsurvey.html Richard Norwood\u2019s Survey of the Land and Landholder\u2019s of Bermuda].\n* Bermuda Yellow Pages [http://www.bermudayp.com/history.html History of Bermuda]{{dead link|date=May 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}.\n* Dan Byrnes. Com [http://www.danbyrnes.com.au/business/business9.html The Business of Slavery - Chapter 9].\n\n{{Chartered companies|state=collapsed}}\n\n[[Category:History of Bermuda]]\n[[Category:Colonial Virginia]]\n[[Category:English colonization of the Americas]]\n[[Category:Chartered companies]]\n[[Category:Trading companies]]\n[[Category:Companies established in 1615]]\n[[Category:1615 establishments in the British Empire]]\n[[Category:1615 establishments in North America]]\n[[Category:1610s establishments in Virginia]]\n[[Category:Companies disestablished in the 1680s]]\n[[Category:1684 disestablishments in the British Empire]]\n[[Category:1684 disestablishments in North America]]\n[[Category:British North America]]\n[[Category:Economy of Stuart England]]\n", "name_user": "Aodhdubh", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eFormation of the Somers Isles Company", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Somers_Isles_Company"}
{"title_page": "One Direction", "text_new": "{{distinguish|One-way (disambiguation){{!}}One-way}}\n{{pp-semi-indef|small=yes}}\n{{short description|English-Irish boy band}}\n{{Use British English|date=February 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = One Direction\n| background       = group_or_band\n| image            = One Direction 2015.jpg\n| landscape        = yes\n| caption          = One Direction performing in [[Glasgow]] on their [[On the Road Again Tour]], October 2015. From left to right: [[Louis Tomlinson]], [[Niall Horan]], [[Liam Payne]] and [[Harry Styles]]\n| alias            = <!--1D-->\n| origin           = [[London]], England\n| genre            = {{flatlist|\n* [[Pop music|Pop]]\n* [[teen pop]]\n* [[pop rock]]\n}}\n| years_active     = 2010\u20132016 (on indefinite hiatus)\n| label            = {{flatlist|\n* [[Syco Music|Syco]]\n* [[Columbia Records|Columbia]]\n}}<!-- Do not add Sony Music as a label, as Columbia and Syco are divisions of it -->\n| associated_acts  = [[List of The X Factor finalists (British series 7)|''The X Factor'' finalists 2010]]\n| current_members  = * [[Harry Styles]]\n* [[Niall Horan]] \n* [[Liam Payne]]\n* [[Louis Tomlinson]]\n| website          = {{URL|onedirectionmusic.com}}\n| past_members     =  * [[Zayn Malik]]\n}}\n\n'''One Direction''', often shortened to '''1D''', are<!-- are is plural for a group, do not change --> an English-Irish<!-- This is based on discussion in the talk page --> [[Pop music|pop]] [[boy band]] formed in London, England in 2010. The group is composed of [[Niall Horan]], [[Liam Payne]], [[Harry Styles]] and [[Louis Tomlinson]]; former member [[Zayn Malik]] departed from the group in 2015. The group signed with [[Simon Cowell]]'s record label [[Syco Music|Syco Records]] after forming and finishing third in the [[The X Factor (British series 7)|seventh series]] of the British televised singing competition ''[[The X Factor (British TV series)|The X Factor]]'' in 2010. Propelled to global success by [[social media]],<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/music/2012/mar/15/one-direction-fab-five-america \u201cOne Direction: the fab five take America\u201d]. ''The Guardian''. Retrieved 27 July 2019</ref><ref>[https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/music/music-news/9157558/One-Direction-make-American-pop-history.html \u201cOne Direction make American pop history\u201d]. ''The Telegraph''. Retrieved 27 July 2019</ref><ref>[https://www.theverge.com/2016/12/13/13937688/one-direction-one-year-hiatus-anniversary-social-media-blogging \u201cHow One Direction stayed the world\u2019s biggest band even after it stopped existing\u201d]. ''The Verge''. Retrieved 27 July 2019</ref> One Direction's five albums, ''[[Up All Night (One Direction album)|Up All Night]]'' (2011), ''[[Take Me Home (One Direction album)|Take Me Home]]'' (2012), ''[[Midnight Memories]]'' (2013), ''[[Four (One Direction album)|Four]]'' (2014), and ''[[Made in the A.M.]]'' (2015), topped charts in most major markets, and generated hit singles including \"[[What Makes You Beautiful]]\", \"[[Live While We're Young]]\", \"[[Best Song Ever (song)|Best Song Ever]]\", \"[[Story of My Life (One Direction song)|Story of My Life]]\" and \"[[Drag Me Down]]\".\n\nThe group have won nearly 200 [[List of awards and nominations received by One Direction|awards]] including seven [[Brit Awards]], four [[MTV Video Music Award]]s, six [[Billboard Music Award|''Billboard'' Music Award]]s, seven [[American Music Awards]] (including [[American Music Award for Artist of the Year|Artist of the Year]] in 2014 and 2015), and 28 [[Teen Choice Awards]]. They have embarked on four world tours, two of which were all-stadium. In 2013, they earned an estimated $75 million, becoming the second highest earning celebrity under 30 according to ''[[Forbes]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/one-direction/|title=One Direction|website=Forbes}}</ref> The world\u2019s best-selling artist of 2013, the [[International Federation of the Phonographic Industry]] (IFPI) named them the [[Global Recording Artist of the Year]].<ref name=\"IFPI\"/> ''Forbes'' ranked them as the fourth [[Forbes Celebrity 100|highest-earning celebrities]] in the world in 2015,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/zackomalleygreenburg/2015/06/29/celebrity-100-the-worlds-highest-paid-superstars-of-2015/|title=Celebrity 100: The World's Highest-Paid Superstars Of 2015|author=Greenburg, Zack O'Malley|date=29 June 2015|work=Forbes|accessdate=1 September 2016}}</ref> and second in 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/zackomalleygreenburg/2016/07/11/celeb-100-the-worlds-highest-paid-celebrities-of-2016/#72cbabf81fb3/|title=Celebrity 100: The World's Highest-Paid Superstars of 2016|author=Zack O'Malley Greenburg|work=Forbes|accessdate = 6 April 2017}}</ref>\n\nAfter the release of ''Four'', One Direction became the first band in the U.S. [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] history to have their first four albums debut at number one.<ref>{{cite news|first=Keith|last=Caulfield|title=One Direction's 'Four' Makes Historic No. 1 Debut on Billboard 200 Chart|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6327789/one-direction-four-no-1-debut-billboard-200|date=26 November 2014 |accessdate=26 November 2014}}</ref> Their third album, ''Midnight Memories'', was the best-selling album worldwide in 2013 with 4 million copies sold globally.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-28599903 |title= One Direction top 2013 global album chart|publisher=BBC News  |date= 1 August 2014|accessdate=2 August 2014}}</ref> The band's [[Where We Are Tour (One Direction)|Where We Are Tour]], in support of ''Midnight Memories'', was the [[List of highest-grossing concert tours|highest-grossing concert tour]] in 2014, the highest-grossing tour by a vocal group in history, and the 15th [[List of highest-grossing concert tours|highest-grossing concert tour]] of all time, grossing $290.2 million (unadjusted for inflation).<ref name=\"billboard1D\">{{cite news|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6281518/one-direction-where-we-are-tour-three-million|title=One Direction's Where We Are Tour Attended by 3.4 Million Fans|last=Allen|first=Bob|date=10 October 2014|work=Billboard|accessdate=11 October 2014}}</ref> In 2014, ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' named One Direction Artist of the Year.<ref>{{cite news|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|title=Billboard's Artists of the Year: 1981\u20132014|url=http://www.billboard.com/photos/6415105/billboard-artist-of-the-year-gallery-1981-to-2014?i=540767|agency=Billboard|issue=23 June 2015|date=13 January 2015}}</ref><ref>[http://www.billboard.com/articles/events/year-in-music-2014/6386043/the-year-in-pop-2014-one-direction-frozen-pharrell \"The Year in Pop 2014: One Direction, 'Frozen,' & Pharrell Dominate\"]. ''Billboard''. Retrieved 8 January 2015</ref> The band went on hiatus in January 2016, allowing all members to pursue other projects.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.express.co.uk/entertainment/music/800249/One-Direction-reunion-timing-Niall-Horan-solo-Harry-Styles|title=One Direction REUNION: Niall Horan opens up on WHEN iconic boyband will get back together|first=George|last=Simpson|date=4 May 2017|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2017/02/15/celebrities/one-direction-reunion-niall-horan-interview/|title=Niall Horan: One Direction reunion is 'definitely' happening|first=Chloe |last=Melas|publisher=}}</ref> As of 2020, the band has sold a total of 50 million records worldwide.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/one-direction-bands-louis-tomlinson-arrested-in-airport-tussle-1666249 |title=One Direction Band's Louis Tomlinson Arrested In Airport Tussle |date=9 March 2018 |work=[[Agence France-Presse]] |accessdate=5 March 2017}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n\n===2010\u20132011: ''The X Factor''===\n[[File:One Direction X Factor Live Glasgow.jpg|thumb|left|One Direction on ''The X Factor'' Live tour in 2011]]\nIn 2010, [[Niall Horan]], [[Zayn Malik]], [[Liam Payne]], [[Harry Styles]], and [[Louis Tomlinson]] auditioned as solo candidates for the [[The X Factor (British series 7)|seventh series]] of the British televised singing competition ''[[The X Factor (British TV series)|The X Factor]]''.<ref name=Kelly>{{cite news| first =Kristy | last = Kelly | url = http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/tv/s103/the-x-factor/news/a331792/nicole-scherzinger-i-did-simon-cowell-a-favour-with-one-direction.html | title= Nicole Scherzinger: 'I did Simon Cowell a favour with One Direction' |work= [[Digital Spy]]| publisher= Hearst | place = UK|date= 26 July 2011 | accessdate =26 July 2011}}</ref> They all failed to progress in the \"Boys\" category at the bootcamp stage of the competition, but were instead put together to form a five-piece boy band,<ref>{{cite news| first = Kate | last = McMahon| url = https://www.mirror.co.uk/celebs/news/2010/07/12/cheryl-tweedy-cancels-x-factor-boot-camp-and-v-festival-appearances-115875-22406276/ | title= Cheryl Tweedy cancels X Factor Boot Camp and V Festival appearances |work=Daily Mirror |date= 12 July 2010|accessdate= 12 July 2010}}</ref> thus qualifying for the \"Groups\" category. [[Nicole Scherzinger]], a guest judge,<ref name=Kelly /><ref>{{cite news|title=One Direction film claims she founded band, not Simon Cowell|url=http://blogs.independent.co.uk/2013/07/19/more-woe-for-nicole-scherzinger-one-direction-film-claims-she-founded-band-not-simon-cowell/|newspaper=[[The Independent]]|location=London|first=Daisy|last=Wyatt|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131122053550/http://blogs.independent.co.uk/2013/07/19/more-woe-for-nicole-scherzinger-one-direction-film-claims-she-founded-band-not-simon-cowell/|archivedate=22 November 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Without Nicole Scherzinger there would be no One Direction |url=http://www.novafm.com.au/audio/without-nicole-scherzinger-there-would-be-no-one-direction |newspaper=NOVA Fm (Australian radio) |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120401001002/http://www.novafm.com.au/audio/without-nicole-scherzinger-there-would-be-no-one-direction |archivedate=1 April 2012 }}</ref> and [[Simon Cowell]] have both claimed to have come up with the idea of forming the band. In 2013, Cowell said that it \"took him 10 minutes to put them together as a group\".<ref name=\"1D Day\">{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a533467/simon-cowell-talks-one-direction-formation-it-was-my-idea.html|title=Simon Cowell talks One Direction formation: 'It was my idea'|last=Harp|first=Justin|date=24 November 2013|work=[[Digital Spy]]|accessdate=24 November 2013}}</ref> Subsequently, the group got together for two weeks to get to know each other and to practice.<ref name=\"thehothits1\">{{cite news|first1=Stan |last1=Walker |first2=Short |last2=Stack |first3=Michael |last3=Paynter |first4=Amy |last4=Meredith |url=http://www.thehothits.com/artists/6069/one-direction/bio |title=One Direction Biography |work=[[The Hot Hits Live from LA]]  |accessdate=27 April 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120327221234/http://www.thehothits.com/artists/6069/one-direction/bio |archivedate=27 March 2012 }}</ref><ref name=autogenerated10>{{cite web|newspaper=South Wales Echo |url=http://www.walesonline.co.uk/showbiz-and-lifestyle/showbiz/2012/01/13/one-direction-prepare-for-cardiff-sell-out-shows-91466-30112196/ |title=One Direction prepare for Cardiff sell-out shows |publisher=[[Media Wales]] |date=13 January 2012 |accessdate=6 June 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120126001640/http://www.walesonline.co.uk/showbiz-and-lifestyle/showbiz/2012/01/13/one-direction-prepare-for-cardiff-sell-out-shows-91466-30112196/ |archivedate=26 January 2012 }}</ref> Styles came up with the name One Direction.<ref name=\"thehothits1\" /> For their qualifying song at \"judges' houses\", and their first song as a group, One Direction sang an acoustic version of \"[[Torn (Ednaswap song)|Torn]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertainment.stv.tv/tv/200816-the-x-factor-2010-the-acts-who-made-it-to-the-live-shows/ |publisher=[[STV (TV network)|STV]] |place=[[Scotland|SCO]], UK |title=The X Factor 2010: the 12 acts who made it to the Live Shows |date=3 October 2010 |accessdate=4 November 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101124111354/http://entertainment.stv.tv/tv/200816-the-x-factor-2010-the-acts-who-made-it-to-the-live-shows/ |archivedate=24 November 2010 }}</ref> Cowell later commented that their performance convinced him that they \"were confident, fun, like a gang of friends, and kind of fearless as well.\"<ref name = \"simoncowellQ&A\">{{cite news| first = Andy | last = Greene |url = https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/exclusive-q-a-simon-cowell-on-one-directions-rise-to-stardom-20120409 |title=Exclusive Q&A: Simon Cowell on One Direction's Rise to Stardom |work=Rolling Stone  |date= 9 April 2012 |accessdate= 11 May 2012}}</ref> Within the first four weeks of the [[The X Factor (British series 7)#Live show details|live shows]], they were his final act in the competition. The group quickly gained popularity in the UK.<ref name=\"simoncowellQ&A\" />\n\nOne Direction achieved third place in the competition and immediately after the final, their song \"[[Forever Young (Alphaville song)|Forever Young]]\", which would have been released if they had won ''The X Factor'', was leaked onto the internet.<ref name = thirdplace>{{cite news|url= https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/tvandradioblog/2010/dec/10/xfactor-final-results-liveblog |title=The X Factor 2010 final results show|work=The Guardian|date= 12 December 2012 |accessdate=15 March 2012 | location = London | first = Stuart | last = Heritage}}</ref> Shortly afterwards it was confirmed that One Direction had been signed by Cowell to a reported [[Pound sterling|\u00a3]]2&nbsp;million [[Syco Music|Syco Records]] record contract.<ref>{{cite news | first = Mayer | last = Nissim |url= http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/s103/the-x-factor/news/a300729/one-direction-get-gbp2m-syco-investment.html | title= One Direction 'get \u00a32m Syco investment' | work= [[Digital Spy]] | publisher = Hearst | place = UK | date=28 January 2011|accessdate=23 October 2011}}</ref> Recording for their debut album began in January 2011, as they flew to Los Angeles to work with [[RedOne]], a record producer.<ref name = Miller>{{cite news | first = Ed | last = Miller |url = http://www.musicweek.com/news/read/sony-excited-about-one-direction-potential/046464 | title = Sony excited about One Direction potential |work= [[Music Week]]  |date = 16 August 2011 | accessdate = 27 July 2012}}</ref> A book licensed by One Direction, ''One Direction: Forever Young (Our Official X Factor Story)'', was published by [[HarperCollins]] in February 2011,<ref>{{cite web| first =Alex | last = Fletcher | url = http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/showbiz/s103/the-x-factor/news/a304324/one-direction-release-autobiography.html | title= One Direction release autobiography |work= [[Digital Spy]]|publisher= Hearst | place = UK | date = 17 February 2011 | accessdate=14 January 2012}}</ref> subsequently topping [[The Sunday Times|''The Sunday Times'' Best Seller list]].<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.sugarscape.com/tags/band/621789/one-direction-number-one-sunday-times-bestseller-list?page=0%2C0 |title=One Direction book number one on Sunday Times bestsetller list |work= [[Sugar (magazine)|Sugarscape]] |date= 5 April 2011|accessdate= 27 July 2012}}</ref> The same month, the boy band and other contestants from the series participated in the ''X Factor'' Live Tour. During the tour, the group performed for 500,000 people throughout the UK.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hmvtickets.com/events/1622?REFID=hmv_tickets_system_body |title=Tickets for One Direction at HMV Apollo Hammersmith, London, now available from hmvtickets.com |publisher=[[HMV]] |accessdate=11 May 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120121204017/http://www.hmvtickets.com/events/1622?REFID=hmv_tickets_system_body |archivedate=21 January 2012 }}</ref> After the tour concluded in April 2011, the group continued working on their debut album.<ref name = Miller /> Recording took place in Stockholm, London and Los Angeles, as One Direction worked with producers [[Carl Falk]], [[Savan Kotecha]], [[Steve Mac]], and [[Rami (producer)|Rami Yacoub]], among others.<ref name=\"allmusic1\">{{cite web | url = http://www.allmusic.com/album/up-all-night-r2324993/credits |title= Up All Night \u2013 One Direction |publisher = AllMusic |date=21 November 2011 |accessdate=21 March 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite AV media notes | title =Up All Night |others=One Direction |year=2011 |type=liner notes |publisher= [[Syco Music]], [[Sony Music Entertainment]]}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable collapsible collapsed\" style=\"width:100%; margin:1em auto 1em auto; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#BFBFBF;\"| ''The X Factor'' performances and results\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:centre\"|Episode\n! style=\"text-align:centre\"|Song choice\n! style=\"text-align:centre\"|Theme\n! style=\"text-align:centre\"|Result\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"| Auditions\n|[[Harry Styles]]: \"[[Isn't She Lovely]]\"\n|rowspan=\"5\"| Free choice (caught singing while driving)\n|rowspan=\"5\"| Through to bootcamp\n|-\n| [[Zayn Malik]]: \"[[Let Me Love You (Mario song)|Let Me Love You]]\"\n|-\n| [[Liam Payne]]: \"[[Cry Me a River (Arthur Hamilton song)|Cry Me a River]]\"\n|-\n| [[Niall Horan]]: \"[[So Sick]]\"\n|-\n| [[Louis Tomlinson]]: \"[[Hey There Delilah]]\"\n|-\n| Bootcamp (Day 1)\n| Boys category: \"[[Man in the Mirror]]\"\n| Sing-offs\n| Through to bootcamp day 2 & 3\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"| Bootcamp (Day 3)\n|Harry: \"[[Stop Crying Your Heart Out]]\"\n|rowspan=\"5\"| Solo performances\n|rowspan=\"5\"| Eliminated individually; One Direction formed and put through to Judge's houses\n|-\n|Zayn: unknown\n|-\n|Liam: \"[[Stop Crying Your Heart Out]]\"\n|-\n|Niall: \"[[Champagne Supernova]]\"\n|-\n|Louis: \"[[Make You Feel My Love]]\"\n|-\n|Judges' houses\n|\"[[Torn (Natalie Imbruglia song)|Torn]]\"\n|Free choice\n|Through to live shows\n|-\n| Live show 1\n|\"[[Viva la Vida]]\"\n|Number-one singles\n|Safe\n|-\n| Live show 2\n|\"[[My Life Would Suck Without You]]\"\n|Heroes\n|Safe\n|-\n| Live show 3\n|\"[[Nobody Knows (Pink song)|Nobody Knows]]\"\n|Guilty pleasures\n|Safe\n|-\n| Live show 4\n| \"[[Total Eclipse of the Heart]]\"\n|Halloween\n|Safe\n|-\n| Live show 5\n| \"[[Kids in America (song)|Kids in America]]\"\n|American anthems\n|Safe\n|-\n| Live show 6\n| \"[[Something About the Way You Look Tonight]]\"\n|Songs by [[Elton John]]\n|Safe\n|-\n| Live show 7\n| \"[[All You Need Is Love]]\"\n|Songs by [[The Beatles]]\n|Safe\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Live show 8\n|\"[[Summer of '69]]\" \n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Rock music|Rock]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Safe\n|-\n|\"[[You Are So Beautiful]]\"\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Semi-final\n|\"[[Only Girl (In the World)]]\"\n|Club classics\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Safe\n|-\n|\"[[Chasing Cars]]\"\n|Song to get you to the final\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|Final\n|\"[[Your Song]]\"\n|Contestant's choice\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Safe\n|-\n|\"[[She's the One (World Party song)|She's the One]]\" (with [[Robbie Williams]])\n|Celebrity duet\n|-\n|\"[[Torn (Natalie Imbruglia)|Torn]]\"\n|Contestant's choice\n|Eliminated; Third place\n|}\n\n===2011\u20132012: ''Up All Night''===\nReleased in September 2011, One Direction's debut single, \"[[What Makes You Beautiful]]\", was a commercial and international success. It reached number one on the [[UK Singles Chart]], after becoming the most pre-ordered [[Sony Music Entertainment]] single in history.<ref>{{cite news | first =Lewis | last = Corner |url = http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a335956/one-directions-what-makes-you-beautiful-breaks-pre-order-sales-record.html | title=One Direction's 'What Makes You Beautiful' breaks pre-order sales record |work=[[Digital Spy]]|publisher=Hearst | place = UK|date=19 August 2011|accessdate=19 August 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | first = Alan | last = Jones | url = http://www.musicweek.com/story.asp?sectioncode=22&storycode=1046622 | title = What Makes You Beautiful becomes fastest seller of the year | work= [[Music Week]]  |date = 19 September 2011 |accessdate= 5 January 2012}}</ref> Subsequent singles, \"[[Gotta Be You (One Direction song)|Gotta Be You]]\" and \"[[One Thing (One Direction song)|One Thing]]\", peaked in the UK Singles Chart top ten.<ref>{{cite news| first = Alan | last = Jones |url= http://www.musicweek.com/story.asp?sectioncode=1&storycode=1047553&c=1 |title=UK Singles Chart Analysis: Rihanna equals Adele record |work=[[Music Week]] |date=21 November 2011 |accessdate=11 June 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| first =Alan | last = Jones |url = http://www.musicweek.com/story.asp?sectioncode=1&storycode=1048551&c=1 |title = Official Chart Analysis: Emeli Sande album sells 113k, DJ Fresh single shifts 128k |work= [[Music Week]]  |date=20 February 2012 | accessdate = 17 March 2012}}</ref> In November 2011, they signed a record deal with [[Columbia Records]] in North America.<ref>{{cite web| first = Lewis | last = Corner| url = http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a352201/one-direction-sign-us-record-deal-with-adele-label-columbia.html |title=One Direction sign U.S. record deal with Adele label Columbia | work=[[Digital Spy]]|publisher= Hearst | place = UK |date= 22 November 2011 |accessdate= 14 January 2012}}</ref> [[Steve Barnett (music executive)|Steve Barnett]], the co-chairman of Columbia Records, said it was not a difficult decision to sign One Direction; \"I just thought there was a void, and maybe they could seize and hold it.\"<ref>{{cite news| first =James C, Jr | last = McKinley | url= https://www.nytimes.com/2012/03/24/arts/music/one-direction-and-the-wanted-boy-bands-return.html |work= [[The New York Times]] | title= One Direction and the Wanted: Boy Bands Return | date=23 March 2012}}</ref> That same month, they released ''[[Up All Night (One Direction album)|Up All Night]]'', their debut studio album, in the UK and Ireland. Critically commended for its appeal to the teenage audience,<ref>{{cite news| first = Adam | last = Markovitz | url = http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,20578458,00.html | type = review | title = Up All Night (2012) One Direction |work=Entertainment Weekly|date= 20 March 2012| accessdate =21 March 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url = https://www.usatoday.com/life/music/reviews/story/2012-03-12/one-direction-up-all-night/53502638/1 | title = Listen Up: Stay 'Up All Night' with One Direction|work= USA Today | publisher = [[Gannett Company|Gannett Co]] | date= 13 March 2012 | accessdate= 31 March 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | first = Matthew | last = Chisling | url = http://www.allmusic.com/album/up-all-night-r2324993/review |title=Up All Night&nbsp;\u2013 One Direction| publisher = AllMusic |date=21 November 2011 |accessdate= 5 January 2012}}</ref> it became the UK's fastest-selling debut album of 2011.<ref>{{cite news |url = http://www.capitalfm.com/artists/one-direction/news/thank-fans-up-all-night-chart-success/ |title= One Direction Thank Fans For 'Up All Night' Chart Success |work= [[Capital (radio network)|Capital FM]]|publisher=[[Global Radio]]|date= 28 November 2011 |accessdate=14 January 2012}}</ref> In December 2011, they embarked on their first headlining UK concert tour, the [[Up All Night Tour]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.capitalfm.com/artists/one-direction/news/up-all-night-tour-watford/ |title= One Direction Prepare For 'Up All Night' Tour With Watford Concert |work=[[Capital (radio network)|Capital FM]]|publisher=[[Global Radio]] | date =19 December 2011| accessdate= 27 March 2012|archiveurl= http://www.freezepage.com/1333935031UMDTEVHWRV?url=http://www.capitalfm.com/artists/one-direction/news/up-all-night-tour-watford/ | archivedate = 9 April 2012}}</ref> Originally, the tour was set to end in January 2012.\n\nUpon One Direction's arrival in the US in February 2012, the group embarked on a radio promotion spree, as well as their first North American concert tour as an opening act for [[Big Time Rush (band)|Big Time Rush]], opening 16 shows after they had completed the first leg of the Up All Night Tour.<ref>{{cite news| first =Mark | last = Savage|url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-18083174 |title= The U.S. love affair with British pop|work= News |publisher= BBC|date= 21 May 2010 | accessdate=25 July 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| first =Stephan | last = Lee|url= http://music-mix.ew.com/2012/02/03/one-direction-big-time-rush-exclusive-photo/ | title= Exclusive Photo: One Direction and Big Time Rush unite for North American tour!|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |accessdate= 4 February 2012}}</ref> That month, they announced that an Oceania leg had been added to the tour.<ref>{{cite news |first= Lisa |last= McGarry |url= http://www.unrealitytv.co.uk/x-factor/one-direction-announce-tour-dates-for-australia-and-new-zealand/ |title= One Direction announce 2012 tour dates for Australia and New Zealand |work= Unreality TV |date= 24 February 2012 |accessdate= 31 March 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20120411004659/http://www.unrealitytv.co.uk/x-factor/one-direction-announce-tour-dates-for-australia-and-new-zealand/ |archivedate= 11 April 2012 }}</ref> They made their first US television appearance on ''[[Today (U.S. TV program)|The Today Show]]'', at the [[Rockefeller Center]]; an estimated 15,000 fans descended on the plaza.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/499360/one-direction-the-wanted-the-billboard-cover-story |title=One Direction & The Wanted: The Billboard Cover Story | first =Steven J | last = Horowitz |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date= 27 March 2012 | accessdate =16 April 2012}}</ref> \"What Makes You Beautiful\" was officially released in the United States that same month,<ref>{{cite news| first =Amanda | last = Hasaka |url= http://www.celebuzz.com/2012-02-14/one-directions-debut-single-what-makes-you-beautiful-now-available-on-itunes/ |title=One Direction's Debut Single 'What Makes You Beautiful' Now Available on iTunes! |work= Celebuzz |date=14 February 2012 |accessdate= 15 February 2012}}</ref> where it debuted on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] at number 28, becoming the highest debut for a British act since 1998.<ref name=\"Hot100\">{{cite web |url = http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/504475/one-direction-has-highest-hot-100-debut-for-new-uk-act-since-1998 |title= One Direction Has Highest Hot 100 Debut For New UK Act Since 1998 |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |date= 22 February 2012 |accessdate=13 March 2012}}</ref> On the US ''Billboard'' Hot 100, it reached as high as number four. As of June 2016, it has sold 4.8 million copies in the US<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7408939/ask-billboard-one-directions-career-sales |title = Ask Billboard: One Direction's Career Sales}}</ref> and over 7 million copes worldwide.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/article/19093915/one-direction-hit-12-million-sales-in-less-than-a-year |title = One Direction hit 12 million sales in less than a year|date = 8 February 2012}}</ref> ''Up All Night'' was released internationally in March, and One Direction became the first UK group to have their debut album reach number one in the US,<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.idolator.com/6226811/one-direction-debut-chart-history?safari=1&Exc_D_LessThanPoint002_p1=1 | title=One Direction Debut at #1, Make Album Chart History| date=21 March 2012}}</ref> and were inducted into the ''[[Guinness World Records]]'' as a result.<ref>{{cite news| first = Colin | last = Daniels| url = http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a404538/adele-one-direction-enter-guinness-world-records.html |title=Adele, One Direction enter 'Guinness World Records' | work = [[Digital Spy]] |publisher=Hearst | place = UK |date=7 September 2012 | accessdate =8 September 2012}}</ref> After the album's international release, it topped the charts in sixteen countries.<ref>{{cite news|url = http://www.musicweek.com/news/read/one-direction-to-hold-global-twitter-viewing-party-for-new-concert-dvd/049052 | title = One Direction to hold global Twitter viewing party for new concert DVD | work= [[Music Week]]  | date=30 May 2012 |accessdate= 11 June 2012}}</ref> ''Up All Night'' also became the first album by a boy band to sell 500,000 digital copies in the US and, by August 2012, had sold over 3 million copies worldwide.<ref name = \"Yahoosales\">{{cite news | title = Week Ending Oct. 21, 2012. Albums: Aldean's Fast Train To #1 | url = http://music.yahoo.com/blogs/chart-watch/week-ending-oct-21-2012-albums-aldean-fast-150305200.html | first =Paul | last = Grein |work= Music |publisher = Yahoo! |date= 24 October 2012 | accessdate = 24 October 2012|location= US}}</ref><ref name = \"12millionsales\">{{cite web| first =Dan | last = Lane|url = http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/one-direction-sell-12-million-singles-albums-and-dvd-and-blu-rays-worldwide-1516/ |title = One Direction sell 12 million singles, albums and DVD and Blu-rays worldwide | publisher = [[Official Charts Company]] |date=2 August 2012 |accessdate=2 August 2012}}</ref> It was the third global best-selling album of the year, selling 4.5 million copies.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aria.com.au/documents/RIN2013.pdf|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130409080309/http://www.aria.com.au/documents/RIN2013.pdf|archivedate=2013-04-09|title=Wayback Machine|date=9 April 2013|website=web.archive.org}}</ref> Following the success of the album, a North American leg of the tour was announced later that month.<ref>{{cite news|url= http://idolator.com/6226892/one-direction-north-american-tour-dates |title=One Direction Reveal North American Tour Dates |work= [[Idolator (website)|Idolator]] |date=21 March 2012 |accessdate=31 March 2012}}</ref>\n\nThe ''Up All Night Tour'', comprising 62 shows, was met with positivity both critically and commercially, with critics praising their singing abilities and stage presence, and with tickets selling out in minutes.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/one-direction-live-review-from-hammersmith-171874 |title=One Direction's Hammersmith Apollo gig | first =James | last = Robertson |date=11 January 2012 |work= Daily Mirror |accessdate= 8 April 2012 | archiveurl = http://www.freezepage.com/1333939607CZJAMCVUXO?url=http://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/one-direction-live-review-from-hammersmith-171874 |archivedate=9 April 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.herald.ie/news/one-direction-show-has-fans-up-all-night-2999092.html |title= One Direction show has fans up all night | last =Ryan | first = Alexandra |date= 25 January 2012 |work= [[Evening Herald]] |publisher= [[Independent News & Media]] |accessdate= 8 April 2012|archiveurl= http://www.freezepage.com/1333939933IFYQZGQCXW?url=http://www.herald.ie/news/one-direction-show-has-fans-up-all-night-2999092.html | archivedate= 9 April 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| last =Brandle | first = Lars|title= One Direction Live: Shriek Show in Australia | url = http://www.billboard.com/articles/photos/live/492534/one-direction-live-shriek-show-in-australia| work = [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=19 April 2012|accessdate= 9 July 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| first1 =Cameron | last1 = Adams | last2 = Siobhan | first2 = Duck|url = http://www.heraldsun.com.au/entertainment/music/one-directions-melbourne-concert-sells-out-in-three-minutes/story-e6frf9hf-1226286954743 |title=One Direction's Melbourne concert sells out in three minutes|work=Herald Sun |location= Australia |date= 2 March 2012|accessdate=1 July 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | first =Bridget | last = Jones|url= http://www.stuff.co.nz/auckland/whats-on/6512032/One-Directions-NZ-tour-sold-out |title=One Direction's NZ tour sold out|work= [[Stuff.co.nz|Stuff]] | place = [[New Zealand|NZ]]  | date = 2 March 2012| accessdate= 1 July 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| first = Emily | last = Hewett |url = http://www.metro.co.uk/music/877239-one-direction-tickets-fans-bombard-ticketmaster-as-ebay-touts-capitalise |title= One Direction tickets: Fans bombard Ticketmaster as eBay touts capitalise| work = [[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]]| date= 1 October 2011| accessdate= 1 July 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | title= One Direction to Headline Madison Square Garden December 3, 2012 |url = http://www.kait8.com/story/17325179/one-direction-to-headline-madison-square-garden-december-3-2012 |publisher= [[KAIT]]  |date=3 April 2012 |accessdate=8 April 2012|archiveurl= http://www.freezepage.com/1333943764HSQQZOQYGS?url=http://www.kait8.com/story/17325179/one-direction-to-headline-madison-square-garden-december-3-2012 | archivedate = 9 April 2012}}</ref> A recording of a concert from the tour, ''[[One Direction: Up All Night \u2013 The Live Tour|Up All Night: The Live Tour]]'', was released in May 2012.<ref name=\"musicDVD\">{{cite news | first = Lewis | last = Corner |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a376053/one-direction-perform-moments-on-tour-video.html |title = One Direction perform 'Moments' on tour | type = video | work= [[Digital Spy]] | publisher= Hearst | place = UK |date = 12 April 2012 |accessdate= 27 April 2012}}</ref> In addition to the DVD topping the charts in twenty-five countries, its global sales had exceeded 1 million copies by August 2012.<ref name=\"12millionsales\"/><ref name =DVDWW>{{cite news | first =Rhian | last = Jones |url= http://www.musicweek.com/news/read/one-direction-live-dvd-hits-no1-in-25-countries/049138 | title= One Direction live DVD hits No.1 in 25 countries | work= [[Music Week]]  | date = 8 June 2012 |accessdate=11 June 2012}}</ref> One Direction's first book to be licensed in America, ''Dare to Dream: Life as One Direction'', published in the US in May 2012, topped [[The New York Times Best Seller list|''The New York Times'' Best Seller list]].<ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.nytimes.com/best-sellers-books/2012-06-10/paperback-books/list.html |work=The New York Times | title=Best Sellers | date=10 June 2012 | accessdate = 24 August 2012 | first=Gregory | last=Cowles}}</ref> In June 2012, Nick Gatfield, the chairman and chief executive officer of [[Sony Music Entertainment|Sony Music Entertainment UK]], stated how he expects One Direction to represent a $100&nbsp;million business empire over 2013.<ref name = \"business empire\">{{cite news| first =Jocelyn | last = Vena | url = http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1687496/one-direction-hundred-million-dollar-business.jhtml |title = One Direction Set To Become Booming $100 Million Business|publisher=[[MTV News]]|date=15 June 2012 |accessdate= 15 June 2012}}</ref> Gatfield stated, \"What you might not know about One Direction is that they already represent a $50&nbsp;million business and that's a figure we expect to double next year\".<ref name=\"business empire\"/> In August 2012, the group's record sales exceeded 8 million singles, 3&nbsp;million albums, and 1&nbsp;million DVDs, and they performed \"What Makes You Beautiful\" at the [[2012 Summer Olympics closing ceremony]] in London, which represented the handover to Rio de Janeiro as the host of the [[2016 Summer Olympics]].<ref name=\"12millionsales\"/><ref>{{cite news | first =Kia | last = Makarechi |url = http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/08/12/one-direction-closing-ceremony-olympics_n_1770803.html |title= One Direction & Closing Ceremony: Olympics Get A Dose Of 'What Makes You Beautiful' | work = [[The Huffington Post]]| date= 12 August 2012 |accessdate=13 August 2012}}</ref> One Direction were the biggest winners of the [[2012 MTV Video Music Awards]] winning their three nominations on 6 September 2012, including [[MTV Video Music Award for Best New Artist|Best New Artist]].<ref name= videomusicawards>{{cite news| place = UK | first =Amelia | last = Butterfly |url = http://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/19515754 | title= One Direction win three MTV Video Music Awards in LA | work = Newsbeat | publisher = BBC|date=7 September 2012|accessdate=7 September 2012}}</ref>\n\n[[File:One Direction Sydney 6.jpg|thumb|right|One Direction performing on their [[Up All Night Tour]], April 2012]]\n\nIn April 2012, an American band that went by the same name filed a [[trademark infringement]] lawsuit.<ref name = trademark>{{cite news| first =Rhian | last = Jones |url= http://www.musicweek.com/news/read/one-direction-sued-for-trademark-infringement/048557 |title=One Direction sued for trademark infringement |work= [[Music Week]]  | date= 11 April 2012 |accessdate= 27 April 2012}}</ref> According to the lawsuit, the US band had been using the name since 2009, recorded two albums and filed an application to register the trademark name in the US in February 2011.<ref name=trademark/> The US band said they were entitled to three times the profits made by the UK band, as well as compensatory damages in excess of US$1&nbsp;million.<ref name=trademark/> The lawsuit claimed that Syco and Sony Music \"chose to ignore the plaintiff's rights and wilfully infringed them\" after they realised in early 2011 that the two bands shared the same name.<ref name=trademark/> Syco Records subsequently counter-sued, suggesting the US group was trying to make money from One Direction's success and that the boy band was the first to use the name in US interstate commerce.<ref name=lawsuit/> The [[BBC]] reported in September 2012 that the UK group won the legal dispute over the right to keep using their band name; the US band changed its name to Uncharted Shores.<ref name=lawsuit/> The change of name was announced in a joint statement that also noted both groups were happy with the outcome.<ref name = lawsuit>{{cite web |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/19473197 |title= One Direction win fight against U.S. band to keep name | work =[[Newsbeat]] |publisher=BBC |date=7 September 2012|accessdate=8 September 2012}}</ref>\n\n===2012\u20132013: ''Take Me Home''===\n[[File:One Direction at the Logies Awards 2012.jpg|thumb|left|One Direction at red carpet of the [[Logie Awards of 2012]] in [[Melbourne]]]]\n\nIn September 2012, \"[[Live While We're Young]]\", the lead single from the group's second album, was released, and was a global success. It reached the top ten in almost every country it charted in and recorded the highest one-week opening sales figure for a song by a non-US artist in the US.<ref>{{cite news| first =Tina| last = Hart|url = http://www.musicweek.com/news/read/one-direction-have-fastest-selling-single-by-a-uk-artist/052114 | title = One Direction achieve fastest-selling single by a UK act in the U.S. |work= Music Week |date= 21 October 2012 |accessdate=11 October 2012|location=United Kingdom}}</ref> A second single, \"[[Little Things (One Direction song)|Little Things]]\", resulted in the band's second [[List of UK Singles Chart number ones of the 2010s|number one single]] in the UK.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/one-direction-score-number-1-single-and-album-__2564/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180830142315/http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/one-direction-score-number-1-single-and-album-__2564/|archivedate=2018-08-30|title=One Direction score Number 1 single AND album!|date=30 August 2018|website=web.archive.org}}</ref> In November 2012, One Direction's second studio album, ''[[Take Me Home (One Direction album)|Take Me Home]]'', was released.<ref name=\"TMH\">{{cite news |url= https://itunes.apple.com/nl/album/take-me-home/id572141438|title= Take Me Home | publisher =[[iTunes Store]] |agency=[[Apple Inc.|Apple]] |accessdate=16 November 2012|language=Dutch| location = Netherlands}}</ref> It was an international hit, reaching number one in over 35 countries. Upon reaching number one on the ''[[Billboard 200]]'', the group became the first boy band in US chart history to record two number-one albums in the same calendar year alongside becoming the first group since 2008 to record two number-one albums in the same year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/474059/one-directions-take-me-home-debuts-at-no-1-with-years-third-biggest-opening|title=One Direction's 'Take Me Home' Debuts at No. 1 With Year's Third-Biggest Opening|website=Billboard}}</ref> One Direction became the first group ever to have their first two albums reach atop the ''Billboard 200''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/music/9694957/One-Direction-make-US-chart-history-with-Take-Me-Home.html|title=One Direction make US chart history with 'Take Me Home'|date=22 November 2012|website=Telegraph.co.uk}}</ref> ''Take Me Home'' sold 540,000 copies in its first week in the US, debuted atop the ''Billboard'' 200, and topped the charts in more than thirty-four other countries.<ref name = \"USTMHdebut\">{{cite web|url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/474059/one-directions-take-me-home-debuts-at-no-1-with-years-third-biggest-opening |title=One Direction's 'Take Me Home' Debuts at No. 1 With Year's Third-Biggest Opening | work=Billboard |date=20 November 2012|accessdate= 22 November 2012 | location = US}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| first =Tina | last = Hart|url = http://www.musicweek.com/news/read/imagem-music-signs-one-direction-hit-writer-fiona-bevan/052709 |title=Imagem Music signs One Direction hit-writer Fiona Bevan |work=[[Music Week]] |date=29 November 2012 | accessdate =1 December 2012|location= United Kingdom}}</ref> Additionally, ''Up All Night'' and ''Take Me Home'' were the number three and number four best-selling albums of 2012 globally, each album selling over 4.4&nbsp;million units worldwide.<ref name=\"Modest Management\">{{cite web|url=http://www.modestmanagement.com/one-direction/ |title=One Direction |publisher=Modest Management |accessdate=2 August 2014}}</ref> The album and \"Little Things\" both debuted at number one in the UK simultaneously, making One Direction the youngest act in British chart history to achieve that.<ref>{{cite news | first = Alan | last = Jones | url = http://www.musicweek.com/businessanalysis/read/official-charts-analysis-one-direction-youngest-ever-act-to-hit-no-1-in-albums-and-singles-lists/052592 |title=Official Charts Analysis: One Direction youngest ever act to score No. 1 Album and Single simultaneously |work=[[Music Week]] |date=19 November 2012 |accessdate=19 November 2012| location = UK}}</ref>\n\n''Take Me Home'' was written in groups and has an average of just under five songwriters per track. Savan Kotecha, Rami Yacoub, and Carl Falk, who composed One Direction's hits \"What Makes You Beautiful\" and \"One Thing\", spent six months in Stockholm developing songs for the album, and were able to shape melodies around their tones.<ref name =Wolk>{{cite news| first = Douglas | last = Wol|url= http://entertainment.time.com/2012/11/13/one-directions-songwriters-theyre-what-make-the-boy-band-beautiful/ | title = One Direction's songwriters: They're what make the boy band beautiful|work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]] |date=28 June 2012 |accessdate=25 August 2012}}</ref> One Direction began recording the album in May 2012, in Stockholm at Kinglet Studios.<ref name=credits>{{cite AV media notes |title = Take Me Home |others=One Direction |year=2012 |type=liner notes |publisher=[[Syco Records]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url= http://www.mtv.co.uk/news/one-direction/354656-one-direction-sweden |title= One Direction Recording Second Album |publisher=MTV News |date=11 May 2012 |accessdate=25 August 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url= http://www.capitalfm.com/artists/one-direction/news/new-album/ |title= One Direction Enjoy 'Amazing Day' In The Studio Recording New Album |publisher=Capital (Global Radio)|date=12 May 2012 |accessdate=25 August 2012}}</ref> The album cover artwork features the group surrounding a traditional British K2 [[red telephone box]], a familiar sight on the streets of the UK.<ref>{{cite web|last=Wheeler |first=Rachael |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/one-direction-reveal-album-artwork-1289666 |title=One Direction reveal album artwork for Take Me Home \u2013 3am & Mirror Online |work=Daily Mirror |date=30 August 2012 |accessdate=2 August 2014}}</ref> ''Take Me Home'' garnered mixed reviews from [[music journalism|music critics]]. There was praise for its quality of production, while it was criticised for its generic, rushed nature.<ref>{{cite news| first =Matt | last = Collar |url = http://www.allmusic.com/album/take-me-home-mw0002418914 |title = Take Me Home (CD \u2013 Sony Music Distribution #88725475972) | publisher = [[AllMusic]]| date = 11 November 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |first= Al | last = Fox |url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/music/reviews/fh8r | type = review |title= One Direction \u2013 Take Me Home |publisher= [[BBC Music]] |date= 12 November 2012|accessdate= 16 November 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | type = review | first = Adam | last = Markovitz |url=http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,20643783,00.html | title = Take Me Home \u2013 One Direction | work = [[Entertainment Weekly]] |date=11 November 2012 | accessdate= 16 November 2012}}</ref><ref name=NYT/><ref name=Guardian/><ref name=NZH/>\n\nOne Direction performed \"Little Things\" at the 2012 [[Royal Variety Performance]] in the presence of [[Elizabeth II|Queen Elizabeth II]], and headlined a sold-out show at New York City's [[Madison Square Garden]] on 3 December 2012.<ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/queen-elizabeth-II/9690193/Royal-Variety-Performance-2012-One-Direction-and-Girls-Aloud-sing-for-The-Queen.html |title=Royal Variety Performance 2012: One Direction and Girls Aloud sing for The Queen |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]| date= 20 November 2012 | accessdate = 24 November 2012 |location=London}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/photos/live/473866/one-direction-headlines-sold-out-show-at-madison-square-garden |title=One Direction Headlines Sold-Out Show at Madison Square Garden|date=4 December 2012| accessdate =5 December 2012|work=Billboard| first =Andrew | last = Hampp}}</ref> In February 2013, One Direction released a cover version of \"[[One Way or Another]]\" and \"[[Teenage Kicks]]\", \"[[One Way or Another (Teenage Kicks)]]\", as the 2013 [[Comic Relief]] single.<ref name=\"Robertson\">{{cite news|url= https://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/one-direction-reflect-on-life-changing-1535079 |title='We are the most selfish people ever': One Direction reflect on 'life changing' charity trip to Africa 'slums'|date=15 January 2013|accessdate=16 February 2013 | work =Metro| first =James | last = Robertson}}</ref> As part of their involvement with the UK charity, One Direction travelled to Ghana to volunteer at a children's hospital, visit a school and make donations.\n\nFollowing the release of ''Take Me Home'', One Direction embarked on their second concert tour in February 2013, the [[Take Me Home Tour (One Direction)|Take Me Home Tour]].<ref>{{cite news| first =Jocelyn | last = Vena|url= http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1682975/one-direction-tour-dates.jhtml | title= One Direction Announce U.S. Dates on 2013 World Tour | work = News |publisher=MTV |date=12 April 2012 |accessdate=20 April 2012}}</ref> The concert tour consisted of 123 shows in Europe, North America, Asia, and Oceania. Ticket sales reached 300,000 within a day of release in the UK and Ireland, which included a six-date sell-out at [[The O2 Arena|the O<sub>2</sub> Arena]] in London.<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.mtv.co.uk/news/one-direction/349694-one-direction-tickets |title=One Direction Fans in Ticket-Buying Frenzy | publisher =MTV |date=26 February 2012 |accessdate=20 April 2012}}</ref> In the Australian and New Zealand markets, tickets grossed US$15.7&nbsp;million, with all 190,000 tickets being sold for the eighteen shows to be held.<ref>{{cite news| first =Brittany | last = Stack |url= http://www.dailytelegraph.com.au/news/how-one-direction-cashed-in-on-their-hugely-successful-australian-tour/story-e6freuy9-1226341685202 |title=How One Direction cashed in on their hugely successful Australian tour |work=[[The Daily Telegraph (Sydney)|The Daily Telegraph]] | place = AU|date= 29 April 2012 |accessdate=11 June 2012}}</ref> The tour received critical acclaim from music critics who praised the band's live vocals and their performance abilities and was a commercial success, selling 1,635,000 tickets from 134 shows.<ref name=\"Box Office\">{{cite web|url=http://onedirectionmusic.com/ |title=One Direction &#124; Welcome to the One Direction website! |publisher=Onedirectionmusic.com |accessdate=2 August 2014}}</ref> In total, the tour grossed $114 million. The [[Official Charts Company]] revealed that One Direction had sold 2,425,000 records in the UK by February 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/the-brit-awards-2013-the-real-winners-revealed-1869/|title= The BRIT Awards 2013: The biggest selling nominees revealed|publisher= [[Official Charts Company]]| first =Dan | last = Lane|date= 20 February 2013 | accessdate = 21 February 2013}}</ref>\n\n===2013\u20132014: ''Midnight Memories'' and ''This Is Us''===\n[[File:One Direction 2, 2013.jpg|thumb|right|One Direction in [[Glasgow]] on their [[Take Me Home Tour (One Direction)|Take Me Home Tour]] in February 2013]]\n\n\"[[Best Song Ever (song)|Best Song Ever]]\", the lead single of the group's then-upcoming third studio album ''[[Midnight Memories]]'', was released on 22 July 2013. The song<ref>{{citation|last=Brandie|first=Lars|date=26 June 2013|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1568160/one-direction-tease-best-song-ever-release-new-movie-trailer|title=One Direction Tease 'Best Song Ever'; Release New Movie Trailer | newspaper = [[Billboard.com|Billboard]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title= One Direction Announce New Single 'Best Song Ever'| place = UK | url= http://www.mtv.co.uk/news/one-direction/384889-one-direction-new-single-best-song-ever-this-is-us-new-trailer |publisher= MTV| accessdate= 1 July 2013}}</ref> is their highest charting single in the US to date, reaching number two.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/one-direction|title=One Direction Chart History|website=Billboard|accessdate=19 July 2019}}</ref> It broke the [[Vevo#Record holders|24-Hour Vevo Record]] with 10.9&nbsp;million views on YouTube (this was the second time the band held the record with \"Live While We're Young\" attaining 8.2&nbsp;million views on 20 September 2012).<ref>{{cite web|title=One Direction's 'Best Song Ever' Breaks One-Day Vevo Record|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/4336507/one-directions-best-song-ever-breaks-one-day-vevo-record|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=One Direction beat Justin Bieber VEVO record with new music video|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/music/news/a408584/one-direction-beat-justin-bieber-vevo-record-with-new-music-video.html|work=[[Digital Spy]]|date=27 September 2012}}</ref> ''[[One Direction: This Is Us]]'', a 3D documentary and concert film about the group directed by [[Morgan Spurlock]] and produced by Spurlock, Ben Winston, Adam Milano and Simon Cowell, was released by [[TriStar Pictures]] on 30 August 2013.<ref name=\"3Dfilm\">{{cite news | url = http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/474195/one-direction-3d-film-gets-super-director|title= One Direction 3D Film Gets 'Super' Director| first = Marc | last = Schneider|work=Billboard|date= 13 November 2012|accessdate=15 November 2012|location= New York}}</ref> The film was a box office success, topping the UK and US box offices and grossing over $60&nbsp;million worldwide, and became the fourth highest-grossing concert movie.<ref name=autogenerated6>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/genres/chart/?id=musicconcert.htm |title=Music Concert Movies at the Box Office |publisher=Box Office Mojo |date=8 January 2014 |accessdate=2 August 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 May 2013, the band announced their first all-stadium tour, the [[Where We Are Tour (One Direction)|Where We Are Tour]]. Tickets for the tour sold out in minutes and more shows were added due to \"overwhelming demand.\"<ref>{{cite web | url=https://chicago.suntimes.com/news/2013/12/4/18541298/one-direction-adds-show-to-chicago-stop-on-tour |title = One Direction adds show to Chicago stop on tour|date = 4 December 2013}}</ref> On 23 November 2013, in support of ''Midnight Memories'', the band participated in \"1D Day\",<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.1dday.com/ |title=Welcome to 1D Day \u2013 1D Day \u2013 One Direction |publisher=1dday.com |date=25 November 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131213102853/http://www.1dday.com/gb/home | archivedate= 13 December 2013 | accessdate=19 January 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/showbiz/news/a533434/one-direction-1d-day-live-stream-watch.html |title=One Direction '1D Day' Live Stream \u2013 watch \u2013 Showbiz News |work=Digital Spy |date=23 November 2013 |accessdate=19 January 2014}}</ref> a day dedicated to One Direction fans. The day constituted of a landmark 7.5-hour socially interactive YouTube live-stream featuring live band performances, celebrity guests including, [[Simon Cowell]], [[Cindy Crawford]], [[Piers Morgan]], and [[Jerry Springer]]. On 28 October 2013, the second single from ''Midnight Memories'', \"[[Story of My Life (One Direction song)|Story of My Life]],\" was released, charting at number six in the US and at number two in the UK, while charting at number one in countries such as Mexico, Spain, Bulgaria, Denmark, and Ireland.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/One-Direction|title=One Direction Chart History|website=Billboard}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/singles-chart/20131208/7501/|title=Official Singles Chart Top 100 &#124; Official Charts Company|website=www.officialcharts.com}}</ref>\n\n[[File:One_Direction_at_the_New_Jersey_concert_on_7.2.13_IMG_4238_(9206417991).jpg|thumb|left|The band performing in [[East Rutherford]], New Jersey on 2 July 2013]]\n\n''Midnight Memories'' was released globally on 25 November 2013. It debuted at number one in the UK and in the US, making them the first group to debut at number one on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] with its first three albums, and the second to reach the top after [[The Monkees]] in 1967.<ref name=\"Billboard record\">{{cite news|first=Keith|last=Caulfield|title=One Direction Scores Historic Third No. 1 Album on Billboard 200 Chart|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5812384/one-direction-scores-historic-third-no-1-album-on-billboard-200-chart|work=Billboard|date=4 December 2013|accessdate=4 December 2013}}</ref> The album was described by the band as edgier and as having a \"slightly rockier tone\" than their previous efforts.<ref>{{cite web|last= Percival| first= Ashley|title= One Direction Big Announcement: 'Where We Are' Stadium Tour Confirmed For 2014|url= http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2013/05/16/one-direction-big-announcement-where-we-are-tour-2014_n_3284795.html |work= The Huffington Post|accessdate=1 July 2013| date= 16 May 2013}}</ref> Despite being released at the year's end, it was the best-selling album worldwide in 2013 with 4 million copies sold globally.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-28599903 | title=One Direction top global album chart| work=BBC News| date=August 2014}}</ref> To promote the album, the band performed on both the [[The X Factor (U.S. TV series)|American]] and [[The X Factor (UK TV series)|British]] versions of ''The X Factor''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.heatworld.com/Celeb-News/2013/10/One-Direction-confirmed-for-The-X-Factor/|title=One Direction confirmed for The X Factor 2013 live shows|publisher=heatworld.com|last=Lewis|first=Anna|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131018011227/http://www.heatworld.com/Celeb-News/2013/10/One-Direction-confirmed-for-The-X-Factor/|archivedate=18 October 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2013, One Direction broke yet another UK sales record with the DVD and [[Blu-ray]] release of ''This Is Us''. Nearly 270,000 copies of the film were sold in the UK within three days of its release, beating the record previously set by ''[[Michael Jackson: This Is It|Michael Jackson's This Is It]]'' in 2010 by 10,000 copies.<ref name=\"Official Charts\">{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/one-direction-beat-michael-jacksons-chart-record-2695/#.Ur4VQbWDpK0.twitter |title=One Direction beat Michael Jackson's chart record |publisher=Officialcharts.com |date=23 December 2013 |accessdate=19 January 2014}}</ref> The group was named among the Top Global artists of 2013 by the [[International Federation of the Phonographic Industry|IFPI]] because of strong digital downloads, physical albums, on-demand streams, and music videos.<ref name=\"IFPI\">{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/one-direction-named-top-global-recording-artist-in-new-award-9093917.html|title=One Direction named top Global Recording Artist in new award|work=The Independent|date= 30 January 2014|accessdate=30 January 2014|location=London|first=Adam|last=Sherwin}}</ref>\n\nThe band embarked on the Where We Are Tour on 25 April 2014, and it was concluded on 5 October 2014. Playing 69 shows with an average of 49,848 fans per show, the tour grossed over $290 million, becoming the [[List of highest-grossing concert tours|highest-grossing concert tour]] in 2014, the 15th [[List of highest-grossing concert tours|highest-grossing concert tour]] of all time, and the highest-grossing tour of all time by a vocal group.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2015/03/24/these-were-the-10-highest-grossing-tours-of-2014/|title=These Were The 10 Highest-Grossing Tours Of 2014|first=Hugh|last=McIntyre|website=Forbes|accessdate=19 July 2019}}</ref> The tour was attended by 3.4 million fans.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6281518/one-direction-where-we-are-tour-three-million|title=One Direction's Where We Are Tour Attended by 3.4 Million Fans|website=Billboard|accessdate=19 July 2019}}</ref> In August of that same year, the group released their third book, ''One Direction: Where We Are: Our Band, Our Story: 100% Official''.\n\n=== 2014\u20132015: ''Four'' ===\n[[File:OnedirectionWWATchile.jpg|thumb|right|One Direction on stage in [[Santiago]], Chile on 14 April 2014 during their [[Where We Are Tour (One Direction)|Where We Are Tour]] ]]\nOn 21 July 2014, One Direction announced ''[[One Direction: Where We Are - The Concert Film]]'', a film which documents the concerts of 28 and 29 June 2014 that took place in [[San Siro Stadium]] during their [[Where We Are Tour (One Direction)|Where We Are Tour]]. After the announcement, the band announced the film would also have a limited 10\u201311 October 2014 international cinema release before its home media release in November 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/Where-We-Are-Live-Stadium/dp/B00KH0VSOU/ref=sr_1_1?s=dvd&ie=UTF8&qid=1400834967&sr=1-1&keywords=B00KH0VSOU&tag=smarturl-gb-21 |title=Where We Are: Live From San Siro Stadium [DVD&#93;: Amazon.co.uk: One Direction: DVD & Blu-ray |accessdate=25 July 2014}}</ref> The group also released an autobiography book titled ''Who We Are'' on 25 September 2014.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.teenvogue.com/entertainment/books/2014-07/one-direction-autobiography-who-we-are | title=Attention, Directioners: 1D Is Releasing an Autobiography! Here's the Scoop on Your New Favorite Book | work=Teen Vogue | accessdate=13 September 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 September 2014, One Direction announced their fourth studio album to be titled ''[[Four (One Direction album)|Four]]'', set to be released on 17 November 2014.<ref name=\"New Album Four (Time)\">{{cite news|last1=Locker|first1=Melissa|title=One Direction Announces New Album Four, Out November 17|url=https://time.com/3303214/one-direction-four-new-album-release-date/|accessdate=8 September 2014|work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|agency=[[Time Inc.]]|date=8 September 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"New Album Four (LA Times)\">{{cite news|last1=Kennedy|first1=Gerrick D.|title=One Direction to release new album 'Four' on Nov. 17|url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/music/posts/la-et-ms-one-direction-to-release-new-album-four-on-nov-17-20140908-story.html |accessdate=8 September 2014 |agency= [[Tribune Publishing]]|work=Los Angeles Times |date=8 September 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"New Album Four (Billboard)\">{{cite news |last1=Lynch |first1=Joe |title= One Direction Reveal New Album 'Four,' Release Free Song (for 24 Hours Only) |url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6243989/one-direction-four-new-album-fireproof|accessdate=8 September 2014|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |agency=[[Prometheus Global Media]] |date=8 September 2014}}</ref> As part of the announcement, one of the songs from the album, \"Fireproof\" was released for free download for 24 hours on their official website.<ref name=\"New Album Four (Time)\"/><ref name=\"New Album Four (LA Times)\"/><ref name=\"New Album Four (Billboard)\"/> \"[[Steal My Girl]]\", the album's lead single, was released on 29 September 2014,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6251459/one-direction-announces-next-four-album-single-steal-my-girl-due-late-september|title=One Direction Announces 'Four' Album Lead Single 'Steal My Girl,' Due Late September \u2013 Billboard|date=14 September 2014|work=Billboard|accessdate=26 October 2014}}</ref> \nreceiving critical acclaim for its classic rock sound.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/article/2014/09/29/one-direction-steal-my-girl/|title=One Direction channels Journey, gets dad-friendly with 'Steal My Girl'|website=EW.com}}</ref> The second single from the album, \"[[Night Changes]]\", was released on 14 November, three days before the album's release. It also achieve platinum status, selling over one million units in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/|title=Gold & Platinum|website=RIAA}}</ref> ''Four'' was released on 17 November 2014, topping the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] and the [[UK Album Chart]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://m.billboard.com/entry/view/id/108201 | title = One Direction's 'Four' Makes Historic No. 1 Debut on Billboard 200 Chart | first= Keith |last=Caulfield | work = Billboard | date = 26 November 2014 | accessdate = 28 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/four-scores-one-direction-a-third-consecutive-official-albums-chart-number-1-3302/|title=Four scores One Direction a third Official Albums Chart Number 1|publisher=}}</ref> In total, in debuted at number one in 18 countries, selling 3.2 million copies.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lthqofficial.com/news/2018/11/17/fourth-anniversary-of-one-directions-album-four|title=Fourth Anniversary of One Direction's Album, Four \u2014 LTHQ Official &#124; Louis Tomlinson &#124; We Made It|website=LTHQ Official}}</ref> It became the top charted album on [[iTunes]] in 67 countries.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mashable.com/2014/09/08/one-direction-new-album-four-fireproof/|title=10 Fans Freaking Out About One Direction's New Album, Free Song|first=Brian Anthony|last=Hernandez|website=Mashable}}</ref> One Direction became the only group in the 58-year history of the ''Billboard'' 200 albums chart to have their first four albums debut at number one.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Caufield|first1=Keith|title=One Direction's 'Four' Makes Historic No. 1 Debut on Billboard 200 Chart|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6327789/one-direction-four-no-1-debut-billboard-200|publisher=Billboard.com|accessdate=20 October 2015}}</ref> In February 2015, the group embarked on their fourth world tour and second all-stadium tour, the [[On the Road Again Tour]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/music/direction-announces-u-s-stadium-tour-2015-article-1.1985235|title=One Direction announces 2015 U.S. stadium tour as part of \u2018On The Road Again\u2019 tour|first=Kirthana|last=Ramisetti|work=New York Daily News|accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref> grossing $208 million, making it the second highest-grossing tour of 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6770115/billboard-touring-conference-winners-one-direction-ed-sheeran|title=Billboard Touring Awards: One Direction, Ed Sheeran & The Grateful Dead Big Winners|date=20 November 2015|website=Billboard|accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== 2015\u20132018: Malik's departure, ''Made in the A.M.'' and hiatus===\n{{Main|Made in the A.M.}}\n\nOn 25 March 2015, the band released a statement announcing Malik's departure.<ref name=\"inveterate\">{{cite web | url=http://www.inveterate.co.uk/music/one-direction-zayn-malik-confirms-departure-from-band/145871/ | title=One Direction: Zayn Malik Confirms Departure From Band | publisher=Inveterate | date=25 March 2015 | accessdate=23 March 2015 | last=Abbey | first=Lewis | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150329001801/http://www.inveterate.co.uk/music/one-direction-zayn-malik-confirms-departure-from-band/145871 | archivedate=29 March 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Zayn Malik officially quits One Direction|url=http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2015/03/25/zayn-malik-leaves-one-direction/|publisher=[[Fox News Channel]]|accessdate=25 March 2015|date=25 March 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150325193633/http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2015/03/25/zayn-malik-leaves-one-direction/|archivedate=25 March 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Lynch|first1=Joe|title=Zayn Malik Explains One Direction Exit: 'I Have To Do What Feels Right in My Heart'|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6509661/zayn-malik-one-direction-exit-explanation|accessdate=25 March 2015|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|agency=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|date=25 March 2015|location=United States}}</ref> The group made their first official public appearance as a four-piece on ''[[The Late Late Show with James Corden]]'' on 14 May, where they confirmed that they would continue working without a new fifth member.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/article/one-direction-interview-zayn-malik-james-corden-late-late-show|title=One Direction Discusses Zayn Malik's Departure with James Corden: We Were a Little Bit Angry|date=15 May 2015|publisher=}}</ref> The On the Road Again tour concluded on 31 October 2015 after playing eighty shows in Australia, Asia, Africa, Europe, and North America. Grossing $208 million, over 2.3 million tickets were sold.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2016/01/12/these-were-the-highest-grossing-tours-of-2015/|title=The Highest-Grossing Tours Of 2015|first=Hugh|last=McIntyre|website=Forbes}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Chicago IMG 9077 (21423367939).jpg|thumb|right|The group performing as a four piece at [[Soldier Field]], Chicago in 2015]]\nOn 31 July 2015, the group released \"[[Drag Me Down]]\" without promotional material or announcement. Despite this, it still topped the charts in multiple countries, including France and Australia, making the song their first single to reach number one in those respective countries. It also reached number one in multiple other countries, including Ireland and the UK, while charting third in the United States. The single was the first single from their fifth studio album, ''[[Made in the A.M.]]'', and the first material released by the group after Malik's departure.<ref>{{cite web|title=One Direction Shares First Track Without Zayn Malik, 'Drag Me Down'|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6649246/one-direction-shares-first-track-without-zayn-malik-drag-me-down|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=31 July 2015|date=31 July 2015}}</ref> Following the release, it was revealed that the group would be going on hiatus in 2016.<ref name=\"2016break\">{{cite web | url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/6806071/one-direction-x-factor-infinity-history-video-fans | title=One Direction Makes Final 'X Factor' Appearance Before Hiatus, Thanks Fans in New Video | work=Billboard | date=13 December 2015 | accessdate=13 December 2015}}</ref> On 22 September, the title for the fifth studio album, ''Made in the A.M.'', was officially announced along with promotional single \"[[Infinity (One Direction song)|Infinity]]\" being released.<ref>[https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/made-in-the-am-one-direction-announce-new-album-title-and-single-infinity-10513171.html \"Made in the A.M: One Direction announce new album title and single 'Infinity'\"]. The Independent. Retrieved 25 October 2015</ref> The group began to reveal the track listing on their [[Snapchat]] stories to which it was later confirmed on [[iTunes]].<ref>[http://www.etonline.com/news/173824_one_direction_made_the_am_tracklist_revealed_via_snapchat/ \"One Direction's 'Made in the A.M.' Tracklist Revealed Via Snapchat\"]. E!. Retrieved 25 October 2015</ref> In October, another single, \"[[Perfect (One Direction song)|Perfect]],\" was released. It reached the ''Billboard'' top ten, making it the group's second consecutive (after \"Drag Me Down\") and fifth overall top ten hit, breaking [[The Beatles]]' record for the most top ten Hot 100 debuts among bands.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6745031/one-direction-beatles-record-fifth-top-10-debut-hot-100|title=One Direction Beats Beatles' Record With Fifth Top 10 Debut on Hot 100|website=Billboard}}</ref>\n\n''Made in the A.M.'' was released on 13 November 2015,<ref>[http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6706833/one-direction-justin-bieber-album-release-november-13-poll \"One Direction & Justin Bieber Album Release Showdown Set for November 13?\"]. ''Billboard''. Retrieved 25 October 2015</ref> topping the charts in the UK among other countries while reaching number two in the U.S. It was the sixth-best selling album of 2015. At the 2015 [[American Music Awards of 2015|American Music Awards]] on 22 November, One Direction won the award for [[American Music Award for Artist of the Year|Artist of the Year]] for the second year in succession.<ref name=\"AMA\">{{cite news|title=American Music Awards 2015: Check Out All the Winners Here|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/events/amas/6770317/american-music-awards-2015-winners-list-amas|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=24 November 2015}}</ref> Louis Tomlinson later confirmed that the break would be around 18 months. On 13 December, One Direction performed on ''The X Factor'' final. Their last televised performance as a group, before their hiatus, was on ''[[Dick Clark's New Year's Rockin' Eve]]'' on 31 December 2015.<ref name=thewrap-1d2016>{{cite web|title=One Direction Returns to Headline 'Dick Clark's New Year's Rockin' Eve' Billboard Party|url=https://www.thewrap.com/one-direction-returns-to-headline-dick-clarks-new-years-rockin-eve-billboard-party/|website=TheWrap|accessdate=24 November 2015|date=18 November 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 January 2016, ''[[Us Weekly]]'' published a report claiming that the group's hiatus would become a permanent split, with a \"source\" citing that each of the four remaining group members did not renew their contracts following the completion of the On The Road Again Tour in October 2015.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Blynn|first1=Jamie|title=One Direction Is Splitting, Extended Hiatus to Become a Permanent Break|url=http://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/one-direction-is-splitting-hiatus-to-become-a-permanent-break-w161510|accessdate=13 January 2016|work=[[Us Weekly]]|agency=[[Jann Wenner|Wenner Media]] [[Limited liability company|LLC]]|date=13 January 2016|location=United States}}</ref> Representatives for the group denied said-report in a statement to ''Billboard'', stating, \"nothing has changed regarding hiatus plans for the group, and all will be revealed in due time from the band members' own mouths.\"<ref>{{cite news|last1=Strecker|first1=Eric|title=One Direction Breakup Rumors: 'Nothing Has Changed' Since Hiatus, Says Source|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/6842942/one-direction-break-up-rumors-not-true|accessdate=13 January 2016|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|agency=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|date=13 January 2016|location=United States}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Hegarty|first1=Tasha|title=One Direction deny their 'hiatus' is a permanent split|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/music/news/a779897/one-direction-deny-their-extended-hiatus-is-a-permanent-split-and-is-still-just-temporary/|website=[[Digital Spy]]|accessdate=13 January 2016|location=United Kingdom|date=13 January 2016}}</ref> By May 2017, all members of the group had released solo singles.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7808577/one-direction-solo-singles-ranked-list|title=Every One Direction Solo Single, Ranked|work=Billboard|date=25 May 2017|first=Andrew|last=Unterberger}}</ref> Despite saying the hiatus would last 18 months, the band still are yet to confirm when they will reform.\n\nAt the [[2017 Brit Awards]], One Direction won the Video of the Year award for their song \"[[History (One Direction song)|History]]\". Payne accepted the award on the behalf of the band.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2986071/one-direction-respond-2017-brit-award/|title=ALL FOUR ONE DIRECTION MEMBERS RESPOND TO THEIR NEW BRIT AWARD|work=MTV News|date=22 February 2017|first=Madeline|last=Roth}}</ref> In February 2018, it was reported that the group has folded its touring company after having applied for removal within the [[Companies House]] registry in October 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/newsbeat-43055424|title=There's a new sign One Direction might be over|date=14 February 2018||website=Bbc.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://nz.news.yahoo.com/one-direction-fold-touring-company-185107831.html|title=One Direction fold touring company|website=Nz.news.yahoo.com}}</ref>\n\n==Artistry==\n{{Listen\n| filename    = What Makes You Beautiful.ogg\n| title       = \"What Makes You Beautiful\"\n| description = One Direction's debut single, \"[[What Makes You Beautiful]]\", features a prominent guitar-based chorus and [[guitar riff|riff]].<ref name=\"DS1\">{{cite web| first =Robert | last = Copsey| url = http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/singlesreviews/a338401/one-direction-what-makes-you-beautiful-single-review.html |title= One Direction: 'What Makes You Beautiful | type = single review |work= [[Digital Spy]] |publisher= Hearst | place = UK| date= 11 September 2011 | accessdate=25 July 2012}}</ref> It also contains [[cowbell (instrument)|cowbell]] instrumentation,<ref name = \"cowbell\" /> and the [[middle eight]] consists of an \"oh na na na\" hook.<ref name=\"NME\">{{cite news |url = http://www.nme.com/blog/index.php?blog=148&title=one_direction_what_makes_you_beautiful_r&more=1&c=1&tb=1&pb=1 |title = One Direction, 'What Makes You Beautiful' | type = review |work= NME | first= Ailbhe | last= Malone | date= 8 October 2011 |accessdate=3 January 2012}}</ref> It is among the [[List of best-selling singles|best-selling singles of all time]], selling over 5 million copies.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/19093915 |title=One Direction hit 12 million sales in less than a year|date= 2 August 2012 |publisher=BBC News  | accessdate =2 August 2012}}</ref>\n| pos = right\n}}\nOne Direction's debut studio album, ''Up All Night'' (2011), is predominantly a pop music record, containing elements of [[teen pop]], [[dance-pop]], [[pop rock]], with [[Synthpop|electropop]] and rock influences.<ref name=\"Rosen\">{{cite web |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/up-all-night-20120328 | title = One Direction \u2013 Up All Night | work= Rolling Stone  | author-link = Jody Rosen | first = Jody | last = Rosen |date= 28 March 2012 |accessdate= 16 April 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"allmusic3\">{{cite web | first = Jon | last = O'Brien|url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/one-direction-mn0002766592|title=One Direction| publisher = AllMusic |accessdate=30 June 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"Chisling\">{{cite news| first = Matthew | last = Chisling |url= http://www.allmusic.com/album/up-all-night-r2324993/review |title= Up All Night&nbsp;\u2013 One Direction|publisher=AllMusic |date=21 November 2011 |accessdate=5 January 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"Lipshutz\">{{cite news| first =Jason | last = Lipshutz |url = http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/502856/one-direction-up-all-night-track-by-track-review |title= One Direction, 'Up All Night': Track-By-Track Review |location=New York |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=7 March 2012 |accessdate=16 April 2012}}</ref> [[Digital Spy]]'s Robert Copsey described the album as a \"collection of PG pop rock with killer choruses\",<ref>{{cite web| first =Robert | last = Copsey|url= http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/albumreviews/a352333/one-direction-up-all-night-album-review.html |title=One Direction: 'Up All Night' | type = album review |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=Hearst | place = UK|date=22 November 2011 |accessdate=28 November 2011}}</ref> while ''[[The New York Times]]'' considered it \"full of easy rock-inflected pop, blithe and sometimes clever.\"<ref name=autogenerated11>{{cite news | first = Jon | last = Caramanica| url= https://www.nytimes.com/2012/05/28/arts/music/one-direction-the-boy-band-plays-the-beacon-theater.html | work= The New York Times | title= One Direction, the Boy Band, Plays the Beacon Theater | date=27 May 2012|accessdate=16 June 2012}}</ref> Jason Lipshutz of ''Billboard'' acknowledged that the album demonstrates an originality in sound that was \"necessary for the revitalization of the boy band movement\".<ref name = \"Lipshutz\" /> The songs \"One Thing\" and \"What Makes You Beautiful\" were particularly noted for the genres of power pop and pop rock, for their \"powerhouse\" [[guitar riff]]s and \"forceful\" choruses.<ref name=\"DS1\" /><ref name=\"cowbell\">{{cite web | first = Zachary | last = Houle | url = http://www.popmatters.com/pm/review/155316-one-direction-up-all-night/ | title= One Direction: Up All Night| work= [[PopMatters]]  | date= 16 March 2012 | accessdate = 31 March 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"Rosen\" /><ref>{{cite web| first =Lewis | last = Corner |url = http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/singlesreviews/a363531/one-direction-one-thing-single-review.html | title= One Direction: 'One Thing' \u2013 Single review |work=[[Digital Spy]] | publisher= Hearst | place = UK|date= 2 February 2012 |accessdate=25 July 2012}}</ref>\n\nTheir second studio album, ''Take Me Home'' (2012), is characterised by rock-inherited pop, prominent electric guitar riffs, bright synthesisers, a [[Homogeneity and heterogeneity|homogeneous]] sound and message, and the pitch-correcting software [[Auto-Tune]].<ref name= NYT>{{cite news| first = Jon | last = Caramanica | url= https://www.nytimes.com/2012/11/15/arts/music/one-direction-rides-boy-band-wave-with-take-me-home.html |work = The New York Times | title=Riding the Boy Band Wave While It Lasts | date=14 November 2012|accessdate= 30 November 2012}}</ref><ref name=Guardian>{{cite news|url= https://www.theguardian.com/music/2012/nov/08/one-direction-take-me-review | title = One Direction: Take Me Home | type = review | work = The Guardian | author-link = Alexis Petridis | first = Alexis | last = Petridis | date=8 November 2012|accessdate=9 November 2012 | location=London}}</ref><ref name = NZH>{{cite news|url = http://www.nzherald.co.nz/entertainment/news/article.cfm?c_id=1501119&objectid=10847430 | type = album review | title = One Direction \u2013 Take Me Home| work = [[The New Zealand Herald]]|publisher= [[APN News & Media]]|date= 15 November 2012|accessdate = 16 November 2012 | first = Lyndia | last = Jenkin}}</ref><ref name=autogenerated1>{{cite news| first = Douglas | last = Wol|url= http://entertainment.time.com/2012/11/13/one-directions-songwriters-theyre-what-make-the-boy-band-beautiful/ |title=One Direction's songwriters: They're what make the boy band beautiful|work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]] |date= 28 June 2012 |accessdate= 25 August 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| first = Matt | last = Collar |url = http://www.allmusic.com/album/take-me-home-mw0002418914 | title = Take Me Home (CD \u2013 Sony Music Distribution #88725475972) |publisher=AllMusic|date=11 November 2012 |accessdate= 16 November 2012}}</ref> [[Alexis Petridis]] of ''[[The Guardian]]'' interpreted its signature sound as a \"peppy, [[synth]]-bolstered take on early-80s [[New wave music|new-wave]] pop, heavy on clipped rhythms and chugging guitars,\" which, he said, is at least an improvement on the substitute [[contemporary R&B]] \"that was once the grim lot of the boyband.\"<ref name = Guardian /> Jon Caramanica, writing in ''The New York Times'', considered the album \"far more mechanical\" than their debut album, although noted that it is sonically and lyrically similar.<ref name=NYT /> The album's lyricism speaks of falling in love, [[unrequited love]], the insistence that flaws are what make a person unique, commitment, jealousy and longing for past significant others.<ref name=NYT/><ref name=Guardian/><ref name= NZH /><ref name = \"autogenerated12\">{{cite news | url = http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/11/12/one-direction-lyrics-take-me-home_n_2118855.html |title=One Direction lyrics: 'Take Me Home' pushes boundaries, targets older audience| date= 15 November 2012| accessdate= 16 March 2013 | work = [[The Huffington Post]] | first=Madeline | last=Boardman}}</ref>\n\nErica Futterman for ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' favoured their live [[Musical acoustics|acoustic]] performances as both showing, \"Horan's ability to play guitar, as well as One Direction's admirable live vocals. There was no need to worry about a backing track or a bum note, a pleasant realization at a pop show.\"<ref>{{cite news| first =Erica | last = Futterman |url= https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/one-direction-make-a-play-for-longevity-on-first-american-headlining-tour-20120527 |title= One Direction Make a Play For Longevity on First American Headlining Tour |work = Rolling Stone |date=27 May 2012 |accessdate=11 May 2012}}</ref> ''[[Herald Sun]]''{{'}}s Cameron Adams opined that One Direction have \"strong pop voices\".<ref>{{cite news| first =Cameron | last = Adams |url = http://www.heraldsun.com.au/entertainment/one-direction-infection-sweeps-melbourne/story-e6frf96f-1226329537630 |title = One Direction infection sweeps Melbourne |work=Herald Sun |location= Australia  |date=18 April 2012 |accessdate=11 May 2012}}</ref> Melody Lau of the ''[[National Post]]'' wrote, \"It's easy to get lost in inherent appeal of their perfectly coiffed dos and almost-too-put-together preppy style but somewhere in the midst of all the love-struck squeals of teenage girls are guys who can actually sing and, to a certain extent, entertain.\"<ref>{{cite news |first= Melody |last= Lau |url= http://arts.nationalpost.com/2012/06/01/concert-review-one-direction-are-mostly-killer-with-some-filler/ |title= Concert Review: One Direction are mostly killer with some filler |work= National Post |location= Canada |publisher= [[Postmedia Network]] |date= 1 June 2012 |accessdate= 11 June 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl= https://archive.is/20120709183651/http://arts.nationalpost.com/2012/06/01/concert-review-one-direction-are-mostly-killer-with-some-filler/ |archivedate= 9 July 2012 }}</ref> Jane Stevenson of the portal site [[Canoe.ca|Canoe]] concurred: \"What I didn't really prepare myself for was that they all can actually sing in concert.\"<ref>{{cite news | first = Jane | last = Stevenson | url = http://jam.canoe.ca/Music/Artists/O/One_Direction/ConcertReviews/2012/05/30/19815201-qmi.html | title = Concert Review: Live Review: One Direction in TO | work = [[Canoe.ca|Jam! Canoe]] | publisher = [[Qu\u00e9becor M\u00e9dia]] | date = 30 May 2012 | accessdate = 11 June 2012 | url-status=dead | archiveurl = https://archive.is/20120710002923/http://jam.canoe.ca/Music/Artists/O/One_Direction/ConcertReviews/2012/05/30/19815201-qmi.html | archivedate = 10 July 2012 }}</ref> Chris Richards, writing in ''[[The Washington Post]]'', dissented from the approval: \"As the five traded couplets, it was tough to imagine a future [[Justin Timberlake]], [[Ricky Martin]] or [[Bobby Brown]] emerging from the pack. No one voice stood out.\"<ref>{{cite news| first =Chris | last = Richards| url = https://www.washingtonpost.com/lifestyle/style/one-direction-show-polite-boy-band-excites-squealing-fans/2012/05/25/gJQAmYxVpU_story.html |work=The Washington Post | title = One Direction whips Patriot Center into a G-rated frenzy | date = 25 May 2012|accessdate=9 July 2012}}</ref> Mike Wass of [[Idolator (website)|Idolator]] felt One Direction's \"surprisingly accomplished effort\" of [[Kings of Leon]]'s \"[[Use Somebody]]\" proved that One Direction are \"more than capable\" of evolving their sound.<ref>{{cite news| first =Mike | last = Wass |url= http://idolator.com/6351471/one-direction-live-in-sydney-concert-review |title=One Direction Live in Sydney: Concert Review |work= [[Idolator (website)|Idolator]] |date=13 April 2012 |accessdate=9 July 2012}}</ref>\n\nTheir third album ''Midnight Memories'' (2013) is a pop rock record, a slight departure from the band's original teen pop sound. Liam Payne called Midnight Memories a \"slightly rockier and edgier\" album than their previous material. The album is heavily influenced by 80's rock<ref name=Rebellion>{{cite web|url=http://whstherebellion.com/?p=51482 |title=One Direction Embraces New Sound with 'Midnight Memories' |publisher=Whstherebellion.com |date=2 December 2013 |accessdate=2 August 2014}}</ref> and folk music and briefly integrates elements of dubstep, notably in \"Little White Lies\". The album's lyrical themes primarily revolve around love, heartbreak and sexual intercourse. Many critics praised its lyrical depth and musical composition, as well as the group's level of involvement in the production process.<ref name=\"Hollywood Reporter\">{{cite news| url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/one-directions-midnight-memories-what-660135 | work=The Hollywood Reporter | first=Kyle | last=Jaeger | title=One Direction's 'Midnight Memories': What the Critics Are Saying | date=26 November 2013}}</ref>\n\nTheir fourth album ''Four'' (2014) was released on 17 November 2014. Payne once again claimed that the album would be \"edgier\" and that the group had written most of the songs for it; Horan came up with the name of the album, commemorating the fact that it is One Direction's fourth record to date and that it has been four years since the band's formation. Signifying a further maturation of their pop sound, the album's first single, \"[[Steal My Girl]]\", was dubbed by ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' as \"no [[What Makes You Beautiful]], but its [[Coldplay]]-like piano pop could be a good direction\",<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/review/album-review/6319861/one-direction-four-album-review |title=Album Review: One Direction's 'Four' | work=Billboard | first=Chuck | last=Arnold | date=17 November 2014}}</ref> and that the band was \"not entirely ready to let go of its bubble-gum days\". ''Rolling Stone'' described the record as \"saturated with retro vibes\"; its songs \"split the difference between big, splashy Eighties [[pop rock]] and more elegant Seventies flavours \u2013 a very pesky whipper-snapper move that's not so far from what [[Haim (band)|Haim]]'s hit \"[[Days Are Gone]]\" did last year.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/one-direction-four-20141118 |title=One Direction extend their winning streak, with echoes of the 1970s and 1980s | work=Rolling Stone | first=Jon | last=Dolan | date=18 November 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Other ventures==\n\n===Endorsements===\nIn 2011, One Direction became the face of [[Pokemon Black and White]], starring in a series of television adverts.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2011-04-06-one-direction-become-pokemon-face |title=One Direction become Pokemon face |last=Purchese |first=Robert |work=Eurogamer |accessdate=6 April 2011}}</ref> They were the first installments in the fifth [[Pok\u00e9mon#Generations|generation]] of the ''[[Pok\u00e9mon (video game series)|Pok\u00e9mon]]'' series of role-playing games.<ref name=\"bw\">{{cite web |url=http://www.pokemon.co.jp/bw/index.html |script-title=ja:\u300e\u30dd\u30b1\u30c3\u30c8\u30e2\u30f3\u30b9\u30bf\u30fc\u30d6\u30e9\u30c3\u30af\u30fb\u30db\u30ef\u30a4\u30c8\u300f |language=Japanese |publisher=[[Nintendo]] |accessdate=7 April 2010 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5sv9suCz9?url=http://www.pokemon-sp.jp/series/bw/ |archivedate=22 September 2010 |url-status=dead}}</ref> They also launched [[Nokia C3 (disambiguation)|Nokia C3]] and [[Nokia C2-02]] phones. To promote the launch [[Nokia]] made a series of photos of the band members using the phones to take photos of themselves.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theinquirer.net/inquirer/news/2110372/nokia-enlists-direction-launch-phones |title=Nokia enlists One Direction to launch phones |last=Martin |first=Chris |work=The Inquirer |accessdate=20 September 2011}}</ref>\n\nIn 2012, they teamed up with [[Colgate (toothpaste)|Colgate]] to launch their own One Direction Colgate MaxFresh Power Toothbrush, the One Direction Colgate Maxfresh Manual Toothbrush, and the One Direction Colgate MaxFresh Toothpaste.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2012/10/10/one-direction-colgate-toothbrush-toothpaste_n_1954108.html?guccounter=1 |title=One Direction Colgate Range: Boyband Launch Their Own Toothbrushes And Toothpaste |last=Bagwell |first=Matt |work=Huffpost |date=10 November 2012 |accessdate=10 November 2012}}</ref> The band was signed by [[Pepsi]] in a multimillion-dollar advertising deal in 2012.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://metro.co.uk/2012/09/05/one-direction-land-multi-million-dollar-pepsi-advertising-deal-566025/ |title=One Direction land multi-million dollar Pepsi advertising deal |author=metrowebukmetro |work=Metro UK |accessdate=5 September 2012}}</ref> Social media marketing included a tie up with [[Shazam (application)|Shazam]], whereby consumers that used the digital music app in conjunction with the ad both on TV and online were be able to view exclusive content and link back to [[iTunes]] to buy One Direction's single, \u201c[[Live While We're Young]]\u201d.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.campaignlive.co.uk/article/pepsi-pits-one-direction-against-nfl-star-live-push/1154374 |title=Pepsi pits One Direction against NFL star in Live For Now push |last=Smith |first=Loulla |work=Campaign |accessdate=11 October 2012}}</ref> Mini figures based on members of the group were launched for the band's US fans after the agreement was signed by American firm [[Hasbro]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.expressandstar.com/entertainment/music/2012/04/28/1d-toy-firm-hasbro-to-create-one-direction-toys/ |title=Toy firm Hasbro to create One Direction toys |publisher=Express And Star |accessdate=28 April 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/hasbro-results-marvel-one-direction-443908 |title=Hasbro First-Quarter Revenue Helped by One Direction, Marvel Products |last=Szalai |first=Georg |work=Hollywood Reporter |accessdate=22 April 2013}}</ref> In October 2012, the band also signed up to endorse Filipino clothing brand, [[Penshoppe]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://entertainment.inquirer.net/61776/one-direction-to-endorse-filipino-clothing-brand |title=One Direction to endorse Filipino clothing brand |last=Conception |first=Pocholo |work=Philippines Daily Inquirer |accessdate=7 October 2012}}</ref>\n\n[[File:1D World, Albion Street, Leeds (30th March 2013) 001.JPG|thumb|right|A One Direction merchandising shop in [[Leeds]] in March 2013]]\nIn 2013, One Direction announced pop-up shops around the world, including Brisbane, Toronto, Chicago, New York, Tokyo and Stockholm, selling exclusive merchandise.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/showbiz/news/a464976/one-direction-to-launch-1d-world-store-in-leeds-for-three-weeks/ |title=One Direction to launch 1D World store in Leeds for three weeks |last=Eames |first=Tom |work=Digital Spy |accessdate=12 March 2013}}</ref> [[Nabisco]] became the title sponsor of One Direction's North American tour.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.eventmarketer.com/article/nabisco-one-direction-north-american-tour/ |title=NABISCO SPONSORSHIP SATISFIES ONE DIRECTION'S FAN CONNECTION |last=Boucher |first=Rachel |work=Event Marketer |accessdate=20 June 2013}}</ref> The band became the new faces of [[Toyota]] [[Toyota Vios|VIOS]], releasing behind-the-scenes look at their commercial for the vehicle.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://popcrush.com/one-direction-toyota-vios-commercial-behind-the-scenes/ |title=one direction toyota vios commercial behind the scenes |last=Sager |first=Jessica |work=Pop Crush |accessdate=20 October 2013}}</ref> One Direction's debut fragrance, [[Our Moment]], launched at [[Harrods]] in London and on their website in 2013.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache:http://www.vogue.co.uk/article/one-direction-our-moment-fragrance-waiting-list-harrods |title=Waiting For One Direction |last=Niven |first=Lisa |work=Vogue |accessdate=21 August 2013 }}{{Dead link|date=September 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> The full length advert for the fragrance was released on 24 August 2013, featuring the song \"[[My Favorite Things (song)|My Favourite Things]]\u201d.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/showbiz/news/a509881/one-directions-our-moment-fragrance-ad-diana-vickers-sings-video.html|title=One Direction's Our Moment fragrance ad, Diana Vickers sings - video|accessdate=26 August 2013|work=Digital Spy|first=Sam|last=Rigby}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pressparty.com/pg/newsdesk/OneDirection/view/77929/|title=One Direction's Liam Payne says perfume was inspired by fan petition|work=Press Party|accessdate=7 June 2013}}</ref> The perfume was the best-selling famous fragrance of Christmas 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sugarscape.com/main-topics/fashion-beauty/996227/one-direction%E2%80%99s-our-moment-beating-taylor-swift-lady-gaga-britney-|title=One Direction's Our Moment beating Taylor Swift, Lady Gaga, Britney Spears and basically everyone in the fragrance war|work=Sugarscape|accessdate=6 December 2013|first=Lucy|last=Wood}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.irishmirror.ie/showbiz/celebrity-news/one-direction-moment-fragrance-beats-2894369|title=One Direction perfume beats Lady Gaga, Britney Spears and Taylor Swift fragrances|work=Irish Mirror|accessdate=5 December 2013|first=Rebecca|last=Pocklington}}</ref> In 2014, the band released their second scent That Moment.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2014/02/27/one-direction-release-new-fragrance-that-moment-harry-styles_n_4864093.html |title=One Direction To Release New Fragrance 'That Moment', Confirms Harry Styles |last=Nelson |first=Sarah |work=huffpost |accessdate=27 February 2014}}</ref> The fragrance was released with a matching shower gel and body lotion.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.seventeen.com/beauty/news/a22750/one-direction-that-moment-perfume/ |title=Check Out 1D's Pics for Their New Perfume! |last=Mcgrath |first=Kara |work=Seventeen |accessdate=21 March 2014}}</ref> They released a commercial for their third fragrance, \"You & I\", named after their [[You & I (One Direction song)|2014 song of the same name]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6207040/one-direction-commercial-perfume-you-i |title=One Direction Debut Commercial Behind New Perfume 'You & I' |last=Strecker |first=Erin |work=Billboard |accessdate=5 August 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, One Direction appeared in an advert for the [[Toyota Vios]]. the commercial aired in Thailand.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nme.com/news/music/one-direction-118-1214327#LiGp0Cx3I53E7Kfu.99 |title=One Direction star in Toyota ad \u2013 watch |publisher=NME |accessdate=17 March 2015}}</ref> [[Coca-Cola]] Mexico launched the session and full interview with One Direction, with a series of commercials in which Tomlinson, Payne, Styles and Horan showed us what it means to be a True Friend.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.es.j-14.com/posts/coca-cola-por-fin-lanzan-su-session-en-el-estudio-con-one-direction-59033?age_gate%5Bbirth_year%5D=691&age_gate%5Bcoppa_cookie%5D= |title=Directioners: Coca-Cola Finally Launch Their Session In The Studio With One Direction |last=Rodriguez |first=Karla |work=J-14 |accessdate=22 May 2015}}</ref> One Direction revealed their fourth fragrance \u2018Between Us\u2019 at The Sanderson in London, England on 24 June.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://hollywoodlife.com/2015/06/24/one-direction-between-us-fourth-fragrance-new-scent/ |title=One Direction Launches Fourth Fragrance 'Between Us |last=Zayas |first=Dory |work=Hollywood life |accessdate=24 June 2015}}</ref> The band appeared in a [[Honda Civic]] ad which shows the quartet testing out the car's stereo, style and trunk space with a humorous tone and the tagline \"It's all One Direction approved.\" The ad is set to the 1D single \u201c[[Drag Me Down]]\u201d. The group's 2015 U.S. tour was also supported by [[Honda]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6760883/one-direction-honda-civic-test-drive-commercial-video |title=Watch One Direction Put New Honda Civic to the Test in TV Commercial |last=Stutz |first=Colin |work=Billboard |accessdate=12 November 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Philanthropy===\nIn 2011, the band performed on the BBC's [[Children in Need 2011]] charity telethon. In 2012, they extended their involvement with Children in Need as they opened the telecast with a performance of their single \"[[Live While We're Young]]\". A prominent annual event in British television, the group said it was \"incredible\" to be involved in [[Children in Need]] as it was something that they had \"always watched as children\".<ref name=\"BBC\">{{cite news| url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-20367022 | publisher=BBC News | title=One Direction: 'Incredible to open Children In Need' | date=16 November 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2013, One Direction released \"[[One Way or Another (Teenage Kicks)]]\" (a medley of \"[[One Way or Another]]\" and \"[[Teenage Kicks]]\") as the 2013 single for the UK's other major charity telethon [[Comic Relief]].<ref name=\"Robertson\"/> For [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]]'s Santa charity Christmas campaign, they filmed a set of pleas to their fans and the general public, asking them to donate \u00a32.<ref name=\"Sugarscape\">{{cite web|url=http://www.sugarscape.com/main-topics/film-and-tv/999397/one-direction-join-itv%E2%80%99s-text-santa-charity-campaign |title=One Direction join ITV\u0411\u2500\u2265s Text Santa charity campaign |publisher=Sugarscape |accessdate=2 August 2014}}</ref> The band have made numerous other appearances for charitable causes, including the 2011 [[Pride of Britain Awards]] where they presented 13-year-old quadruple amputee Danielle Bailey the Child of Courage award at her school assembly, and the 2014 [[Royal Variety Performance]] where they played in front of [[Prince William, Duke of Cambridge|Prince William]] and [[Catherine, Duchess of Cambridge|Catherine]] at the London Palladium.<ref>[https://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/one-direction-surprise-pride-of-britain-156163 \"One Direction surprise Pride of Britain winner Danielle Bailey at school assembly\"]. Mirror. Retrieved 26 August 2015</ref><ref>[https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/theroyalfamily/11230239/Duke-and-Duchess-of-Cambridge-meet-One-Direction-at-Royal-Variety-Performance.html \"Duke and Duchess of Cambridge meet One Direction at Royal Variety Performance\"]. The Telegraph. Retrieved 26 August 2015</ref>\n\nIn September 2012, Niall Horan organised an event to raise money for Irish Autism Action and another charity, called Temporary Emergency Accommodation Mullingar, based in his hometown. Due to overwhelming demand to participate in the fundraising, the ticket website for the event broke down. Horan's brother Greg commented on the website crash, saying that \"there were 500 tickets and they were all snapped up pretty quick\".<ref name=autogenerated2>{{cite web|url=http://www.sugarscape.com/main-topics/homepage/764642/niall-horans-charity-event-crashes-website |title=Niall Horan breaks charity website |publisher=Sugarscape |accessdate=2 August 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013, band members Liam Payne and Harry Styles partnered with Trekstock, a leading cancer charity to help raise money for cancer research.<ref name=\"Trekstock\">{{cite web|url=http://trekstock.com/our-story/patrons-ambassadors/ |title=Patrons & Ambassadors |publisher=Trekstock |accessdate=29 November 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141030012714/http://trekstock.com/our-story/patrons-ambassadors/ |archivedate=30 October 2014 }}</ref> As ambassadors of the charity, the duo collaborated to offer the chance for one fan and a friend to win an evening out with them in return for a donation to the charity as part of an exclusive \"#HangwithLiam&Harry\" global campaign. They had originally set a goal of raising $500,000 and ended up raising $784,984. Trekstock later added that this amount would allow them to \"complete funding of their [[Hodgkin's lymphoma]] trial, in the hope of offering a much brighter future to thousands of children and young people affected by this form of disease.\" One Direction were named the most charitable in 2013 behind [[Taylor Swift]] by social change organisation [[DoSomething.org]].<ref name=\"Do Something\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5847924/taylor-swift-one-direction-top-list-of-most-charitable-stars |title=Taylor Swift, One Direction Top List of Most Charitable Stars |work=Billboard |accessdate=19 January 2014}}</ref> On 30 May 2013, the band announced a partnership with [[Office Depot]] on a limited-edition capsule collection of back to school supplies. They also confirmed that a portion of the proceeds from the alliance would go toward an anti-bullying educational program intended to promote kinder behaviour in schools.<ref>[http://uk.eonline.com/news/426786/one-direction-boys-launch-anti-bullying-campaign-with-office-depot \"One Direction Boys Launch Anti-Bullying Campaign with Office Depot\"]. E!. Retrieved 13 September 2015</ref>\n\nIn 2014, One Direction donated \u00a3600,000 for the Stand up to Cancer campaign by giving portions of their ticket sales revenues from their [[Where We Are Tour (One Direction)|Where We Are Tour]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sugarscape.com/main-topics/lads/1045055/one-direction-release-selfie-they-took-stage-last-night-wembley-its-reveale|title=Cosmopolitan, the women's magazine for fashion, beauty, sex tips and celebrity news|website=Cosmopolitan}}</ref> On 15 November 2014, One Direction joined the charity group [[Band Aid 30]] along with other British and Irish pop acts, recording the latest version of the track \"[[Do They Know It's Christmas?]]\" at [[Sarm West Studios]] in [[Notting Hill]], London, to raise money for the [[West African Ebola virus epidemic|2014 Ebola crisis]] in Western Africa.<ref>{{cite news|title=Band Aid 30: One Direction among celebrity line-up|newspaper=The Daily Telegraph|date=11 November 2014 |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/music/music-news/11220735/Band-Aid-30-line-up-revealed.html |accessdate=11 January 2015|location=London|first=Anita|last=Singh}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, One Direction launched 'Action 1D' campaign to raise awareness of global issues. The initiative aims to end extreme poverty, tackle inequality and slow down climate change with the help of their millions of fans. It is part of the wider [[action/2015]] campaign, a global citizen's movement that is all about the idea that 2015 can be the year when the world can set the agenda to end major global issues. One Direction will be asking their fans to describe the kind of world they want to live in by sharing powerful pieces of creative content, including videos and photos, using the hashtag #Action1D.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mtv.co.uk/one-direction/news/one-direction-launch-action-1d-campaign-to-raise-awareness-of-global-issues |title=one direction launch action 1d campaign to raise awareness of global issues |publisher=MTV |accessdate=8 July 2015}}</ref> The quartet also starred in a campaign video, appealing to fans to join the movement.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2015/07/08/one-direction-action-1d-campaign-video_n_7752930.html |title=One Direction Launch Action/1D Campaign To End Poverty, Inequality And Global Warming |last=Percival |first=Ashley |work=Huffington Post UK |accessdate=7 August 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Image==\n[[File:One Direction 2012 Stockholm.jpg|thumb|right|One Direction greet Swedish fans in [[Stockholm]], May 2012]]\nNeil McCormick of ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]'', in an article on One Direction's success in North America, notes that Americans had left a gap in the market and it took the prominence of [[Justin Bieber]] to demonstrate that there still was a market for \"clean cut, wholesome, whiter-than-white, middle class parent friendly pop: cute boys advocating puppy love. And what could be better than one cute boy, if not five?\"<ref>{{cite news | first = Neil | last = McCormick |url= https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/music/rockandpopmusic/9111003/The-Wanted-and-One-Direction-why-British-boybands-are-conquering-America.html |title=The Wanted & One Direction: why British boybands are conquering America |work= The Daily Telegraph |location= London |date= 28 February 2012|accessdate= 17 March 2012}}</ref> One Direction have been described as sparking a resurgence in the interest in boy bands, and as forming part of a new \"[[British Invasion]]\" in the United States.<ref name=autogenerated8>{{cite news| first =Kerry | last = O'Shea |url = http://www.irishcentral.com/ent/One-Direction-BritishIrish-boy-band--about-to-explode-in-America-says-Simon-Cowell--142303325.html |title=One Direction, British/Irish boy band about to explode in America says Simon Cowell |work =IrishCentral | date=12 March 2012 |accessdate=31 March 2012}}</ref><ref name=autogenerated5>{{cite news| first = Lyndsey | last = Parker |url= http://ca.music.yahoo.com/blogs/reality-rocks/british-coming-one-direction-set-conquer-america-202911123.html |title=The British Are Coming! One Direction Set To Conquer America |work=[[Yahoo! News|News]] | publisher =Yahoo! |date=12 March 2012 |accessdate=31 March 2012}}</ref><ref name=autogenerated4>{{cite news| first = Jocelyn | last = Vena|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1681029/the-wanted-one-direction-boy-bands.jhtml |title= The Wanted Vs. One Direction: A Boy Band Cheat Sheet |publisher=[[MTV News]] |date=14 March 2012 | accessdate =31 March 2012}}</ref><ref name=autogenerated3>{{cite news| first =Brian | last = Mansfield |url = https://www.usatoday.com/life/music/ontheverge/story/2012-03-07/one-direction/53425236/1 |title=Meet UK boy band One Direction |work=USA Today|publisher=[[Gannett Company|Gannett Co]] |date=9 March 2012 |accessdate=31 March 2012}}</ref><ref name= Greene>{{cite web | first = Andy | last = Greene | url = http://rollingstoneindia.com/features/the-new-british-invasion-boy-bands/ | title = The New British Invasion: Boy Bands |work= Rolling Stone |date= 8 May 2012 | accessdate = 11 June 2012}}</ref> Bill Werde, a representative of [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']] magazine, commented, \"There's a lot of possibility here, there's a lot of upside, that level of talent with those kinds of looks, it's really a perfect storm for a massive, massive successful phenomenon.\"<ref name=\"guardian1\">{{cite news| first = Caspar Llewellyn | last = Smith |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2012/mar/15/one-direction-fab-five-america |title = One Direction: the fab five take America |work=The Guardian| location=London |date=15 March 2012| accessdate= 31 March 2012}}</ref> In [[NPR]], Maria Sherman noticed that before One Direction's breakthrough, boy bands were \"off the radar\" since [[NSYNC]] went on an indefinite hiatus in 2002.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.npr.org/2020/03/20/818464377/nsync-no-strings-attached-20th-anniversary-timberlake-backstreet|title=The Future According To NSYNC: 20 Years Of 'No Strings Attached'|work=NPR}}</ref>\n\nSonny Takhar, the chief executive officer of Syco Records, attributes the breakthrough to the power of [[social media]]. \"Sometimes you feel the song's the star, but it's not like that here&nbsp;\u2013 it's the act,\" he said. \"It's a real moment. Social media has become the new radio, it's never broken an act globally like this before.\"<ref name=\"guardian1\"/> Will Bloomfield, the group's manager, added, \"These guys live online, and so do their fans.\"<ref name= Greene /> Their management employs a social media team and the members all tweet themselves, \"which helps create the illusion that they couldn't be any closer to their fans,\" according to Caspar Llewellyn Smith, writing for ''The Guardian''.<ref name = \"guardian1\" /> One Direction's Twitter account had amassed 10 million followers by February 2013, with the account gaining followers at an average of 21,000 per day.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://twittercounter.com/compare/one%20direction/week/followers | title = One Direction Twitter Stats |work= Counter| publisher= Twitter | accessdate= 15 March 2013}}</ref> In an approach pioneered by [[The Beatles]], each member is known for his feature; Horan is \"the cute one\", Malik is \"the quiet and mysterious one\", Payne is \"the sensible one\", Styles is \"the charming one\" and Tomlinson is \"the funny one\".<ref name=Abrams>{{cite news| first =Stephanie | last = Abrahams |url = http://entertainment.time.com/2012/04/06/behind-the-hype-can-one-direction-save-the-boy-band/ | title = Can One Direction Save the Boy Band? | work = Time | date = 6 April 2012 | accessdate= 27 April 2012}}</ref> Each member's individual identity is reinforced by their intentionally different personal styles. Caroline Watson, the band's original stylist, spoke about styling the band, \"At the beginning I didn't want them all in black or all in leather\u2014that whole stereotypical boy band thing.\" Instead, her original idea was for them to be the \"male equivalent to the [[Spice Girls]]\", with each member being a part of the group but still having his own individual style.<ref name=styling>{{cite news| first =Brodie | last = Lancaster |url = http://themuse.jezebel.com/behind-the-boy-band-q-a-with-caroline-watson-one-dire-1687594935 | title = Behind the Boy Band: Q&A with Caroline Watson, One Direction's Stylist | work = Jezebel | date = 2 March 2015 | accessdate= 9 March 2017}}</ref> \n\nHoran commented on One Direction as a boy band, \"People think that a boy band is air-grabs and [being] dressed in all one colour. We're boys in a band. We're trying to do something different from what people would think is the typical kind of boy band. We're trying to do different kinds of music and we're just trying to be ourselves, not squeaky clean.\"<ref name=\"nationalpost1\">{{cite news | first = Leah | last = Collins | url = http://arts.nationalpost.com/2012/03/12/one-direction-is-more-than-just-another-boy-band/ | archive-url = https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20120313001910/http://arts.nationalpost.com/2012/03/12/one-direction-is-more-than-just-another-boy-band/ | url-status=dead | archivedate = 13 March 2012 | title = One Direction: X Factor boy band on what sets them apart | work = National Post | location = Canada | publisher = [[Postmedia Network]] | date = 12 March 2012 | accessdate = 17 March 2012 }}</ref> Leah Collins, writing for the ''[[National Post]]'', remarked they had succeeded on the latter front. \"For the most part, that just means the group presents themselves as typical, goofy and uncensored teenage boys&nbsp;\u2013 posting jokey YouTube videos, for instance, or boozing at awards shows.\"<ref name=\"nationalpost1\" /> Writing for ''[[The Observer]]'', [[Kitty Empire]] opined, \"One Direction fulfill a great many boy band prerequisites (looks, soppy lyrics, tune-grasp, fame-lust) but their lack of routines points to the subtle digressions afoot here\".<ref>{{cite news| author-link = Kitty Empire | first = Kitty | last = Empire |url= https://www.theguardian.com/music/2012/jan/08/one-direction-x-factor-live |title= One Direction | type = review |date=7 January 2012 |work= The Observer |accessdate= 8 April 2012 | archiveurl = http://www.freezepage.com/1333939139CSPGVONNPC?url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/music/2012/jan/08/one-direction-x-factor-live |archivedate= 9 April 2012 |location= London}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n{{Main|One Direction discography|List of songs recorded by One Direction}}\n\n* ''[[Up All Night (One Direction album)|Up All Night]]'' (2011)\n* ''[[Take Me Home (One Direction album)|Take Me Home]]'' (2012)\n* ''[[Midnight Memories]]'' (2013)\n* ''[[Four (One Direction album)|Four]]'' (2014)\n* ''[[Made in the A.M.]]'' (2015)\n\n==Filmography==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n|2010\n|''[[The X Factor (British TV series)|The X Factor]]\n|Themselves (contestants)\n|[[The X Factor (British series 7)|Series 7]]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|2012\n|''[[iCarly]]''\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Themselves\n|Episode: iGo One Direction\n|-\n|''[[Up All Night: The Live Tour]]''\n|Video album\n|-\n| 2012\u201314\n|''[[Saturday Night Live]]''\n|Themselves (musical guests)\n|Episodes: Sofia Vergara/One Direction; Paul Rudd/One Direction; Amy Adams/One Direction\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[One Direction: This Is Us]]''\n| rowspan=\"2\"|Themselves\n| [[Documentary film|Documentary]] [[concert film]]\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[One Direction: Where We Are \u2013 The Concert Film]]''\n| Concert film\n|}\n\n==Tours==\n{{Col-begin}}\n{{Col-2}}\n'''Headlining'''\n*[[Up All Night Tour]] (2011\u201312)\n*[[Take Me Home Tour (One Direction)|Take Me Home Tour]] (2013)\n*[[Where We Are Tour (One Direction)|Where We Are Tour]] (2014)\n*[[On the Road Again Tour]] (2015)\n\n{{Col-2}}\n'''Opening act'''\n*[[The X Factor (British TV series)|X Factor Tour 2011]] (2011)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/newsround/33639898|title=One Direction: A look back at five years of 1D madness - CBBC Newsround|agency=BBC}}</ref>\n*[[Better with U Tour]] {{small|([[Big Time Rush (band)|Big Time Rush]])}} (2012)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1678972/big-time-rush-one-direction-tour/ |title=One Direction, Big Time Rush Talk Joint Tour |publisher=MTV |date=10 February 2012 |accessdate=9 July 2014}}</ref>\n{{Col-end}}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{{Main|List of awards and nominations received by One Direction}}\nOne Direction has received seven [[Brit Awards]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7701365/one-direction-zayn-malik-video-of-the-year-2017-brit-awards|title=One Direction Beats Out Zayn Malik for Video of the Year at 2017 Brit Awards|last=Weatherby|first=Taylor|date=22 February 2017|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=24 August 2018}}</ref> seven [[American Music Awards]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theamas.com/winners-database/?winnerKeyword=one+direction&winnerYear=&winnerCategory=|title=Winners Database|last=|first=|date=|website=[[American Music Awards]]|accessdate=24 August 2018}}</ref> six [[Billboard Music Award|''Billboard'' Music Awards]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboardmusicawards.com/winners-database/?winnerKeyword=one+direction&winnerYear=&winnerCategory=|title=Winners Database|last=|first=|date=|website=[[Billboard Music Award]]s|accessdate=24 August 2018}}</ref> five [[Billboard Touring Awards|''Billboard'' Touring Awards]], and four [[MTV Video Music Awards]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1713022/one-direction-vma-2013-song-of-the-summer/|title=One Direction: Eight Million Votes Prove The Boys Own 'Song Of The Summer'|last=Vena|first=Jocelyn|date=25 August 2013|website=[[MTV News]]|accessdate=24 August 2018}}</ref> among other awards. One Direction holds the record as the most awarded act at the [[Teen Choice Awards]] with 28 wins from 31 nominations.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Dresdale |first1=Andrea |title=It's One Direction vs. One Direction at tonight's Teen Choice Awards |url=https://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/direction-direction-tonights-teen-choice-awards/story?id=49156368 |website=[[ABC News]] |accessdate=25 August 2018 |date=13 August 2017}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n\n* [[List of Billboard Social 50 number-one artists]]\n* [[List of artists who reached number one on the UK Singles Chart]]\n* [[List of highest-grossing concert tours]]\n\n==Publications==\n*''One Direction: Forever Young'', HarperCollins (17 February 2011) {{ISBN|978-0-00-743230-1}}\n*''One Direction: The Official Annual 2012'', HarperCollins (1 September 2011) {{ISBN|978-0-00-743625-5}}\n*''Dare to Dream: Life as One Direction'', HarperCollins (15 September 2011) {{ISBN|978-0-00-744439-7}}\n*''One Direction: Where We Are: Our Band, Our Story: 100% Official'', HarperCollins (19 November 2013) {{ISBN|978-0-00-748900-8}}\n*''One Direction: Who We Are: Our Official Autobiography'', HarperCollins (25 September 2014) {{ISBN|978-0-00-757731-6}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{wikiquote}}\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{Official website}}\n* {{allmusic}}\n* {{IMDb name}}\n\n{{One Direction}}\n{{Navboxes\n|list=\n{{Niall Horan}}\n{{Zayn Malik}}\n{{Liam Payne}}\n{{Harry Styles}}\n{{Louis Tomlinson}}\n{{The X Factor (UK)}}\n{{IFPI Global Year-End}}\n{{Japan Gold Disc Award for Artist of the Year}}\n{{MTV EMA for Best UK & Ireland Act}}\n}}\n{{Good article}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:One Direction| ]]\n[[Category:ARIA Award winners]]\n[[Category:Brit Award winners]]\n[[Category:MTV EMA winners]]\n[[Category:English pop music groups]]\n[[Category:English boy bands]]\n[[Category:English pop rock music groups]]\n[[Category:English vocal groups]]\n[[Category:Bubblegum pop]]\n[[Category:Teen pop groups]]\n[[Category:Columbia Records artists]]\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 2010]]\n[[Category:Musical groups from London]]\n[[Category:Musical quartets]]\n[[Category:NME Awards winners]]\n[[Category:Syco Music artists]]\n[[Category:Sony/ATV Music Publishing artists]]\n[[Category:Sony BMG artists]]\n[[Category:Vocal quartets]]\n[[Category:The X Factor (British TV series) contestants]]\n[[Category:Vocal quintets]]\n", "text_old": "{{distinguish|One-way (disambiguation){{!}}One-way}}\n{{pp-semi-indef|small=yes}}\n{{short description|English-Irish boy band}}\n{{Use British English|date=February 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = One Direction\n| background       = group_or_band\n| image            = One Direction 2015.jpg\n| landscape        = yes\n| caption          = One Direction performing in [[Glasgow]] on their [[On the Road Again Tour]], October 2015. From left to right: [[Louis Tomlinson]], [[Niall Horan]], [[Liam Payne]] and [[Harry Styles]]\n| alias            = <!--1D-->\n| origin           = [[London]], England\n| genre            = {{flatlist|\n* [[Pop music|Pop]]\n* [[teen pop]]\n* [[pop rock]]\n}}\n| years_active     = 2010\u20132016 (on indefinite hiatus)\n| label            = {{flatlist|\n* [[Syco Music|Syco]]\n* [[Columbia Records|Columbia]]\n}}<!-- Do not add Sony Music as a label, as Columbia and Syco are divisions of it -->\n| associated_acts  = [[List of The X Factor finalists (British series 7)|''The X Factor'' finalists 2010]]\n| current_members  = * [[Harry Styles]]\n* [[Niall Horan]] \n* [[Liam Payne]]\n* [[Louis Tomlinson]]\n| website          = {{URL|onedirectionmusic.com}}\n| past_members     =  * [[Zayn Malik]]\n}}\n\n'''One Direction''', often shortened to '''1D''', are<!-- are is plural for a group, do not change --> an English-Irish<!-- This is based on discussion in the talk page --> [[Pop music|pop]] [[boy band]] formed in London, England in 2010. The group are composed of [[Niall Horan]], [[Liam Payne]], [[Harry Styles]] and [[Louis Tomlinson]]; former member [[Zayn Malik]] departed from the group in 2015. The group signed with [[Simon Cowell]]'s record label [[Syco Music|Syco Records]] after forming and finishing third in the [[The X Factor (British series 7)|seventh series]] of the British televised singing competition ''[[The X Factor (British TV series)|The X Factor]]'' in 2010. Propelled to global success by [[social media]],<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/music/2012/mar/15/one-direction-fab-five-america \u201cOne Direction: the fab five take America\u201d]. ''The Guardian''. Retrieved 27 July 2019</ref><ref>[https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/music/music-news/9157558/One-Direction-make-American-pop-history.html \u201cOne Direction make American pop history\u201d]. ''The Telegraph''. Retrieved 27 July 2019</ref><ref>[https://www.theverge.com/2016/12/13/13937688/one-direction-one-year-hiatus-anniversary-social-media-blogging \u201cHow One Direction stayed the world\u2019s biggest band even after it stopped existing\u201d]. ''The Verge''. Retrieved 27 July 2019</ref> One Direction's five albums, ''[[Up All Night (One Direction album)|Up All Night]]'' (2011), ''[[Take Me Home (One Direction album)|Take Me Home]]'' (2012), ''[[Midnight Memories]]'' (2013), ''[[Four (One Direction album)|Four]]'' (2014), and ''[[Made in the A.M.]]'' (2015), topped charts in most major markets, and generated hit singles including \"[[What Makes You Beautiful]]\", \"[[Live While We're Young]]\", \"[[Best Song Ever (song)|Best Song Ever]]\", \"[[Story of My Life (One Direction song)|Story of My Life]]\" and \"[[Drag Me Down]]\".\n\nThe group have won nearly 200 [[List of awards and nominations received by One Direction|awards]] including seven [[Brit Awards]], four [[MTV Video Music Award]]s, six [[Billboard Music Award|''Billboard'' Music Award]]s, seven [[American Music Awards]] (including [[American Music Award for Artist of the Year|Artist of the Year]] in 2014 and 2015), and 28 [[Teen Choice Awards]]. They have embarked on four world tours, two of which were all-stadium. In 2013, they earned an estimated $75 million, becoming the second highest earning celebrity under 30 according to ''[[Forbes]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/one-direction/|title=One Direction|website=Forbes}}</ref> The world\u2019s best-selling artist of 2013, the [[International Federation of the Phonographic Industry]] (IFPI) named them the [[Global Recording Artist of the Year]].<ref name=\"IFPI\"/> ''Forbes'' ranked them as the fourth [[Forbes Celebrity 100|highest-earning celebrities]] in the world in 2015,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/zackomalleygreenburg/2015/06/29/celebrity-100-the-worlds-highest-paid-superstars-of-2015/|title=Celebrity 100: The World's Highest-Paid Superstars Of 2015|author=Greenburg, Zack O'Malley|date=29 June 2015|work=Forbes|accessdate=1 September 2016}}</ref> and second in 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/zackomalleygreenburg/2016/07/11/celeb-100-the-worlds-highest-paid-celebrities-of-2016/#72cbabf81fb3/|title=Celebrity 100: The World's Highest-Paid Superstars of 2016|author=Zack O'Malley Greenburg|work=Forbes|accessdate = 6 April 2017}}</ref>\n\nAfter the release of ''Four'', One Direction became the first band in the U.S. [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] history to have their first four albums debut at number one.<ref>{{cite news|first=Keith|last=Caulfield|title=One Direction's 'Four' Makes Historic No. 1 Debut on Billboard 200 Chart|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6327789/one-direction-four-no-1-debut-billboard-200|date=26 November 2014 |accessdate=26 November 2014}}</ref> Their third album, ''Midnight Memories'', was the best-selling album worldwide in 2013 with 4 million copies sold globally.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-28599903 |title= One Direction top 2013 global album chart|publisher=BBC News  |date= 1 August 2014|accessdate=2 August 2014}}</ref> The band's [[Where We Are Tour (One Direction)|Where We Are Tour]], in support of ''Midnight Memories'', was the [[List of highest-grossing concert tours|highest-grossing concert tour]] in 2014, the highest-grossing tour by a vocal group in history, and the 15th [[List of highest-grossing concert tours|highest-grossing concert tour]] of all time, grossing $290.2 million (unadjusted for inflation).<ref name=\"billboard1D\">{{cite news|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6281518/one-direction-where-we-are-tour-three-million|title=One Direction's Where We Are Tour Attended by 3.4 Million Fans|last=Allen|first=Bob|date=10 October 2014|work=Billboard|accessdate=11 October 2014}}</ref> In 2014, ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' named One Direction Artist of the Year.<ref>{{cite news|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|title=Billboard's Artists of the Year: 1981\u20132014|url=http://www.billboard.com/photos/6415105/billboard-artist-of-the-year-gallery-1981-to-2014?i=540767|agency=Billboard|issue=23 June 2015|date=13 January 2015}}</ref><ref>[http://www.billboard.com/articles/events/year-in-music-2014/6386043/the-year-in-pop-2014-one-direction-frozen-pharrell \"The Year in Pop 2014: One Direction, 'Frozen,' & Pharrell Dominate\"]. ''Billboard''. Retrieved 8 January 2015</ref> The band went on hiatus in January 2016, allowing all members to pursue other projects.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.express.co.uk/entertainment/music/800249/One-Direction-reunion-timing-Niall-Horan-solo-Harry-Styles|title=One Direction REUNION: Niall Horan opens up on WHEN iconic boyband will get back together|first=George|last=Simpson|date=4 May 2017|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2017/02/15/celebrities/one-direction-reunion-niall-horan-interview/|title=Niall Horan: One Direction reunion is 'definitely' happening|first=Chloe |last=Melas|publisher=}}</ref> As of 2020, the band has sold a total of 50 million records worldwide.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/one-direction-bands-louis-tomlinson-arrested-in-airport-tussle-1666249 |title=One Direction Band's Louis Tomlinson Arrested In Airport Tussle |date=9 March 2018 |work=[[Agence France-Presse]] |accessdate=5 March 2017}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n\n===2010\u20132011: ''The X Factor''===\n[[File:One Direction X Factor Live Glasgow.jpg|thumb|left|One Direction on ''The X Factor'' Live tour in 2011]]\nIn 2010, [[Niall Horan]], [[Zayn Malik]], [[Liam Payne]], [[Harry Styles]], and [[Louis Tomlinson]] auditioned as solo candidates for the [[The X Factor (British series 7)|seventh series]] of the British televised singing competition ''[[The X Factor (British TV series)|The X Factor]]''.<ref name=Kelly>{{cite news| first =Kristy | last = Kelly | url = http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/tv/s103/the-x-factor/news/a331792/nicole-scherzinger-i-did-simon-cowell-a-favour-with-one-direction.html | title= Nicole Scherzinger: 'I did Simon Cowell a favour with One Direction' |work= [[Digital Spy]]| publisher= Hearst | place = UK|date= 26 July 2011 | accessdate =26 July 2011}}</ref> They all failed to progress in the \"Boys\" category at the bootcamp stage of the competition, but were instead put together to form a five-piece boy band,<ref>{{cite news| first = Kate | last = McMahon| url = https://www.mirror.co.uk/celebs/news/2010/07/12/cheryl-tweedy-cancels-x-factor-boot-camp-and-v-festival-appearances-115875-22406276/ | title= Cheryl Tweedy cancels X Factor Boot Camp and V Festival appearances |work=Daily Mirror |date= 12 July 2010|accessdate= 12 July 2010}}</ref> thus qualifying for the \"Groups\" category. [[Nicole Scherzinger]], a guest judge,<ref name=Kelly /><ref>{{cite news|title=One Direction film claims she founded band, not Simon Cowell|url=http://blogs.independent.co.uk/2013/07/19/more-woe-for-nicole-scherzinger-one-direction-film-claims-she-founded-band-not-simon-cowell/|newspaper=[[The Independent]]|location=London|first=Daisy|last=Wyatt|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131122053550/http://blogs.independent.co.uk/2013/07/19/more-woe-for-nicole-scherzinger-one-direction-film-claims-she-founded-band-not-simon-cowell/|archivedate=22 November 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Without Nicole Scherzinger there would be no One Direction |url=http://www.novafm.com.au/audio/without-nicole-scherzinger-there-would-be-no-one-direction |newspaper=NOVA Fm (Australian radio) |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120401001002/http://www.novafm.com.au/audio/without-nicole-scherzinger-there-would-be-no-one-direction |archivedate=1 April 2012 }}</ref> and [[Simon Cowell]] have both claimed to have come up with the idea of forming the band. In 2013, Cowell said that it \"took him 10 minutes to put them together as a group\".<ref name=\"1D Day\">{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a533467/simon-cowell-talks-one-direction-formation-it-was-my-idea.html|title=Simon Cowell talks One Direction formation: 'It was my idea'|last=Harp|first=Justin|date=24 November 2013|work=[[Digital Spy]]|accessdate=24 November 2013}}</ref> Subsequently, the group got together for two weeks to get to know each other and to practice.<ref name=\"thehothits1\">{{cite news|first1=Stan |last1=Walker |first2=Short |last2=Stack |first3=Michael |last3=Paynter |first4=Amy |last4=Meredith |url=http://www.thehothits.com/artists/6069/one-direction/bio |title=One Direction Biography |work=[[The Hot Hits Live from LA]]  |accessdate=27 April 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120327221234/http://www.thehothits.com/artists/6069/one-direction/bio |archivedate=27 March 2012 }}</ref><ref name=autogenerated10>{{cite web|newspaper=South Wales Echo |url=http://www.walesonline.co.uk/showbiz-and-lifestyle/showbiz/2012/01/13/one-direction-prepare-for-cardiff-sell-out-shows-91466-30112196/ |title=One Direction prepare for Cardiff sell-out shows |publisher=[[Media Wales]] |date=13 January 2012 |accessdate=6 June 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120126001640/http://www.walesonline.co.uk/showbiz-and-lifestyle/showbiz/2012/01/13/one-direction-prepare-for-cardiff-sell-out-shows-91466-30112196/ |archivedate=26 January 2012 }}</ref> Styles came up with the name One Direction.<ref name=\"thehothits1\" /> For their qualifying song at \"judges' houses\", and their first song as a group, One Direction sang an acoustic version of \"[[Torn (Ednaswap song)|Torn]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertainment.stv.tv/tv/200816-the-x-factor-2010-the-acts-who-made-it-to-the-live-shows/ |publisher=[[STV (TV network)|STV]] |place=[[Scotland|SCO]], UK |title=The X Factor 2010: the 12 acts who made it to the Live Shows |date=3 October 2010 |accessdate=4 November 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101124111354/http://entertainment.stv.tv/tv/200816-the-x-factor-2010-the-acts-who-made-it-to-the-live-shows/ |archivedate=24 November 2010 }}</ref> Cowell later commented that their performance convinced him that they \"were confident, fun, like a gang of friends, and kind of fearless as well.\"<ref name = \"simoncowellQ&A\">{{cite news| first = Andy | last = Greene |url = https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/exclusive-q-a-simon-cowell-on-one-directions-rise-to-stardom-20120409 |title=Exclusive Q&A: Simon Cowell on One Direction's Rise to Stardom |work=Rolling Stone  |date= 9 April 2012 |accessdate= 11 May 2012}}</ref> Within the first four weeks of the [[The X Factor (British series 7)#Live show details|live shows]], they were his final act in the competition. The group quickly gained popularity in the UK.<ref name=\"simoncowellQ&A\" />\n\nOne Direction achieved third place in the competition and immediately after the final, their song \"[[Forever Young (Alphaville song)|Forever Young]]\", which would have been released if they had won ''The X Factor'', was leaked onto the internet.<ref name = thirdplace>{{cite news|url= https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/tvandradioblog/2010/dec/10/xfactor-final-results-liveblog |title=The X Factor 2010 final results show|work=The Guardian|date= 12 December 2012 |accessdate=15 March 2012 | location = London | first = Stuart | last = Heritage}}</ref> Shortly afterwards it was confirmed that One Direction had been signed by Cowell to a reported [[Pound sterling|\u00a3]]2&nbsp;million [[Syco Music|Syco Records]] record contract.<ref>{{cite news | first = Mayer | last = Nissim |url= http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/s103/the-x-factor/news/a300729/one-direction-get-gbp2m-syco-investment.html | title= One Direction 'get \u00a32m Syco investment' | work= [[Digital Spy]] | publisher = Hearst | place = UK | date=28 January 2011|accessdate=23 October 2011}}</ref> Recording for their debut album began in January 2011, as they flew to Los Angeles to work with [[RedOne]], a record producer.<ref name = Miller>{{cite news | first = Ed | last = Miller |url = http://www.musicweek.com/news/read/sony-excited-about-one-direction-potential/046464 | title = Sony excited about One Direction potential |work= [[Music Week]]  |date = 16 August 2011 | accessdate = 27 July 2012}}</ref> A book licensed by One Direction, ''One Direction: Forever Young (Our Official X Factor Story)'', was published by [[HarperCollins]] in February 2011,<ref>{{cite web| first =Alex | last = Fletcher | url = http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/showbiz/s103/the-x-factor/news/a304324/one-direction-release-autobiography.html | title= One Direction release autobiography |work= [[Digital Spy]]|publisher= Hearst | place = UK | date = 17 February 2011 | accessdate=14 January 2012}}</ref> subsequently topping [[The Sunday Times|''The Sunday Times'' Best Seller list]].<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.sugarscape.com/tags/band/621789/one-direction-number-one-sunday-times-bestseller-list?page=0%2C0 |title=One Direction book number one on Sunday Times bestsetller list |work= [[Sugar (magazine)|Sugarscape]] |date= 5 April 2011|accessdate= 27 July 2012}}</ref> The same month, the boy band and other contestants from the series participated in the ''X Factor'' Live Tour. During the tour, the group performed for 500,000 people throughout the UK.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hmvtickets.com/events/1622?REFID=hmv_tickets_system_body |title=Tickets for One Direction at HMV Apollo Hammersmith, London, now available from hmvtickets.com |publisher=[[HMV]] |accessdate=11 May 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120121204017/http://www.hmvtickets.com/events/1622?REFID=hmv_tickets_system_body |archivedate=21 January 2012 }}</ref> After the tour concluded in April 2011, the group continued working on their debut album.<ref name = Miller /> Recording took place in Stockholm, London and Los Angeles, as One Direction worked with producers [[Carl Falk]], [[Savan Kotecha]], [[Steve Mac]], and [[Rami (producer)|Rami Yacoub]], among others.<ref name=\"allmusic1\">{{cite web | url = http://www.allmusic.com/album/up-all-night-r2324993/credits |title= Up All Night \u2013 One Direction |publisher = AllMusic |date=21 November 2011 |accessdate=21 March 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite AV media notes | title =Up All Night |others=One Direction |year=2011 |type=liner notes |publisher= [[Syco Music]], [[Sony Music Entertainment]]}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable collapsible collapsed\" style=\"width:100%; margin:1em auto 1em auto; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#BFBFBF;\"| ''The X Factor'' performances and results\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:centre\"|Episode\n! style=\"text-align:centre\"|Song choice\n! style=\"text-align:centre\"|Theme\n! style=\"text-align:centre\"|Result\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"| Auditions\n|[[Harry Styles]]: \"[[Isn't She Lovely]]\"\n|rowspan=\"5\"| Free choice (caught singing while driving)\n|rowspan=\"5\"| Through to bootcamp\n|-\n| [[Zayn Malik]]: \"[[Let Me Love You (Mario song)|Let Me Love You]]\"\n|-\n| [[Liam Payne]]: \"[[Cry Me a River (Arthur Hamilton song)|Cry Me a River]]\"\n|-\n| [[Niall Horan]]: \"[[So Sick]]\"\n|-\n| [[Louis Tomlinson]]: \"[[Hey There Delilah]]\"\n|-\n| Bootcamp (Day 1)\n| Boys category: \"[[Man in the Mirror]]\"\n| Sing-offs\n| Through to bootcamp day 2 & 3\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"| Bootcamp (Day 3)\n|Harry: \"[[Stop Crying Your Heart Out]]\"\n|rowspan=\"5\"| Solo performances\n|rowspan=\"5\"| Eliminated individually; One Direction formed and put through to Judge's houses\n|-\n|Zayn: unknown\n|-\n|Liam: \"[[Stop Crying Your Heart Out]]\"\n|-\n|Niall: \"[[Champagne Supernova]]\"\n|-\n|Louis: \"[[Make You Feel My Love]]\"\n|-\n|Judges' houses\n|\"[[Torn (Natalie Imbruglia song)|Torn]]\"\n|Free choice\n|Through to live shows\n|-\n| Live show 1\n|\"[[Viva la Vida]]\"\n|Number-one singles\n|Safe\n|-\n| Live show 2\n|\"[[My Life Would Suck Without You]]\"\n|Heroes\n|Safe\n|-\n| Live show 3\n|\"[[Nobody Knows (Pink song)|Nobody Knows]]\"\n|Guilty pleasures\n|Safe\n|-\n| Live show 4\n| \"[[Total Eclipse of the Heart]]\"\n|Halloween\n|Safe\n|-\n| Live show 5\n| \"[[Kids in America (song)|Kids in America]]\"\n|American anthems\n|Safe\n|-\n| Live show 6\n| \"[[Something About the Way You Look Tonight]]\"\n|Songs by [[Elton John]]\n|Safe\n|-\n| Live show 7\n| \"[[All You Need Is Love]]\"\n|Songs by [[The Beatles]]\n|Safe\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Live show 8\n|\"[[Summer of '69]]\" \n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Rock music|Rock]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Safe\n|-\n|\"[[You Are So Beautiful]]\"\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Semi-final\n|\"[[Only Girl (In the World)]]\"\n|Club classics\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Safe\n|-\n|\"[[Chasing Cars]]\"\n|Song to get you to the final\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|Final\n|\"[[Your Song]]\"\n|Contestant's choice\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Safe\n|-\n|\"[[She's the One (World Party song)|She's the One]]\" (with [[Robbie Williams]])\n|Celebrity duet\n|-\n|\"[[Torn (Natalie Imbruglia)|Torn]]\"\n|Contestant's choice\n|Eliminated; Third place\n|}\n\n===2011\u20132012: ''Up All Night''===\nReleased in September 2011, One Direction's debut single, \"[[What Makes You Beautiful]]\", was a commercial and international success. It reached number one on the [[UK Singles Chart]], after becoming the most pre-ordered [[Sony Music Entertainment]] single in history.<ref>{{cite news | first =Lewis | last = Corner |url = http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a335956/one-directions-what-makes-you-beautiful-breaks-pre-order-sales-record.html | title=One Direction's 'What Makes You Beautiful' breaks pre-order sales record |work=[[Digital Spy]]|publisher=Hearst | place = UK|date=19 August 2011|accessdate=19 August 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | first = Alan | last = Jones | url = http://www.musicweek.com/story.asp?sectioncode=22&storycode=1046622 | title = What Makes You Beautiful becomes fastest seller of the year | work= [[Music Week]]  |date = 19 September 2011 |accessdate= 5 January 2012}}</ref> Subsequent singles, \"[[Gotta Be You (One Direction song)|Gotta Be You]]\" and \"[[One Thing (One Direction song)|One Thing]]\", peaked in the UK Singles Chart top ten.<ref>{{cite news| first = Alan | last = Jones |url= http://www.musicweek.com/story.asp?sectioncode=1&storycode=1047553&c=1 |title=UK Singles Chart Analysis: Rihanna equals Adele record |work=[[Music Week]] |date=21 November 2011 |accessdate=11 June 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| first =Alan | last = Jones |url = http://www.musicweek.com/story.asp?sectioncode=1&storycode=1048551&c=1 |title = Official Chart Analysis: Emeli Sande album sells 113k, DJ Fresh single shifts 128k |work= [[Music Week]]  |date=20 February 2012 | accessdate = 17 March 2012}}</ref> In November 2011, they signed a record deal with [[Columbia Records]] in North America.<ref>{{cite web| first = Lewis | last = Corner| url = http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a352201/one-direction-sign-us-record-deal-with-adele-label-columbia.html |title=One Direction sign U.S. record deal with Adele label Columbia | work=[[Digital Spy]]|publisher= Hearst | place = UK |date= 22 November 2011 |accessdate= 14 January 2012}}</ref> [[Steve Barnett (music executive)|Steve Barnett]], the co-chairman of Columbia Records, said it was not a difficult decision to sign One Direction; \"I just thought there was a void, and maybe they could seize and hold it.\"<ref>{{cite news| first =James C, Jr | last = McKinley | url= https://www.nytimes.com/2012/03/24/arts/music/one-direction-and-the-wanted-boy-bands-return.html |work= [[The New York Times]] | title= One Direction and the Wanted: Boy Bands Return | date=23 March 2012}}</ref> That same month, they released ''[[Up All Night (One Direction album)|Up All Night]]'', their debut studio album, in the UK and Ireland. Critically commended for its appeal to the teenage audience,<ref>{{cite news| first = Adam | last = Markovitz | url = http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,20578458,00.html | type = review | title = Up All Night (2012) One Direction |work=Entertainment Weekly|date= 20 March 2012| accessdate =21 March 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url = https://www.usatoday.com/life/music/reviews/story/2012-03-12/one-direction-up-all-night/53502638/1 | title = Listen Up: Stay 'Up All Night' with One Direction|work= USA Today | publisher = [[Gannett Company|Gannett Co]] | date= 13 March 2012 | accessdate= 31 March 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | first = Matthew | last = Chisling | url = http://www.allmusic.com/album/up-all-night-r2324993/review |title=Up All Night&nbsp;\u2013 One Direction| publisher = AllMusic |date=21 November 2011 |accessdate= 5 January 2012}}</ref> it became the UK's fastest-selling debut album of 2011.<ref>{{cite news |url = http://www.capitalfm.com/artists/one-direction/news/thank-fans-up-all-night-chart-success/ |title= One Direction Thank Fans For 'Up All Night' Chart Success |work= [[Capital (radio network)|Capital FM]]|publisher=[[Global Radio]]|date= 28 November 2011 |accessdate=14 January 2012}}</ref> In December 2011, they embarked on their first headlining UK concert tour, the [[Up All Night Tour]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.capitalfm.com/artists/one-direction/news/up-all-night-tour-watford/ |title= One Direction Prepare For 'Up All Night' Tour With Watford Concert |work=[[Capital (radio network)|Capital FM]]|publisher=[[Global Radio]] | date =19 December 2011| accessdate= 27 March 2012|archiveurl= http://www.freezepage.com/1333935031UMDTEVHWRV?url=http://www.capitalfm.com/artists/one-direction/news/up-all-night-tour-watford/ | archivedate = 9 April 2012}}</ref> Originally, the tour was set to end in January 2012.\n\nUpon One Direction's arrival in the US in February 2012, the group embarked on a radio promotion spree, as well as their first North American concert tour as an opening act for [[Big Time Rush (band)|Big Time Rush]], opening 16 shows after they had completed the first leg of the Up All Night Tour.<ref>{{cite news| first =Mark | last = Savage|url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-18083174 |title= The U.S. love affair with British pop|work= News |publisher= BBC|date= 21 May 2010 | accessdate=25 July 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| first =Stephan | last = Lee|url= http://music-mix.ew.com/2012/02/03/one-direction-big-time-rush-exclusive-photo/ | title= Exclusive Photo: One Direction and Big Time Rush unite for North American tour!|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |accessdate= 4 February 2012}}</ref> That month, they announced that an Oceania leg had been added to the tour.<ref>{{cite news |first= Lisa |last= McGarry |url= http://www.unrealitytv.co.uk/x-factor/one-direction-announce-tour-dates-for-australia-and-new-zealand/ |title= One Direction announce 2012 tour dates for Australia and New Zealand |work= Unreality TV |date= 24 February 2012 |accessdate= 31 March 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20120411004659/http://www.unrealitytv.co.uk/x-factor/one-direction-announce-tour-dates-for-australia-and-new-zealand/ |archivedate= 11 April 2012 }}</ref> They made their first US television appearance on ''[[Today (U.S. TV program)|The Today Show]]'', at the [[Rockefeller Center]]; an estimated 15,000 fans descended on the plaza.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/499360/one-direction-the-wanted-the-billboard-cover-story |title=One Direction & The Wanted: The Billboard Cover Story | first =Steven J | last = Horowitz |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date= 27 March 2012 | accessdate =16 April 2012}}</ref> \"What Makes You Beautiful\" was officially released in the United States that same month,<ref>{{cite news| first =Amanda | last = Hasaka |url= http://www.celebuzz.com/2012-02-14/one-directions-debut-single-what-makes-you-beautiful-now-available-on-itunes/ |title=One Direction's Debut Single 'What Makes You Beautiful' Now Available on iTunes! |work= Celebuzz |date=14 February 2012 |accessdate= 15 February 2012}}</ref> where it debuted on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] at number 28, becoming the highest debut for a British act since 1998.<ref name=\"Hot100\">{{cite web |url = http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/504475/one-direction-has-highest-hot-100-debut-for-new-uk-act-since-1998 |title= One Direction Has Highest Hot 100 Debut For New UK Act Since 1998 |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |date= 22 February 2012 |accessdate=13 March 2012}}</ref> On the US ''Billboard'' Hot 100, it reached as high as number four. As of June 2016, it has sold 4.8 million copies in the US<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7408939/ask-billboard-one-directions-career-sales |title = Ask Billboard: One Direction's Career Sales}}</ref> and over 7 million copes worldwide.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/article/19093915/one-direction-hit-12-million-sales-in-less-than-a-year |title = One Direction hit 12 million sales in less than a year|date = 8 February 2012}}</ref> ''Up All Night'' was released internationally in March, and One Direction became the first UK group to have their debut album reach number one in the US,<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.idolator.com/6226811/one-direction-debut-chart-history?safari=1&Exc_D_LessThanPoint002_p1=1 | title=One Direction Debut at #1, Make Album Chart History| date=21 March 2012}}</ref> and were inducted into the ''[[Guinness World Records]]'' as a result.<ref>{{cite news| first = Colin | last = Daniels| url = http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a404538/adele-one-direction-enter-guinness-world-records.html |title=Adele, One Direction enter 'Guinness World Records' | work = [[Digital Spy]] |publisher=Hearst | place = UK |date=7 September 2012 | accessdate =8 September 2012}}</ref> After the album's international release, it topped the charts in sixteen countries.<ref>{{cite news|url = http://www.musicweek.com/news/read/one-direction-to-hold-global-twitter-viewing-party-for-new-concert-dvd/049052 | title = One Direction to hold global Twitter viewing party for new concert DVD | work= [[Music Week]]  | date=30 May 2012 |accessdate= 11 June 2012}}</ref> ''Up All Night'' also became the first album by a boy band to sell 500,000 digital copies in the US and, by August 2012, had sold over 3 million copies worldwide.<ref name = \"Yahoosales\">{{cite news | title = Week Ending Oct. 21, 2012. Albums: Aldean's Fast Train To #1 | url = http://music.yahoo.com/blogs/chart-watch/week-ending-oct-21-2012-albums-aldean-fast-150305200.html | first =Paul | last = Grein |work= Music |publisher = Yahoo! |date= 24 October 2012 | accessdate = 24 October 2012|location= US}}</ref><ref name = \"12millionsales\">{{cite web| first =Dan | last = Lane|url = http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/one-direction-sell-12-million-singles-albums-and-dvd-and-blu-rays-worldwide-1516/ |title = One Direction sell 12 million singles, albums and DVD and Blu-rays worldwide | publisher = [[Official Charts Company]] |date=2 August 2012 |accessdate=2 August 2012}}</ref> It was the third global best-selling album of the year, selling 4.5 million copies.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aria.com.au/documents/RIN2013.pdf|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130409080309/http://www.aria.com.au/documents/RIN2013.pdf|archivedate=2013-04-09|title=Wayback Machine|date=9 April 2013|website=web.archive.org}}</ref> Following the success of the album, a North American leg of the tour was announced later that month.<ref>{{cite news|url= http://idolator.com/6226892/one-direction-north-american-tour-dates |title=One Direction Reveal North American Tour Dates |work= [[Idolator (website)|Idolator]] |date=21 March 2012 |accessdate=31 March 2012}}</ref>\n\nThe ''Up All Night Tour'', comprising 62 shows, was met with positivity both critically and commercially, with critics praising their singing abilities and stage presence, and with tickets selling out in minutes.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/one-direction-live-review-from-hammersmith-171874 |title=One Direction's Hammersmith Apollo gig | first =James | last = Robertson |date=11 January 2012 |work= Daily Mirror |accessdate= 8 April 2012 | archiveurl = http://www.freezepage.com/1333939607CZJAMCVUXO?url=http://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/one-direction-live-review-from-hammersmith-171874 |archivedate=9 April 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.herald.ie/news/one-direction-show-has-fans-up-all-night-2999092.html |title= One Direction show has fans up all night | last =Ryan | first = Alexandra |date= 25 January 2012 |work= [[Evening Herald]] |publisher= [[Independent News & Media]] |accessdate= 8 April 2012|archiveurl= http://www.freezepage.com/1333939933IFYQZGQCXW?url=http://www.herald.ie/news/one-direction-show-has-fans-up-all-night-2999092.html | archivedate= 9 April 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| last =Brandle | first = Lars|title= One Direction Live: Shriek Show in Australia | url = http://www.billboard.com/articles/photos/live/492534/one-direction-live-shriek-show-in-australia| work = [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=19 April 2012|accessdate= 9 July 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| first1 =Cameron | last1 = Adams | last2 = Siobhan | first2 = Duck|url = http://www.heraldsun.com.au/entertainment/music/one-directions-melbourne-concert-sells-out-in-three-minutes/story-e6frf9hf-1226286954743 |title=One Direction's Melbourne concert sells out in three minutes|work=Herald Sun |location= Australia |date= 2 March 2012|accessdate=1 July 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | first =Bridget | last = Jones|url= http://www.stuff.co.nz/auckland/whats-on/6512032/One-Directions-NZ-tour-sold-out |title=One Direction's NZ tour sold out|work= [[Stuff.co.nz|Stuff]] | place = [[New Zealand|NZ]]  | date = 2 March 2012| accessdate= 1 July 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| first = Emily | last = Hewett |url = http://www.metro.co.uk/music/877239-one-direction-tickets-fans-bombard-ticketmaster-as-ebay-touts-capitalise |title= One Direction tickets: Fans bombard Ticketmaster as eBay touts capitalise| work = [[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]]| date= 1 October 2011| accessdate= 1 July 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | title= One Direction to Headline Madison Square Garden December 3, 2012 |url = http://www.kait8.com/story/17325179/one-direction-to-headline-madison-square-garden-december-3-2012 |publisher= [[KAIT]]  |date=3 April 2012 |accessdate=8 April 2012|archiveurl= http://www.freezepage.com/1333943764HSQQZOQYGS?url=http://www.kait8.com/story/17325179/one-direction-to-headline-madison-square-garden-december-3-2012 | archivedate = 9 April 2012}}</ref> A recording of a concert from the tour, ''[[One Direction: Up All Night \u2013 The Live Tour|Up All Night: The Live Tour]]'', was released in May 2012.<ref name=\"musicDVD\">{{cite news | first = Lewis | last = Corner |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a376053/one-direction-perform-moments-on-tour-video.html |title = One Direction perform 'Moments' on tour | type = video | work= [[Digital Spy]] | publisher= Hearst | place = UK |date = 12 April 2012 |accessdate= 27 April 2012}}</ref> In addition to the DVD topping the charts in twenty-five countries, its global sales had exceeded 1 million copies by August 2012.<ref name=\"12millionsales\"/><ref name =DVDWW>{{cite news | first =Rhian | last = Jones |url= http://www.musicweek.com/news/read/one-direction-live-dvd-hits-no1-in-25-countries/049138 | title= One Direction live DVD hits No.1 in 25 countries | work= [[Music Week]]  | date = 8 June 2012 |accessdate=11 June 2012}}</ref> One Direction's first book to be licensed in America, ''Dare to Dream: Life as One Direction'', published in the US in May 2012, topped [[The New York Times Best Seller list|''The New York Times'' Best Seller list]].<ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.nytimes.com/best-sellers-books/2012-06-10/paperback-books/list.html |work=The New York Times | title=Best Sellers | date=10 June 2012 | accessdate = 24 August 2012 | first=Gregory | last=Cowles}}</ref> In June 2012, Nick Gatfield, the chairman and chief executive officer of [[Sony Music Entertainment|Sony Music Entertainment UK]], stated how he expects One Direction to represent a $100&nbsp;million business empire over 2013.<ref name = \"business empire\">{{cite news| first =Jocelyn | last = Vena | url = http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1687496/one-direction-hundred-million-dollar-business.jhtml |title = One Direction Set To Become Booming $100 Million Business|publisher=[[MTV News]]|date=15 June 2012 |accessdate= 15 June 2012}}</ref> Gatfield stated, \"What you might not know about One Direction is that they already represent a $50&nbsp;million business and that's a figure we expect to double next year\".<ref name=\"business empire\"/> In August 2012, the group's record sales exceeded 8 million singles, 3&nbsp;million albums, and 1&nbsp;million DVDs, and they performed \"What Makes You Beautiful\" at the [[2012 Summer Olympics closing ceremony]] in London, which represented the handover to Rio de Janeiro as the host of the [[2016 Summer Olympics]].<ref name=\"12millionsales\"/><ref>{{cite news | first =Kia | last = Makarechi |url = http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/08/12/one-direction-closing-ceremony-olympics_n_1770803.html |title= One Direction & Closing Ceremony: Olympics Get A Dose Of 'What Makes You Beautiful' | work = [[The Huffington Post]]| date= 12 August 2012 |accessdate=13 August 2012}}</ref> One Direction were the biggest winners of the [[2012 MTV Video Music Awards]] winning their three nominations on 6 September 2012, including [[MTV Video Music Award for Best New Artist|Best New Artist]].<ref name= videomusicawards>{{cite news| place = UK | first =Amelia | last = Butterfly |url = http://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/19515754 | title= One Direction win three MTV Video Music Awards in LA | work = Newsbeat | publisher = BBC|date=7 September 2012|accessdate=7 September 2012}}</ref>\n\n[[File:One Direction Sydney 6.jpg|thumb|right|One Direction performing on their [[Up All Night Tour]], April 2012]]\n\nIn April 2012, an American band that went by the same name filed a [[trademark infringement]] lawsuit.<ref name = trademark>{{cite news| first =Rhian | last = Jones |url= http://www.musicweek.com/news/read/one-direction-sued-for-trademark-infringement/048557 |title=One Direction sued for trademark infringement |work= [[Music Week]]  | date= 11 April 2012 |accessdate= 27 April 2012}}</ref> According to the lawsuit, the US band had been using the name since 2009, recorded two albums and filed an application to register the trademark name in the US in February 2011.<ref name=trademark/> The US band said they were entitled to three times the profits made by the UK band, as well as compensatory damages in excess of US$1&nbsp;million.<ref name=trademark/> The lawsuit claimed that Syco and Sony Music \"chose to ignore the plaintiff's rights and wilfully infringed them\" after they realised in early 2011 that the two bands shared the same name.<ref name=trademark/> Syco Records subsequently counter-sued, suggesting the US group was trying to make money from One Direction's success and that the boy band was the first to use the name in US interstate commerce.<ref name=lawsuit/> The [[BBC]] reported in September 2012 that the UK group won the legal dispute over the right to keep using their band name; the US band changed its name to Uncharted Shores.<ref name=lawsuit/> The change of name was announced in a joint statement that also noted both groups were happy with the outcome.<ref name = lawsuit>{{cite web |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/19473197 |title= One Direction win fight against U.S. band to keep name | work =[[Newsbeat]] |publisher=BBC |date=7 September 2012|accessdate=8 September 2012}}</ref>\n\n===2012\u20132013: ''Take Me Home''===\n[[File:One Direction at the Logies Awards 2012.jpg|thumb|left|One Direction at red carpet of the [[Logie Awards of 2012]] in [[Melbourne]]]]\n\nIn September 2012, \"[[Live While We're Young]]\", the lead single from the group's second album, was released, and was a global success. It reached the top ten in almost every country it charted in and recorded the highest one-week opening sales figure for a song by a non-US artist in the US.<ref>{{cite news| first =Tina| last = Hart|url = http://www.musicweek.com/news/read/one-direction-have-fastest-selling-single-by-a-uk-artist/052114 | title = One Direction achieve fastest-selling single by a UK act in the U.S. |work= Music Week |date= 21 October 2012 |accessdate=11 October 2012|location=United Kingdom}}</ref> A second single, \"[[Little Things (One Direction song)|Little Things]]\", resulted in the band's second [[List of UK Singles Chart number ones of the 2010s|number one single]] in the UK.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/one-direction-score-number-1-single-and-album-__2564/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180830142315/http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/one-direction-score-number-1-single-and-album-__2564/|archivedate=2018-08-30|title=One Direction score Number 1 single AND album!|date=30 August 2018|website=web.archive.org}}</ref> In November 2012, One Direction's second studio album, ''[[Take Me Home (One Direction album)|Take Me Home]]'', was released.<ref name=\"TMH\">{{cite news |url= https://itunes.apple.com/nl/album/take-me-home/id572141438|title= Take Me Home | publisher =[[iTunes Store]] |agency=[[Apple Inc.|Apple]] |accessdate=16 November 2012|language=Dutch| location = Netherlands}}</ref> It was an international hit, reaching number one in over 35 countries. Upon reaching number one on the ''[[Billboard 200]]'', the group became the first boy band in US chart history to record two number-one albums in the same calendar year alongside becoming the first group since 2008 to record two number-one albums in the same year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/474059/one-directions-take-me-home-debuts-at-no-1-with-years-third-biggest-opening|title=One Direction's 'Take Me Home' Debuts at No. 1 With Year's Third-Biggest Opening|website=Billboard}}</ref> One Direction became the first group ever to have their first two albums reach atop the ''Billboard 200''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/music/9694957/One-Direction-make-US-chart-history-with-Take-Me-Home.html|title=One Direction make US chart history with 'Take Me Home'|date=22 November 2012|website=Telegraph.co.uk}}</ref> ''Take Me Home'' sold 540,000 copies in its first week in the US, debuted atop the ''Billboard'' 200, and topped the charts in more than thirty-four other countries.<ref name = \"USTMHdebut\">{{cite web|url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/474059/one-directions-take-me-home-debuts-at-no-1-with-years-third-biggest-opening |title=One Direction's 'Take Me Home' Debuts at No. 1 With Year's Third-Biggest Opening | work=Billboard |date=20 November 2012|accessdate= 22 November 2012 | location = US}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| first =Tina | last = Hart|url = http://www.musicweek.com/news/read/imagem-music-signs-one-direction-hit-writer-fiona-bevan/052709 |title=Imagem Music signs One Direction hit-writer Fiona Bevan |work=[[Music Week]] |date=29 November 2012 | accessdate =1 December 2012|location= United Kingdom}}</ref> Additionally, ''Up All Night'' and ''Take Me Home'' were the number three and number four best-selling albums of 2012 globally, each album selling over 4.4&nbsp;million units worldwide.<ref name=\"Modest Management\">{{cite web|url=http://www.modestmanagement.com/one-direction/ |title=One Direction |publisher=Modest Management |accessdate=2 August 2014}}</ref> The album and \"Little Things\" both debuted at number one in the UK simultaneously, making One Direction the youngest act in British chart history to achieve that.<ref>{{cite news | first = Alan | last = Jones | url = http://www.musicweek.com/businessanalysis/read/official-charts-analysis-one-direction-youngest-ever-act-to-hit-no-1-in-albums-and-singles-lists/052592 |title=Official Charts Analysis: One Direction youngest ever act to score No. 1 Album and Single simultaneously |work=[[Music Week]] |date=19 November 2012 |accessdate=19 November 2012| location = UK}}</ref>\n\n''Take Me Home'' was written in groups and has an average of just under five songwriters per track. Savan Kotecha, Rami Yacoub, and Carl Falk, who composed One Direction's hits \"What Makes You Beautiful\" and \"One Thing\", spent six months in Stockholm developing songs for the album, and were able to shape melodies around their tones.<ref name =Wolk>{{cite news| first = Douglas | last = Wol|url= http://entertainment.time.com/2012/11/13/one-directions-songwriters-theyre-what-make-the-boy-band-beautiful/ | title = One Direction's songwriters: They're what make the boy band beautiful|work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]] |date=28 June 2012 |accessdate=25 August 2012}}</ref> One Direction began recording the album in May 2012, in Stockholm at Kinglet Studios.<ref name=credits>{{cite AV media notes |title = Take Me Home |others=One Direction |year=2012 |type=liner notes |publisher=[[Syco Records]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url= http://www.mtv.co.uk/news/one-direction/354656-one-direction-sweden |title= One Direction Recording Second Album |publisher=MTV News |date=11 May 2012 |accessdate=25 August 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url= http://www.capitalfm.com/artists/one-direction/news/new-album/ |title= One Direction Enjoy 'Amazing Day' In The Studio Recording New Album |publisher=Capital (Global Radio)|date=12 May 2012 |accessdate=25 August 2012}}</ref> The album cover artwork features the group surrounding a traditional British K2 [[red telephone box]], a familiar sight on the streets of the UK.<ref>{{cite web|last=Wheeler |first=Rachael |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/one-direction-reveal-album-artwork-1289666 |title=One Direction reveal album artwork for Take Me Home \u2013 3am & Mirror Online |work=Daily Mirror |date=30 August 2012 |accessdate=2 August 2014}}</ref> ''Take Me Home'' garnered mixed reviews from [[music journalism|music critics]]. There was praise for its quality of production, while it was criticised for its generic, rushed nature.<ref>{{cite news| first =Matt | last = Collar |url = http://www.allmusic.com/album/take-me-home-mw0002418914 |title = Take Me Home (CD \u2013 Sony Music Distribution #88725475972) | publisher = [[AllMusic]]| date = 11 November 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |first= Al | last = Fox |url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/music/reviews/fh8r | type = review |title= One Direction \u2013 Take Me Home |publisher= [[BBC Music]] |date= 12 November 2012|accessdate= 16 November 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | type = review | first = Adam | last = Markovitz |url=http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,20643783,00.html | title = Take Me Home \u2013 One Direction | work = [[Entertainment Weekly]] |date=11 November 2012 | accessdate= 16 November 2012}}</ref><ref name=NYT/><ref name=Guardian/><ref name=NZH/>\n\nOne Direction performed \"Little Things\" at the 2012 [[Royal Variety Performance]] in the presence of [[Elizabeth II|Queen Elizabeth II]], and headlined a sold-out show at New York City's [[Madison Square Garden]] on 3 December 2012.<ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/queen-elizabeth-II/9690193/Royal-Variety-Performance-2012-One-Direction-and-Girls-Aloud-sing-for-The-Queen.html |title=Royal Variety Performance 2012: One Direction and Girls Aloud sing for The Queen |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]| date= 20 November 2012 | accessdate = 24 November 2012 |location=London}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/photos/live/473866/one-direction-headlines-sold-out-show-at-madison-square-garden |title=One Direction Headlines Sold-Out Show at Madison Square Garden|date=4 December 2012| accessdate =5 December 2012|work=Billboard| first =Andrew | last = Hampp}}</ref> In February 2013, One Direction released a cover version of \"[[One Way or Another]]\" and \"[[Teenage Kicks]]\", \"[[One Way or Another (Teenage Kicks)]]\", as the 2013 [[Comic Relief]] single.<ref name=\"Robertson\">{{cite news|url= https://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/one-direction-reflect-on-life-changing-1535079 |title='We are the most selfish people ever': One Direction reflect on 'life changing' charity trip to Africa 'slums'|date=15 January 2013|accessdate=16 February 2013 | work =Metro| first =James | last = Robertson}}</ref> As part of their involvement with the UK charity, One Direction travelled to Ghana to volunteer at a children's hospital, visit a school and make donations.\n\nFollowing the release of ''Take Me Home'', One Direction embarked on their second concert tour in February 2013, the [[Take Me Home Tour (One Direction)|Take Me Home Tour]].<ref>{{cite news| first =Jocelyn | last = Vena|url= http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1682975/one-direction-tour-dates.jhtml | title= One Direction Announce U.S. Dates on 2013 World Tour | work = News |publisher=MTV |date=12 April 2012 |accessdate=20 April 2012}}</ref> The concert tour consisted of 123 shows in Europe, North America, Asia, and Oceania. Ticket sales reached 300,000 within a day of release in the UK and Ireland, which included a six-date sell-out at [[The O2 Arena|the O<sub>2</sub> Arena]] in London.<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.mtv.co.uk/news/one-direction/349694-one-direction-tickets |title=One Direction Fans in Ticket-Buying Frenzy | publisher =MTV |date=26 February 2012 |accessdate=20 April 2012}}</ref> In the Australian and New Zealand markets, tickets grossed US$15.7&nbsp;million, with all 190,000 tickets being sold for the eighteen shows to be held.<ref>{{cite news| first =Brittany | last = Stack |url= http://www.dailytelegraph.com.au/news/how-one-direction-cashed-in-on-their-hugely-successful-australian-tour/story-e6freuy9-1226341685202 |title=How One Direction cashed in on their hugely successful Australian tour |work=[[The Daily Telegraph (Sydney)|The Daily Telegraph]] | place = AU|date= 29 April 2012 |accessdate=11 June 2012}}</ref> The tour received critical acclaim from music critics who praised the band's live vocals and their performance abilities and was a commercial success, selling 1,635,000 tickets from 134 shows.<ref name=\"Box Office\">{{cite web|url=http://onedirectionmusic.com/ |title=One Direction &#124; Welcome to the One Direction website! |publisher=Onedirectionmusic.com |accessdate=2 August 2014}}</ref> In total, the tour grossed $114 million. The [[Official Charts Company]] revealed that One Direction had sold 2,425,000 records in the UK by February 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/the-brit-awards-2013-the-real-winners-revealed-1869/|title= The BRIT Awards 2013: The biggest selling nominees revealed|publisher= [[Official Charts Company]]| first =Dan | last = Lane|date= 20 February 2013 | accessdate = 21 February 2013}}</ref>\n\n===2013\u20132014: ''Midnight Memories'' and ''This Is Us''===\n[[File:One Direction 2, 2013.jpg|thumb|right|One Direction in [[Glasgow]] on their [[Take Me Home Tour (One Direction)|Take Me Home Tour]] in February 2013]]\n\n\"[[Best Song Ever (song)|Best Song Ever]]\", the lead single of the group's then-upcoming third studio album ''[[Midnight Memories]]'', was released on 22 July 2013. The song<ref>{{citation|last=Brandie|first=Lars|date=26 June 2013|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1568160/one-direction-tease-best-song-ever-release-new-movie-trailer|title=One Direction Tease 'Best Song Ever'; Release New Movie Trailer | newspaper = [[Billboard.com|Billboard]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title= One Direction Announce New Single 'Best Song Ever'| place = UK | url= http://www.mtv.co.uk/news/one-direction/384889-one-direction-new-single-best-song-ever-this-is-us-new-trailer |publisher= MTV| accessdate= 1 July 2013}}</ref> is their highest charting single in the US to date, reaching number two.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/one-direction|title=One Direction Chart History|website=Billboard|accessdate=19 July 2019}}</ref> It broke the [[Vevo#Record holders|24-Hour Vevo Record]] with 10.9&nbsp;million views on YouTube (this was the second time the band held the record with \"Live While We're Young\" attaining 8.2&nbsp;million views on 20 September 2012).<ref>{{cite web|title=One Direction's 'Best Song Ever' Breaks One-Day Vevo Record|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/4336507/one-directions-best-song-ever-breaks-one-day-vevo-record|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=One Direction beat Justin Bieber VEVO record with new music video|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/music/news/a408584/one-direction-beat-justin-bieber-vevo-record-with-new-music-video.html|work=[[Digital Spy]]|date=27 September 2012}}</ref> ''[[One Direction: This Is Us]]'', a 3D documentary and concert film about the group directed by [[Morgan Spurlock]] and produced by Spurlock, Ben Winston, Adam Milano and Simon Cowell, was released by [[TriStar Pictures]] on 30 August 2013.<ref name=\"3Dfilm\">{{cite news | url = http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/474195/one-direction-3d-film-gets-super-director|title= One Direction 3D Film Gets 'Super' Director| first = Marc | last = Schneider|work=Billboard|date= 13 November 2012|accessdate=15 November 2012|location= New York}}</ref> The film was a box office success, topping the UK and US box offices and grossing over $60&nbsp;million worldwide, and became the fourth highest-grossing concert movie.<ref name=autogenerated6>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/genres/chart/?id=musicconcert.htm |title=Music Concert Movies at the Box Office |publisher=Box Office Mojo |date=8 January 2014 |accessdate=2 August 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 May 2013, the band announced their first all-stadium tour, the [[Where We Are Tour (One Direction)|Where We Are Tour]]. Tickets for the tour sold out in minutes and more shows were added due to \"overwhelming demand.\"<ref>{{cite web | url=https://chicago.suntimes.com/news/2013/12/4/18541298/one-direction-adds-show-to-chicago-stop-on-tour |title = One Direction adds show to Chicago stop on tour|date = 4 December 2013}}</ref> On 23 November 2013, in support of ''Midnight Memories'', the band participated in \"1D Day\",<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.1dday.com/ |title=Welcome to 1D Day \u2013 1D Day \u2013 One Direction |publisher=1dday.com |date=25 November 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131213102853/http://www.1dday.com/gb/home | archivedate= 13 December 2013 | accessdate=19 January 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/showbiz/news/a533434/one-direction-1d-day-live-stream-watch.html |title=One Direction '1D Day' Live Stream \u2013 watch \u2013 Showbiz News |work=Digital Spy |date=23 November 2013 |accessdate=19 January 2014}}</ref> a day dedicated to One Direction fans. The day constituted of a landmark 7.5-hour socially interactive YouTube live-stream featuring live band performances, celebrity guests including, [[Simon Cowell]], [[Cindy Crawford]], [[Piers Morgan]], and [[Jerry Springer]]. On 28 October 2013, the second single from ''Midnight Memories'', \"[[Story of My Life (One Direction song)|Story of My Life]],\" was released, charting at number six in the US and at number two in the UK, while charting at number one in countries such as Mexico, Spain, Bulgaria, Denmark, and Ireland.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/One-Direction|title=One Direction Chart History|website=Billboard}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/singles-chart/20131208/7501/|title=Official Singles Chart Top 100 &#124; Official Charts Company|website=www.officialcharts.com}}</ref>\n\n[[File:One_Direction_at_the_New_Jersey_concert_on_7.2.13_IMG_4238_(9206417991).jpg|thumb|left|The band performing in [[East Rutherford]], New Jersey on 2 July 2013]]\n\n''Midnight Memories'' was released globally on 25 November 2013. It debuted at number one in the UK and in the US, making them the first group to debut at number one on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] with its first three albums, and the second to reach the top after [[The Monkees]] in 1967.<ref name=\"Billboard record\">{{cite news|first=Keith|last=Caulfield|title=One Direction Scores Historic Third No. 1 Album on Billboard 200 Chart|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5812384/one-direction-scores-historic-third-no-1-album-on-billboard-200-chart|work=Billboard|date=4 December 2013|accessdate=4 December 2013}}</ref> The album was described by the band as edgier and as having a \"slightly rockier tone\" than their previous efforts.<ref>{{cite web|last= Percival| first= Ashley|title= One Direction Big Announcement: 'Where We Are' Stadium Tour Confirmed For 2014|url= http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2013/05/16/one-direction-big-announcement-where-we-are-tour-2014_n_3284795.html |work= The Huffington Post|accessdate=1 July 2013| date= 16 May 2013}}</ref> Despite being released at the year's end, it was the best-selling album worldwide in 2013 with 4 million copies sold globally.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-28599903 | title=One Direction top global album chart| work=BBC News| date=August 2014}}</ref> To promote the album, the band performed on both the [[The X Factor (U.S. TV series)|American]] and [[The X Factor (UK TV series)|British]] versions of ''The X Factor''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.heatworld.com/Celeb-News/2013/10/One-Direction-confirmed-for-The-X-Factor/|title=One Direction confirmed for The X Factor 2013 live shows|publisher=heatworld.com|last=Lewis|first=Anna|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131018011227/http://www.heatworld.com/Celeb-News/2013/10/One-Direction-confirmed-for-The-X-Factor/|archivedate=18 October 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2013, One Direction broke yet another UK sales record with the DVD and [[Blu-ray]] release of ''This Is Us''. Nearly 270,000 copies of the film were sold in the UK within three days of its release, beating the record previously set by ''[[Michael Jackson: This Is It|Michael Jackson's This Is It]]'' in 2010 by 10,000 copies.<ref name=\"Official Charts\">{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/one-direction-beat-michael-jacksons-chart-record-2695/#.Ur4VQbWDpK0.twitter |title=One Direction beat Michael Jackson's chart record |publisher=Officialcharts.com |date=23 December 2013 |accessdate=19 January 2014}}</ref> The group was named among the Top Global artists of 2013 by the [[International Federation of the Phonographic Industry|IFPI]] because of strong digital downloads, physical albums, on-demand streams, and music videos.<ref name=\"IFPI\">{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/one-direction-named-top-global-recording-artist-in-new-award-9093917.html|title=One Direction named top Global Recording Artist in new award|work=The Independent|date= 30 January 2014|accessdate=30 January 2014|location=London|first=Adam|last=Sherwin}}</ref>\n\nThe band embarked on the Where We Are Tour on 25 April 2014, and it was concluded on 5 October 2014. Playing 69 shows with an average of 49,848 fans per show, the tour grossed over $290 million, becoming the [[List of highest-grossing concert tours|highest-grossing concert tour]] in 2014, the 15th [[List of highest-grossing concert tours|highest-grossing concert tour]] of all time, and the highest-grossing tour of all time by a vocal group.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2015/03/24/these-were-the-10-highest-grossing-tours-of-2014/|title=These Were The 10 Highest-Grossing Tours Of 2014|first=Hugh|last=McIntyre|website=Forbes|accessdate=19 July 2019}}</ref> The tour was attended by 3.4 million fans.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6281518/one-direction-where-we-are-tour-three-million|title=One Direction's Where We Are Tour Attended by 3.4 Million Fans|website=Billboard|accessdate=19 July 2019}}</ref> In August of that same year, the group released their third book, ''One Direction: Where We Are: Our Band, Our Story: 100% Official''.\n\n=== 2014\u20132015: ''Four'' ===\n[[File:OnedirectionWWATchile.jpg|thumb|right|One Direction on stage in [[Santiago]], Chile on 14 April 2014 during their [[Where We Are Tour (One Direction)|Where We Are Tour]] ]]\nOn 21 July 2014, One Direction announced ''[[One Direction: Where We Are - The Concert Film]]'', a film which documents the concerts of 28 and 29 June 2014 that took place in [[San Siro Stadium]] during their [[Where We Are Tour (One Direction)|Where We Are Tour]]. After the announcement, the band announced the film would also have a limited 10\u201311 October 2014 international cinema release before its home media release in November 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/Where-We-Are-Live-Stadium/dp/B00KH0VSOU/ref=sr_1_1?s=dvd&ie=UTF8&qid=1400834967&sr=1-1&keywords=B00KH0VSOU&tag=smarturl-gb-21 |title=Where We Are: Live From San Siro Stadium [DVD&#93;: Amazon.co.uk: One Direction: DVD & Blu-ray |accessdate=25 July 2014}}</ref> The group also released an autobiography book titled ''Who We Are'' on 25 September 2014.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.teenvogue.com/entertainment/books/2014-07/one-direction-autobiography-who-we-are | title=Attention, Directioners: 1D Is Releasing an Autobiography! Here's the Scoop on Your New Favorite Book | work=Teen Vogue | accessdate=13 September 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 September 2014, One Direction announced their fourth studio album to be titled ''[[Four (One Direction album)|Four]]'', set to be released on 17 November 2014.<ref name=\"New Album Four (Time)\">{{cite news|last1=Locker|first1=Melissa|title=One Direction Announces New Album Four, Out November 17|url=https://time.com/3303214/one-direction-four-new-album-release-date/|accessdate=8 September 2014|work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|agency=[[Time Inc.]]|date=8 September 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"New Album Four (LA Times)\">{{cite news|last1=Kennedy|first1=Gerrick D.|title=One Direction to release new album 'Four' on Nov. 17|url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/music/posts/la-et-ms-one-direction-to-release-new-album-four-on-nov-17-20140908-story.html |accessdate=8 September 2014 |agency= [[Tribune Publishing]]|work=Los Angeles Times |date=8 September 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"New Album Four (Billboard)\">{{cite news |last1=Lynch |first1=Joe |title= One Direction Reveal New Album 'Four,' Release Free Song (for 24 Hours Only) |url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6243989/one-direction-four-new-album-fireproof|accessdate=8 September 2014|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |agency=[[Prometheus Global Media]] |date=8 September 2014}}</ref> As part of the announcement, one of the songs from the album, \"Fireproof\" was released for free download for 24 hours on their official website.<ref name=\"New Album Four (Time)\"/><ref name=\"New Album Four (LA Times)\"/><ref name=\"New Album Four (Billboard)\"/> \"[[Steal My Girl]]\", the album's lead single, was released on 29 September 2014,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6251459/one-direction-announces-next-four-album-single-steal-my-girl-due-late-september|title=One Direction Announces 'Four' Album Lead Single 'Steal My Girl,' Due Late September \u2013 Billboard|date=14 September 2014|work=Billboard|accessdate=26 October 2014}}</ref> \nreceiving critical acclaim for its classic rock sound.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/article/2014/09/29/one-direction-steal-my-girl/|title=One Direction channels Journey, gets dad-friendly with 'Steal My Girl'|website=EW.com}}</ref> The second single from the album, \"[[Night Changes]]\", was released on 14 November, three days before the album's release. It also achieve platinum status, selling over one million units in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/|title=Gold & Platinum|website=RIAA}}</ref> ''Four'' was released on 17 November 2014, topping the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] and the [[UK Album Chart]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://m.billboard.com/entry/view/id/108201 | title = One Direction's 'Four' Makes Historic No. 1 Debut on Billboard 200 Chart | first= Keith |last=Caulfield | work = Billboard | date = 26 November 2014 | accessdate = 28 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/four-scores-one-direction-a-third-consecutive-official-albums-chart-number-1-3302/|title=Four scores One Direction a third Official Albums Chart Number 1|publisher=}}</ref> In total, in debuted at number one in 18 countries, selling 3.2 million copies.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lthqofficial.com/news/2018/11/17/fourth-anniversary-of-one-directions-album-four|title=Fourth Anniversary of One Direction's Album, Four \u2014 LTHQ Official &#124; Louis Tomlinson &#124; We Made It|website=LTHQ Official}}</ref> It became the top charted album on [[iTunes]] in 67 countries.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mashable.com/2014/09/08/one-direction-new-album-four-fireproof/|title=10 Fans Freaking Out About One Direction's New Album, Free Song|first=Brian Anthony|last=Hernandez|website=Mashable}}</ref> One Direction became the only group in the 58-year history of the ''Billboard'' 200 albums chart to have their first four albums debut at number one.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Caufield|first1=Keith|title=One Direction's 'Four' Makes Historic No. 1 Debut on Billboard 200 Chart|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6327789/one-direction-four-no-1-debut-billboard-200|publisher=Billboard.com|accessdate=20 October 2015}}</ref> In February 2015, the group embarked on their fourth world tour and second all-stadium tour, the [[On the Road Again Tour]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/music/direction-announces-u-s-stadium-tour-2015-article-1.1985235|title=One Direction announces 2015 U.S. stadium tour as part of \u2018On The Road Again\u2019 tour|first=Kirthana|last=Ramisetti|work=New York Daily News|accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref> grossing $208 million, making it the second highest-grossing tour of 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6770115/billboard-touring-conference-winners-one-direction-ed-sheeran|title=Billboard Touring Awards: One Direction, Ed Sheeran & The Grateful Dead Big Winners|date=20 November 2015|website=Billboard|accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== 2015\u20132018: Malik's departure, ''Made in the A.M.'' and hiatus===\n{{Main|Made in the A.M.}}\n\nOn 25 March 2015, the band released a statement announcing Malik's departure.<ref name=\"inveterate\">{{cite web | url=http://www.inveterate.co.uk/music/one-direction-zayn-malik-confirms-departure-from-band/145871/ | title=One Direction: Zayn Malik Confirms Departure From Band | publisher=Inveterate | date=25 March 2015 | accessdate=23 March 2015 | last=Abbey | first=Lewis | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150329001801/http://www.inveterate.co.uk/music/one-direction-zayn-malik-confirms-departure-from-band/145871 | archivedate=29 March 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Zayn Malik officially quits One Direction|url=http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2015/03/25/zayn-malik-leaves-one-direction/|publisher=[[Fox News Channel]]|accessdate=25 March 2015|date=25 March 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150325193633/http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2015/03/25/zayn-malik-leaves-one-direction/|archivedate=25 March 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Lynch|first1=Joe|title=Zayn Malik Explains One Direction Exit: 'I Have To Do What Feels Right in My Heart'|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6509661/zayn-malik-one-direction-exit-explanation|accessdate=25 March 2015|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|agency=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|date=25 March 2015|location=United States}}</ref> The group made their first official public appearance as a four-piece on ''[[The Late Late Show with James Corden]]'' on 14 May, where they confirmed that they would continue working without a new fifth member.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/article/one-direction-interview-zayn-malik-james-corden-late-late-show|title=One Direction Discusses Zayn Malik's Departure with James Corden: We Were a Little Bit Angry|date=15 May 2015|publisher=}}</ref> The On the Road Again tour concluded on 31 October 2015 after playing eighty shows in Australia, Asia, Africa, Europe, and North America. Grossing $208 million, over 2.3 million tickets were sold.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2016/01/12/these-were-the-highest-grossing-tours-of-2015/|title=The Highest-Grossing Tours Of 2015|first=Hugh|last=McIntyre|website=Forbes}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Chicago IMG 9077 (21423367939).jpg|thumb|right|The group performing as a four piece at [[Soldier Field]], Chicago in 2015]]\nOn 31 July 2015, the group released \"[[Drag Me Down]]\" without promotional material or announcement. Despite this, it still topped the charts in multiple countries, including France and Australia, making the song their first single to reach number one in those respective countries. It also reached number one in multiple other countries, including Ireland and the UK, while charting third in the United States. The single was the first single from their fifth studio album, ''[[Made in the A.M.]]'', and the first material released by the group after Malik's departure.<ref>{{cite web|title=One Direction Shares First Track Without Zayn Malik, 'Drag Me Down'|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6649246/one-direction-shares-first-track-without-zayn-malik-drag-me-down|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=31 July 2015|date=31 July 2015}}</ref> Following the release, it was revealed that the group would be going on hiatus in 2016.<ref name=\"2016break\">{{cite web | url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/6806071/one-direction-x-factor-infinity-history-video-fans | title=One Direction Makes Final 'X Factor' Appearance Before Hiatus, Thanks Fans in New Video | work=Billboard | date=13 December 2015 | accessdate=13 December 2015}}</ref> On 22 September, the title for the fifth studio album, ''Made in the A.M.'', was officially announced along with promotional single \"[[Infinity (One Direction song)|Infinity]]\" being released.<ref>[https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/made-in-the-am-one-direction-announce-new-album-title-and-single-infinity-10513171.html \"Made in the A.M: One Direction announce new album title and single 'Infinity'\"]. The Independent. Retrieved 25 October 2015</ref> The group began to reveal the track listing on their [[Snapchat]] stories to which it was later confirmed on [[iTunes]].<ref>[http://www.etonline.com/news/173824_one_direction_made_the_am_tracklist_revealed_via_snapchat/ \"One Direction's 'Made in the A.M.' Tracklist Revealed Via Snapchat\"]. E!. Retrieved 25 October 2015</ref> In October, another single, \"[[Perfect (One Direction song)|Perfect]],\" was released. It reached the ''Billboard'' top ten, making it the group's second consecutive (after \"Drag Me Down\") and fifth overall top ten hit, breaking [[The Beatles]]' record for the most top ten Hot 100 debuts among bands.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6745031/one-direction-beatles-record-fifth-top-10-debut-hot-100|title=One Direction Beats Beatles' Record With Fifth Top 10 Debut on Hot 100|website=Billboard}}</ref>\n\n''Made in the A.M.'' was released on 13 November 2015,<ref>[http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6706833/one-direction-justin-bieber-album-release-november-13-poll \"One Direction & Justin Bieber Album Release Showdown Set for November 13?\"]. ''Billboard''. Retrieved 25 October 2015</ref> topping the charts in the UK among other countries while reaching number two in the U.S. It was the sixth-best selling album of 2015. At the 2015 [[American Music Awards of 2015|American Music Awards]] on 22 November, One Direction won the award for [[American Music Award for Artist of the Year|Artist of the Year]] for the second year in succession.<ref name=\"AMA\">{{cite news|title=American Music Awards 2015: Check Out All the Winners Here|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/events/amas/6770317/american-music-awards-2015-winners-list-amas|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=24 November 2015}}</ref> Louis Tomlinson later confirmed that the break would be around 18 months. On 13 December, One Direction performed on ''The X Factor'' final. Their last televised performance as a group, before their hiatus, was on ''[[Dick Clark's New Year's Rockin' Eve]]'' on 31 December 2015.<ref name=thewrap-1d2016>{{cite web|title=One Direction Returns to Headline 'Dick Clark's New Year's Rockin' Eve' Billboard Party|url=https://www.thewrap.com/one-direction-returns-to-headline-dick-clarks-new-years-rockin-eve-billboard-party/|website=TheWrap|accessdate=24 November 2015|date=18 November 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 January 2016, ''[[Us Weekly]]'' published a report claiming that the group's hiatus would become a permanent split, with a \"source\" citing that each of the four remaining group members did not renew their contracts following the completion of the On The Road Again Tour in October 2015.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Blynn|first1=Jamie|title=One Direction Is Splitting, Extended Hiatus to Become a Permanent Break|url=http://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/one-direction-is-splitting-hiatus-to-become-a-permanent-break-w161510|accessdate=13 January 2016|work=[[Us Weekly]]|agency=[[Jann Wenner|Wenner Media]] [[Limited liability company|LLC]]|date=13 January 2016|location=United States}}</ref> Representatives for the group denied said-report in a statement to ''Billboard'', stating, \"nothing has changed regarding hiatus plans for the group, and all will be revealed in due time from the band members' own mouths.\"<ref>{{cite news|last1=Strecker|first1=Eric|title=One Direction Breakup Rumors: 'Nothing Has Changed' Since Hiatus, Says Source|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/6842942/one-direction-break-up-rumors-not-true|accessdate=13 January 2016|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|agency=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|date=13 January 2016|location=United States}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Hegarty|first1=Tasha|title=One Direction deny their 'hiatus' is a permanent split|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/music/news/a779897/one-direction-deny-their-extended-hiatus-is-a-permanent-split-and-is-still-just-temporary/|website=[[Digital Spy]]|accessdate=13 January 2016|location=United Kingdom|date=13 January 2016}}</ref> By May 2017, all members of the group had released solo singles.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7808577/one-direction-solo-singles-ranked-list|title=Every One Direction Solo Single, Ranked|work=Billboard|date=25 May 2017|first=Andrew|last=Unterberger}}</ref> Despite saying the hiatus would last 18 months, the band still are yet to confirm when they will reform.\n\nAt the [[2017 Brit Awards]], One Direction won the Video of the Year award for their song \"[[History (One Direction song)|History]]\". Payne accepted the award on the behalf of the band.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2986071/one-direction-respond-2017-brit-award/|title=ALL FOUR ONE DIRECTION MEMBERS RESPOND TO THEIR NEW BRIT AWARD|work=MTV News|date=22 February 2017|first=Madeline|last=Roth}}</ref> In February 2018, it was reported that the group has folded its touring company after having applied for removal within the [[Companies House]] registry in October 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/newsbeat-43055424|title=There's a new sign One Direction might be over|date=14 February 2018||website=Bbc.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://nz.news.yahoo.com/one-direction-fold-touring-company-185107831.html|title=One Direction fold touring company|website=Nz.news.yahoo.com}}</ref>\n\n==Artistry==\n{{Listen\n| filename    = What Makes You Beautiful.ogg\n| title       = \"What Makes You Beautiful\"\n| description = One Direction's debut single, \"[[What Makes You Beautiful]]\", features a prominent guitar-based chorus and [[guitar riff|riff]].<ref name=\"DS1\">{{cite web| first =Robert | last = Copsey| url = http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/singlesreviews/a338401/one-direction-what-makes-you-beautiful-single-review.html |title= One Direction: 'What Makes You Beautiful | type = single review |work= [[Digital Spy]] |publisher= Hearst | place = UK| date= 11 September 2011 | accessdate=25 July 2012}}</ref> It also contains [[cowbell (instrument)|cowbell]] instrumentation,<ref name = \"cowbell\" /> and the [[middle eight]] consists of an \"oh na na na\" hook.<ref name=\"NME\">{{cite news |url = http://www.nme.com/blog/index.php?blog=148&title=one_direction_what_makes_you_beautiful_r&more=1&c=1&tb=1&pb=1 |title = One Direction, 'What Makes You Beautiful' | type = review |work= NME | first= Ailbhe | last= Malone | date= 8 October 2011 |accessdate=3 January 2012}}</ref> It is among the [[List of best-selling singles|best-selling singles of all time]], selling over 5 million copies.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/19093915 |title=One Direction hit 12 million sales in less than a year|date= 2 August 2012 |publisher=BBC News  | accessdate =2 August 2012}}</ref>\n| pos = right\n}}\nOne Direction's debut studio album, ''Up All Night'' (2011), is predominantly a pop music record, containing elements of [[teen pop]], [[dance-pop]], [[pop rock]], with [[Synthpop|electropop]] and rock influences.<ref name=\"Rosen\">{{cite web |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/up-all-night-20120328 | title = One Direction \u2013 Up All Night | work= Rolling Stone  | author-link = Jody Rosen | first = Jody | last = Rosen |date= 28 March 2012 |accessdate= 16 April 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"allmusic3\">{{cite web | first = Jon | last = O'Brien|url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/one-direction-mn0002766592|title=One Direction| publisher = AllMusic |accessdate=30 June 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"Chisling\">{{cite news| first = Matthew | last = Chisling |url= http://www.allmusic.com/album/up-all-night-r2324993/review |title= Up All Night&nbsp;\u2013 One Direction|publisher=AllMusic |date=21 November 2011 |accessdate=5 January 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"Lipshutz\">{{cite news| first =Jason | last = Lipshutz |url = http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/502856/one-direction-up-all-night-track-by-track-review |title= One Direction, 'Up All Night': Track-By-Track Review |location=New York |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=7 March 2012 |accessdate=16 April 2012}}</ref> [[Digital Spy]]'s Robert Copsey described the album as a \"collection of PG pop rock with killer choruses\",<ref>{{cite web| first =Robert | last = Copsey|url= http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/albumreviews/a352333/one-direction-up-all-night-album-review.html |title=One Direction: 'Up All Night' | type = album review |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=Hearst | place = UK|date=22 November 2011 |accessdate=28 November 2011}}</ref> while ''[[The New York Times]]'' considered it \"full of easy rock-inflected pop, blithe and sometimes clever.\"<ref name=autogenerated11>{{cite news | first = Jon | last = Caramanica| url= https://www.nytimes.com/2012/05/28/arts/music/one-direction-the-boy-band-plays-the-beacon-theater.html | work= The New York Times | title= One Direction, the Boy Band, Plays the Beacon Theater | date=27 May 2012|accessdate=16 June 2012}}</ref> Jason Lipshutz of ''Billboard'' acknowledged that the album demonstrates an originality in sound that was \"necessary for the revitalization of the boy band movement\".<ref name = \"Lipshutz\" /> The songs \"One Thing\" and \"What Makes You Beautiful\" were particularly noted for the genres of power pop and pop rock, for their \"powerhouse\" [[guitar riff]]s and \"forceful\" choruses.<ref name=\"DS1\" /><ref name=\"cowbell\">{{cite web | first = Zachary | last = Houle | url = http://www.popmatters.com/pm/review/155316-one-direction-up-all-night/ | title= One Direction: Up All Night| work= [[PopMatters]]  | date= 16 March 2012 | accessdate = 31 March 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"Rosen\" /><ref>{{cite web| first =Lewis | last = Corner |url = http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/singlesreviews/a363531/one-direction-one-thing-single-review.html | title= One Direction: 'One Thing' \u2013 Single review |work=[[Digital Spy]] | publisher= Hearst | place = UK|date= 2 February 2012 |accessdate=25 July 2012}}</ref>\n\nTheir second studio album, ''Take Me Home'' (2012), is characterised by rock-inherited pop, prominent electric guitar riffs, bright synthesisers, a [[Homogeneity and heterogeneity|homogeneous]] sound and message, and the pitch-correcting software [[Auto-Tune]].<ref name= NYT>{{cite news| first = Jon | last = Caramanica | url= https://www.nytimes.com/2012/11/15/arts/music/one-direction-rides-boy-band-wave-with-take-me-home.html |work = The New York Times | title=Riding the Boy Band Wave While It Lasts | date=14 November 2012|accessdate= 30 November 2012}}</ref><ref name=Guardian>{{cite news|url= https://www.theguardian.com/music/2012/nov/08/one-direction-take-me-review | title = One Direction: Take Me Home | type = review | work = The Guardian | author-link = Alexis Petridis | first = Alexis | last = Petridis | date=8 November 2012|accessdate=9 November 2012 | location=London}}</ref><ref name = NZH>{{cite news|url = http://www.nzherald.co.nz/entertainment/news/article.cfm?c_id=1501119&objectid=10847430 | type = album review | title = One Direction \u2013 Take Me Home| work = [[The New Zealand Herald]]|publisher= [[APN News & Media]]|date= 15 November 2012|accessdate = 16 November 2012 | first = Lyndia | last = Jenkin}}</ref><ref name=autogenerated1>{{cite news| first = Douglas | last = Wol|url= http://entertainment.time.com/2012/11/13/one-directions-songwriters-theyre-what-make-the-boy-band-beautiful/ |title=One Direction's songwriters: They're what make the boy band beautiful|work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]] |date= 28 June 2012 |accessdate= 25 August 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| first = Matt | last = Collar |url = http://www.allmusic.com/album/take-me-home-mw0002418914 | title = Take Me Home (CD \u2013 Sony Music Distribution #88725475972) |publisher=AllMusic|date=11 November 2012 |accessdate= 16 November 2012}}</ref> [[Alexis Petridis]] of ''[[The Guardian]]'' interpreted its signature sound as a \"peppy, [[synth]]-bolstered take on early-80s [[New wave music|new-wave]] pop, heavy on clipped rhythms and chugging guitars,\" which, he said, is at least an improvement on the substitute [[contemporary R&B]] \"that was once the grim lot of the boyband.\"<ref name = Guardian /> Jon Caramanica, writing in ''The New York Times'', considered the album \"far more mechanical\" than their debut album, although noted that it is sonically and lyrically similar.<ref name=NYT /> The album's lyricism speaks of falling in love, [[unrequited love]], the insistence that flaws are what make a person unique, commitment, jealousy and longing for past significant others.<ref name=NYT/><ref name=Guardian/><ref name= NZH /><ref name = \"autogenerated12\">{{cite news | url = http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/11/12/one-direction-lyrics-take-me-home_n_2118855.html |title=One Direction lyrics: 'Take Me Home' pushes boundaries, targets older audience| date= 15 November 2012| accessdate= 16 March 2013 | work = [[The Huffington Post]] | first=Madeline | last=Boardman}}</ref>\n\nErica Futterman for ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' favoured their live [[Musical acoustics|acoustic]] performances as both showing, \"Horan's ability to play guitar, as well as One Direction's admirable live vocals. There was no need to worry about a backing track or a bum note, a pleasant realization at a pop show.\"<ref>{{cite news| first =Erica | last = Futterman |url= https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/one-direction-make-a-play-for-longevity-on-first-american-headlining-tour-20120527 |title= One Direction Make a Play For Longevity on First American Headlining Tour |work = Rolling Stone |date=27 May 2012 |accessdate=11 May 2012}}</ref> ''[[Herald Sun]]''{{'}}s Cameron Adams opined that One Direction have \"strong pop voices\".<ref>{{cite news| first =Cameron | last = Adams |url = http://www.heraldsun.com.au/entertainment/one-direction-infection-sweeps-melbourne/story-e6frf96f-1226329537630 |title = One Direction infection sweeps Melbourne |work=Herald Sun |location= Australia  |date=18 April 2012 |accessdate=11 May 2012}}</ref> Melody Lau of the ''[[National Post]]'' wrote, \"It's easy to get lost in inherent appeal of their perfectly coiffed dos and almost-too-put-together preppy style but somewhere in the midst of all the love-struck squeals of teenage girls are guys who can actually sing and, to a certain extent, entertain.\"<ref>{{cite news |first= Melody |last= Lau |url= http://arts.nationalpost.com/2012/06/01/concert-review-one-direction-are-mostly-killer-with-some-filler/ |title= Concert Review: One Direction are mostly killer with some filler |work= National Post |location= Canada |publisher= [[Postmedia Network]] |date= 1 June 2012 |accessdate= 11 June 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl= https://archive.is/20120709183651/http://arts.nationalpost.com/2012/06/01/concert-review-one-direction-are-mostly-killer-with-some-filler/ |archivedate= 9 July 2012 }}</ref> Jane Stevenson of the portal site [[Canoe.ca|Canoe]] concurred: \"What I didn't really prepare myself for was that they all can actually sing in concert.\"<ref>{{cite news | first = Jane | last = Stevenson | url = http://jam.canoe.ca/Music/Artists/O/One_Direction/ConcertReviews/2012/05/30/19815201-qmi.html | title = Concert Review: Live Review: One Direction in TO | work = [[Canoe.ca|Jam! Canoe]] | publisher = [[Qu\u00e9becor M\u00e9dia]] | date = 30 May 2012 | accessdate = 11 June 2012 | url-status=dead | archiveurl = https://archive.is/20120710002923/http://jam.canoe.ca/Music/Artists/O/One_Direction/ConcertReviews/2012/05/30/19815201-qmi.html | archivedate = 10 July 2012 }}</ref> Chris Richards, writing in ''[[The Washington Post]]'', dissented from the approval: \"As the five traded couplets, it was tough to imagine a future [[Justin Timberlake]], [[Ricky Martin]] or [[Bobby Brown]] emerging from the pack. No one voice stood out.\"<ref>{{cite news| first =Chris | last = Richards| url = https://www.washingtonpost.com/lifestyle/style/one-direction-show-polite-boy-band-excites-squealing-fans/2012/05/25/gJQAmYxVpU_story.html |work=The Washington Post | title = One Direction whips Patriot Center into a G-rated frenzy | date = 25 May 2012|accessdate=9 July 2012}}</ref> Mike Wass of [[Idolator (website)|Idolator]] felt One Direction's \"surprisingly accomplished effort\" of [[Kings of Leon]]'s \"[[Use Somebody]]\" proved that One Direction are \"more than capable\" of evolving their sound.<ref>{{cite news| first =Mike | last = Wass |url= http://idolator.com/6351471/one-direction-live-in-sydney-concert-review |title=One Direction Live in Sydney: Concert Review |work= [[Idolator (website)|Idolator]] |date=13 April 2012 |accessdate=9 July 2012}}</ref>\n\nTheir third album ''Midnight Memories'' (2013) is a pop rock record, a slight departure from the band's original teen pop sound. Liam Payne called Midnight Memories a \"slightly rockier and edgier\" album than their previous material. The album is heavily influenced by 80's rock<ref name=Rebellion>{{cite web|url=http://whstherebellion.com/?p=51482 |title=One Direction Embraces New Sound with 'Midnight Memories' |publisher=Whstherebellion.com |date=2 December 2013 |accessdate=2 August 2014}}</ref> and folk music and briefly integrates elements of dubstep, notably in \"Little White Lies\". The album's lyrical themes primarily revolve around love, heartbreak and sexual intercourse. Many critics praised its lyrical depth and musical composition, as well as the group's level of involvement in the production process.<ref name=\"Hollywood Reporter\">{{cite news| url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/one-directions-midnight-memories-what-660135 | work=The Hollywood Reporter | first=Kyle | last=Jaeger | title=One Direction's 'Midnight Memories': What the Critics Are Saying | date=26 November 2013}}</ref>\n\nTheir fourth album ''Four'' (2014) was released on 17 November 2014. Payne once again claimed that the album would be \"edgier\" and that the group had written most of the songs for it; Horan came up with the name of the album, commemorating the fact that it is One Direction's fourth record to date and that it has been four years since the band's formation. Signifying a further maturation of their pop sound, the album's first single, \"[[Steal My Girl]]\", was dubbed by ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' as \"no [[What Makes You Beautiful]], but its [[Coldplay]]-like piano pop could be a good direction\",<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/review/album-review/6319861/one-direction-four-album-review |title=Album Review: One Direction's 'Four' | work=Billboard | first=Chuck | last=Arnold | date=17 November 2014}}</ref> and that the band was \"not entirely ready to let go of its bubble-gum days\". ''Rolling Stone'' described the record as \"saturated with retro vibes\"; its songs \"split the difference between big, splashy Eighties [[pop rock]] and more elegant Seventies flavours \u2013 a very pesky whipper-snapper move that's not so far from what [[Haim (band)|Haim]]'s hit \"[[Days Are Gone]]\" did last year.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/one-direction-four-20141118 |title=One Direction extend their winning streak, with echoes of the 1970s and 1980s | work=Rolling Stone | first=Jon | last=Dolan | date=18 November 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Other ventures==\n\n===Endorsements===\nIn 2011, One Direction became the face of [[Pokemon Black and White]], starring in a series of television adverts.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2011-04-06-one-direction-become-pokemon-face |title=One Direction become Pokemon face |last=Purchese |first=Robert |work=Eurogamer |accessdate=6 April 2011}}</ref> They were the first installments in the fifth [[Pok\u00e9mon#Generations|generation]] of the ''[[Pok\u00e9mon (video game series)|Pok\u00e9mon]]'' series of role-playing games.<ref name=\"bw\">{{cite web |url=http://www.pokemon.co.jp/bw/index.html |script-title=ja:\u300e\u30dd\u30b1\u30c3\u30c8\u30e2\u30f3\u30b9\u30bf\u30fc\u30d6\u30e9\u30c3\u30af\u30fb\u30db\u30ef\u30a4\u30c8\u300f |language=Japanese |publisher=[[Nintendo]] |accessdate=7 April 2010 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5sv9suCz9?url=http://www.pokemon-sp.jp/series/bw/ |archivedate=22 September 2010 |url-status=dead}}</ref> They also launched [[Nokia C3 (disambiguation)|Nokia C3]] and [[Nokia C2-02]] phones. To promote the launch [[Nokia]] made a series of photos of the band members using the phones to take photos of themselves.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theinquirer.net/inquirer/news/2110372/nokia-enlists-direction-launch-phones |title=Nokia enlists One Direction to launch phones |last=Martin |first=Chris |work=The Inquirer |accessdate=20 September 2011}}</ref>\n\nIn 2012, they teamed up with [[Colgate (toothpaste)|Colgate]] to launch their own One Direction Colgate MaxFresh Power Toothbrush, the One Direction Colgate Maxfresh Manual Toothbrush, and the One Direction Colgate MaxFresh Toothpaste.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2012/10/10/one-direction-colgate-toothbrush-toothpaste_n_1954108.html?guccounter=1 |title=One Direction Colgate Range: Boyband Launch Their Own Toothbrushes And Toothpaste |last=Bagwell |first=Matt |work=Huffpost |date=10 November 2012 |accessdate=10 November 2012}}</ref> The band was signed by [[Pepsi]] in a multimillion-dollar advertising deal in 2012.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://metro.co.uk/2012/09/05/one-direction-land-multi-million-dollar-pepsi-advertising-deal-566025/ |title=One Direction land multi-million dollar Pepsi advertising deal |author=metrowebukmetro |work=Metro UK |accessdate=5 September 2012}}</ref> Social media marketing included a tie up with [[Shazam (application)|Shazam]], whereby consumers that used the digital music app in conjunction with the ad both on TV and online were be able to view exclusive content and link back to [[iTunes]] to buy One Direction's single, \u201c[[Live While We're Young]]\u201d.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.campaignlive.co.uk/article/pepsi-pits-one-direction-against-nfl-star-live-push/1154374 |title=Pepsi pits One Direction against NFL star in Live For Now push |last=Smith |first=Loulla |work=Campaign |accessdate=11 October 2012}}</ref> Mini figures based on members of the group were launched for the band's US fans after the agreement was signed by American firm [[Hasbro]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.expressandstar.com/entertainment/music/2012/04/28/1d-toy-firm-hasbro-to-create-one-direction-toys/ |title=Toy firm Hasbro to create One Direction toys |publisher=Express And Star |accessdate=28 April 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/hasbro-results-marvel-one-direction-443908 |title=Hasbro First-Quarter Revenue Helped by One Direction, Marvel Products |last=Szalai |first=Georg |work=Hollywood Reporter |accessdate=22 April 2013}}</ref> In October 2012, the band also signed up to endorse Filipino clothing brand, [[Penshoppe]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://entertainment.inquirer.net/61776/one-direction-to-endorse-filipino-clothing-brand |title=One Direction to endorse Filipino clothing brand |last=Conception |first=Pocholo |work=Philippines Daily Inquirer |accessdate=7 October 2012}}</ref>\n\n[[File:1D World, Albion Street, Leeds (30th March 2013) 001.JPG|thumb|right|A One Direction merchandising shop in [[Leeds]] in March 2013]]\nIn 2013, One Direction announced pop-up shops around the world, including Brisbane, Toronto, Chicago, New York, Tokyo and Stockholm, selling exclusive merchandise.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/showbiz/news/a464976/one-direction-to-launch-1d-world-store-in-leeds-for-three-weeks/ |title=One Direction to launch 1D World store in Leeds for three weeks |last=Eames |first=Tom |work=Digital Spy |accessdate=12 March 2013}}</ref> [[Nabisco]] became the title sponsor of One Direction's North American tour.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.eventmarketer.com/article/nabisco-one-direction-north-american-tour/ |title=NABISCO SPONSORSHIP SATISFIES ONE DIRECTION'S FAN CONNECTION |last=Boucher |first=Rachel |work=Event Marketer |accessdate=20 June 2013}}</ref> The band became the new faces of [[Toyota]] [[Toyota Vios|VIOS]], releasing behind-the-scenes look at their commercial for the vehicle.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://popcrush.com/one-direction-toyota-vios-commercial-behind-the-scenes/ |title=one direction toyota vios commercial behind the scenes |last=Sager |first=Jessica |work=Pop Crush |accessdate=20 October 2013}}</ref> One Direction's debut fragrance, [[Our Moment]], launched at [[Harrods]] in London and on their website in 2013.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache:http://www.vogue.co.uk/article/one-direction-our-moment-fragrance-waiting-list-harrods |title=Waiting For One Direction |last=Niven |first=Lisa |work=Vogue |accessdate=21 August 2013 }}{{Dead link|date=September 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> The full length advert for the fragrance was released on 24 August 2013, featuring the song \"[[My Favorite Things (song)|My Favourite Things]]\u201d.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/showbiz/news/a509881/one-directions-our-moment-fragrance-ad-diana-vickers-sings-video.html|title=One Direction's Our Moment fragrance ad, Diana Vickers sings - video|accessdate=26 August 2013|work=Digital Spy|first=Sam|last=Rigby}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pressparty.com/pg/newsdesk/OneDirection/view/77929/|title=One Direction's Liam Payne says perfume was inspired by fan petition|work=Press Party|accessdate=7 June 2013}}</ref> The perfume was the best-selling famous fragrance of Christmas 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sugarscape.com/main-topics/fashion-beauty/996227/one-direction%E2%80%99s-our-moment-beating-taylor-swift-lady-gaga-britney-|title=One Direction's Our Moment beating Taylor Swift, Lady Gaga, Britney Spears and basically everyone in the fragrance war|work=Sugarscape|accessdate=6 December 2013|first=Lucy|last=Wood}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.irishmirror.ie/showbiz/celebrity-news/one-direction-moment-fragrance-beats-2894369|title=One Direction perfume beats Lady Gaga, Britney Spears and Taylor Swift fragrances|work=Irish Mirror|accessdate=5 December 2013|first=Rebecca|last=Pocklington}}</ref> In 2014, the band released their second scent That Moment.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2014/02/27/one-direction-release-new-fragrance-that-moment-harry-styles_n_4864093.html |title=One Direction To Release New Fragrance 'That Moment', Confirms Harry Styles |last=Nelson |first=Sarah |work=huffpost |accessdate=27 February 2014}}</ref> The fragrance was released with a matching shower gel and body lotion.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.seventeen.com/beauty/news/a22750/one-direction-that-moment-perfume/ |title=Check Out 1D's Pics for Their New Perfume! |last=Mcgrath |first=Kara |work=Seventeen |accessdate=21 March 2014}}</ref> They released a commercial for their third fragrance, \"You & I\", named after their [[You & I (One Direction song)|2014 song of the same name]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6207040/one-direction-commercial-perfume-you-i |title=One Direction Debut Commercial Behind New Perfume 'You & I' |last=Strecker |first=Erin |work=Billboard |accessdate=5 August 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, One Direction appeared in an advert for the [[Toyota Vios]]. the commercial aired in Thailand.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nme.com/news/music/one-direction-118-1214327#LiGp0Cx3I53E7Kfu.99 |title=One Direction star in Toyota ad \u2013 watch |publisher=NME |accessdate=17 March 2015}}</ref> [[Coca-Cola]] Mexico launched the session and full interview with One Direction, with a series of commercials in which Tomlinson, Payne, Styles and Horan showed us what it means to be a True Friend.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.es.j-14.com/posts/coca-cola-por-fin-lanzan-su-session-en-el-estudio-con-one-direction-59033?age_gate%5Bbirth_year%5D=691&age_gate%5Bcoppa_cookie%5D= |title=Directioners: Coca-Cola Finally Launch Their Session In The Studio With One Direction |last=Rodriguez |first=Karla |work=J-14 |accessdate=22 May 2015}}</ref> One Direction revealed their fourth fragrance \u2018Between Us\u2019 at The Sanderson in London, England on 24 June.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://hollywoodlife.com/2015/06/24/one-direction-between-us-fourth-fragrance-new-scent/ |title=One Direction Launches Fourth Fragrance 'Between Us |last=Zayas |first=Dory |work=Hollywood life |accessdate=24 June 2015}}</ref> The band appeared in a [[Honda Civic]] ad which shows the quartet testing out the car's stereo, style and trunk space with a humorous tone and the tagline \"It's all One Direction approved.\" The ad is set to the 1D single \u201c[[Drag Me Down]]\u201d. The group's 2015 U.S. tour was also supported by [[Honda]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6760883/one-direction-honda-civic-test-drive-commercial-video |title=Watch One Direction Put New Honda Civic to the Test in TV Commercial |last=Stutz |first=Colin |work=Billboard |accessdate=12 November 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Philanthropy===\nIn 2011, the band performed on the BBC's [[Children in Need 2011]] charity telethon. In 2012, they extended their involvement with Children in Need as they opened the telecast with a performance of their single \"[[Live While We're Young]]\". A prominent annual event in British television, the group said it was \"incredible\" to be involved in [[Children in Need]] as it was something that they had \"always watched as children\".<ref name=\"BBC\">{{cite news| url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-20367022 | publisher=BBC News | title=One Direction: 'Incredible to open Children In Need' | date=16 November 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2013, One Direction released \"[[One Way or Another (Teenage Kicks)]]\" (a medley of \"[[One Way or Another]]\" and \"[[Teenage Kicks]]\") as the 2013 single for the UK's other major charity telethon [[Comic Relief]].<ref name=\"Robertson\"/> For [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]]'s Santa charity Christmas campaign, they filmed a set of pleas to their fans and the general public, asking them to donate \u00a32.<ref name=\"Sugarscape\">{{cite web|url=http://www.sugarscape.com/main-topics/film-and-tv/999397/one-direction-join-itv%E2%80%99s-text-santa-charity-campaign |title=One Direction join ITV\u0411\u2500\u2265s Text Santa charity campaign |publisher=Sugarscape |accessdate=2 August 2014}}</ref> The band have made numerous other appearances for charitable causes, including the 2011 [[Pride of Britain Awards]] where they presented 13-year-old quadruple amputee Danielle Bailey the Child of Courage award at her school assembly, and the 2014 [[Royal Variety Performance]] where they played in front of [[Prince William, Duke of Cambridge|Prince William]] and [[Catherine, Duchess of Cambridge|Catherine]] at the London Palladium.<ref>[https://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/one-direction-surprise-pride-of-britain-156163 \"One Direction surprise Pride of Britain winner Danielle Bailey at school assembly\"]. Mirror. Retrieved 26 August 2015</ref><ref>[https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/theroyalfamily/11230239/Duke-and-Duchess-of-Cambridge-meet-One-Direction-at-Royal-Variety-Performance.html \"Duke and Duchess of Cambridge meet One Direction at Royal Variety Performance\"]. The Telegraph. Retrieved 26 August 2015</ref>\n\nIn September 2012, Niall Horan organised an event to raise money for Irish Autism Action and another charity, called Temporary Emergency Accommodation Mullingar, based in his hometown. Due to overwhelming demand to participate in the fundraising, the ticket website for the event broke down. Horan's brother Greg commented on the website crash, saying that \"there were 500 tickets and they were all snapped up pretty quick\".<ref name=autogenerated2>{{cite web|url=http://www.sugarscape.com/main-topics/homepage/764642/niall-horans-charity-event-crashes-website |title=Niall Horan breaks charity website |publisher=Sugarscape |accessdate=2 August 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013, band members Liam Payne and Harry Styles partnered with Trekstock, a leading cancer charity to help raise money for cancer research.<ref name=\"Trekstock\">{{cite web|url=http://trekstock.com/our-story/patrons-ambassadors/ |title=Patrons & Ambassadors |publisher=Trekstock |accessdate=29 November 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141030012714/http://trekstock.com/our-story/patrons-ambassadors/ |archivedate=30 October 2014 }}</ref> As ambassadors of the charity, the duo collaborated to offer the chance for one fan and a friend to win an evening out with them in return for a donation to the charity as part of an exclusive \"#HangwithLiam&Harry\" global campaign. They had originally set a goal of raising $500,000 and ended up raising $784,984. Trekstock later added that this amount would allow them to \"complete funding of their [[Hodgkin's lymphoma]] trial, in the hope of offering a much brighter future to thousands of children and young people affected by this form of disease.\" One Direction were named the most charitable in 2013 behind [[Taylor Swift]] by social change organisation [[DoSomething.org]].<ref name=\"Do Something\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5847924/taylor-swift-one-direction-top-list-of-most-charitable-stars |title=Taylor Swift, One Direction Top List of Most Charitable Stars |work=Billboard |accessdate=19 January 2014}}</ref> On 30 May 2013, the band announced a partnership with [[Office Depot]] on a limited-edition capsule collection of back to school supplies. They also confirmed that a portion of the proceeds from the alliance would go toward an anti-bullying educational program intended to promote kinder behaviour in schools.<ref>[http://uk.eonline.com/news/426786/one-direction-boys-launch-anti-bullying-campaign-with-office-depot \"One Direction Boys Launch Anti-Bullying Campaign with Office Depot\"]. E!. Retrieved 13 September 2015</ref>\n\nIn 2014, One Direction donated \u00a3600,000 for the Stand up to Cancer campaign by giving portions of their ticket sales revenues from their [[Where We Are Tour (One Direction)|Where We Are Tour]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sugarscape.com/main-topics/lads/1045055/one-direction-release-selfie-they-took-stage-last-night-wembley-its-reveale|title=Cosmopolitan, the women's magazine for fashion, beauty, sex tips and celebrity news|website=Cosmopolitan}}</ref> On 15 November 2014, One Direction joined the charity group [[Band Aid 30]] along with other British and Irish pop acts, recording the latest version of the track \"[[Do They Know It's Christmas?]]\" at [[Sarm West Studios]] in [[Notting Hill]], London, to raise money for the [[West African Ebola virus epidemic|2014 Ebola crisis]] in Western Africa.<ref>{{cite news|title=Band Aid 30: One Direction among celebrity line-up|newspaper=The Daily Telegraph|date=11 November 2014 |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/music/music-news/11220735/Band-Aid-30-line-up-revealed.html |accessdate=11 January 2015|location=London|first=Anita|last=Singh}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, One Direction launched 'Action 1D' campaign to raise awareness of global issues. The initiative aims to end extreme poverty, tackle inequality and slow down climate change with the help of their millions of fans. It is part of the wider [[action/2015]] campaign, a global citizen's movement that is all about the idea that 2015 can be the year when the world can set the agenda to end major global issues. One Direction will be asking their fans to describe the kind of world they want to live in by sharing powerful pieces of creative content, including videos and photos, using the hashtag #Action1D.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mtv.co.uk/one-direction/news/one-direction-launch-action-1d-campaign-to-raise-awareness-of-global-issues |title=one direction launch action 1d campaign to raise awareness of global issues |publisher=MTV |accessdate=8 July 2015}}</ref> The quartet also starred in a campaign video, appealing to fans to join the movement.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2015/07/08/one-direction-action-1d-campaign-video_n_7752930.html |title=One Direction Launch Action/1D Campaign To End Poverty, Inequality And Global Warming |last=Percival |first=Ashley |work=Huffington Post UK |accessdate=7 August 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Image==\n[[File:One Direction 2012 Stockholm.jpg|thumb|right|One Direction greet Swedish fans in [[Stockholm]], May 2012]]\nNeil McCormick of ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]'', in an article on One Direction's success in North America, notes that Americans had left a gap in the market and it took the prominence of [[Justin Bieber]] to demonstrate that there still was a market for \"clean cut, wholesome, whiter-than-white, middle class parent friendly pop: cute boys advocating puppy love. And what could be better than one cute boy, if not five?\"<ref>{{cite news | first = Neil | last = McCormick |url= https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/music/rockandpopmusic/9111003/The-Wanted-and-One-Direction-why-British-boybands-are-conquering-America.html |title=The Wanted & One Direction: why British boybands are conquering America |work= The Daily Telegraph |location= London |date= 28 February 2012|accessdate= 17 March 2012}}</ref> One Direction have been described as sparking a resurgence in the interest in boy bands, and as forming part of a new \"[[British Invasion]]\" in the United States.<ref name=autogenerated8>{{cite news| first =Kerry | last = O'Shea |url = http://www.irishcentral.com/ent/One-Direction-BritishIrish-boy-band--about-to-explode-in-America-says-Simon-Cowell--142303325.html |title=One Direction, British/Irish boy band about to explode in America says Simon Cowell |work =IrishCentral | date=12 March 2012 |accessdate=31 March 2012}}</ref><ref name=autogenerated5>{{cite news| first = Lyndsey | last = Parker |url= http://ca.music.yahoo.com/blogs/reality-rocks/british-coming-one-direction-set-conquer-america-202911123.html |title=The British Are Coming! One Direction Set To Conquer America |work=[[Yahoo! News|News]] | publisher =Yahoo! |date=12 March 2012 |accessdate=31 March 2012}}</ref><ref name=autogenerated4>{{cite news| first = Jocelyn | last = Vena|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1681029/the-wanted-one-direction-boy-bands.jhtml |title= The Wanted Vs. One Direction: A Boy Band Cheat Sheet |publisher=[[MTV News]] |date=14 March 2012 | accessdate =31 March 2012}}</ref><ref name=autogenerated3>{{cite news| first =Brian | last = Mansfield |url = https://www.usatoday.com/life/music/ontheverge/story/2012-03-07/one-direction/53425236/1 |title=Meet UK boy band One Direction |work=USA Today|publisher=[[Gannett Company|Gannett Co]] |date=9 March 2012 |accessdate=31 March 2012}}</ref><ref name= Greene>{{cite web | first = Andy | last = Greene | url = http://rollingstoneindia.com/features/the-new-british-invasion-boy-bands/ | title = The New British Invasion: Boy Bands |work= Rolling Stone |date= 8 May 2012 | accessdate = 11 June 2012}}</ref> Bill Werde, a representative of [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']] magazine, commented, \"There's a lot of possibility here, there's a lot of upside, that level of talent with those kinds of looks, it's really a perfect storm for a massive, massive successful phenomenon.\"<ref name=\"guardian1\">{{cite news| first = Caspar Llewellyn | last = Smith |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2012/mar/15/one-direction-fab-five-america |title = One Direction: the fab five take America |work=The Guardian| location=London |date=15 March 2012| accessdate= 31 March 2012}}</ref> In [[NPR]], Maria Sherman noticed that before One Direction's breakthrough, boy bands were \"off the radar\" since [[NSYNC]] went on an indefinite hiatus in 2002.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.npr.org/2020/03/20/818464377/nsync-no-strings-attached-20th-anniversary-timberlake-backstreet|title=The Future According To NSYNC: 20 Years Of 'No Strings Attached'|work=NPR}}</ref>\n\nSonny Takhar, the chief executive officer of Syco Records, attributes the breakthrough to the power of [[social media]]. \"Sometimes you feel the song's the star, but it's not like that here&nbsp;\u2013 it's the act,\" he said. \"It's a real moment. Social media has become the new radio, it's never broken an act globally like this before.\"<ref name=\"guardian1\"/> Will Bloomfield, the group's manager, added, \"These guys live online, and so do their fans.\"<ref name= Greene /> Their management employs a social media team and the members all tweet themselves, \"which helps create the illusion that they couldn't be any closer to their fans,\" according to Caspar Llewellyn Smith, writing for ''The Guardian''.<ref name = \"guardian1\" /> One Direction's Twitter account had amassed 10 million followers by February 2013, with the account gaining followers at an average of 21,000 per day.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://twittercounter.com/compare/one%20direction/week/followers | title = One Direction Twitter Stats |work= Counter| publisher= Twitter | accessdate= 15 March 2013}}</ref> In an approach pioneered by [[The Beatles]], each member is known for his feature; Horan is \"the cute one\", Malik is \"the quiet and mysterious one\", Payne is \"the sensible one\", Styles is \"the charming one\" and Tomlinson is \"the funny one\".<ref name=Abrams>{{cite news| first =Stephanie | last = Abrahams |url = http://entertainment.time.com/2012/04/06/behind-the-hype-can-one-direction-save-the-boy-band/ | title = Can One Direction Save the Boy Band? | work = Time | date = 6 April 2012 | accessdate= 27 April 2012}}</ref> Each member's individual identity is reinforced by their intentionally different personal styles. Caroline Watson, the band's original stylist, spoke about styling the band, \"At the beginning I didn't want them all in black or all in leather\u2014that whole stereotypical boy band thing.\" Instead, her original idea was for them to be the \"male equivalent to the [[Spice Girls]]\", with each member being a part of the group but still having his own individual style.<ref name=styling>{{cite news| first =Brodie | last = Lancaster |url = http://themuse.jezebel.com/behind-the-boy-band-q-a-with-caroline-watson-one-dire-1687594935 | title = Behind the Boy Band: Q&A with Caroline Watson, One Direction's Stylist | work = Jezebel | date = 2 March 2015 | accessdate= 9 March 2017}}</ref> \n\nHoran commented on One Direction as a boy band, \"People think that a boy band is air-grabs and [being] dressed in all one colour. We're boys in a band. We're trying to do something different from what people would think is the typical kind of boy band. We're trying to do different kinds of music and we're just trying to be ourselves, not squeaky clean.\"<ref name=\"nationalpost1\">{{cite news | first = Leah | last = Collins | url = http://arts.nationalpost.com/2012/03/12/one-direction-is-more-than-just-another-boy-band/ | archive-url = https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20120313001910/http://arts.nationalpost.com/2012/03/12/one-direction-is-more-than-just-another-boy-band/ | url-status=dead | archivedate = 13 March 2012 | title = One Direction: X Factor boy band on what sets them apart | work = National Post | location = Canada | publisher = [[Postmedia Network]] | date = 12 March 2012 | accessdate = 17 March 2012 }}</ref> Leah Collins, writing for the ''[[National Post]]'', remarked they had succeeded on the latter front. \"For the most part, that just means the group presents themselves as typical, goofy and uncensored teenage boys&nbsp;\u2013 posting jokey YouTube videos, for instance, or boozing at awards shows.\"<ref name=\"nationalpost1\" /> Writing for ''[[The Observer]]'', [[Kitty Empire]] opined, \"One Direction fulfill a great many boy band prerequisites (looks, soppy lyrics, tune-grasp, fame-lust) but their lack of routines points to the subtle digressions afoot here\".<ref>{{cite news| author-link = Kitty Empire | first = Kitty | last = Empire |url= https://www.theguardian.com/music/2012/jan/08/one-direction-x-factor-live |title= One Direction | type = review |date=7 January 2012 |work= The Observer |accessdate= 8 April 2012 | archiveurl = http://www.freezepage.com/1333939139CSPGVONNPC?url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/music/2012/jan/08/one-direction-x-factor-live |archivedate= 9 April 2012 |location= London}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n{{Main|One Direction discography|List of songs recorded by One Direction}}\n\n* ''[[Up All Night (One Direction album)|Up All Night]]'' (2011)\n* ''[[Take Me Home (One Direction album)|Take Me Home]]'' (2012)\n* ''[[Midnight Memories]]'' (2013)\n* ''[[Four (One Direction album)|Four]]'' (2014)\n* ''[[Made in the A.M.]]'' (2015)\n\n==Filmography==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n|2010\n|''[[The X Factor (British TV series)|The X Factor]]\n|Themselves (contestants)\n|[[The X Factor (British series 7)|Series 7]]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|2012\n|''[[iCarly]]''\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Themselves\n|Episode: iGo One Direction\n|-\n|''[[Up All Night: The Live Tour]]''\n|Video album\n|-\n| 2012\u201314\n|''[[Saturday Night Live]]''\n|Themselves (musical guests)\n|Episodes: Sofia Vergara/One Direction; Paul Rudd/One Direction; Amy Adams/One Direction\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[One Direction: This Is Us]]''\n| rowspan=\"2\"|Themselves\n| [[Documentary film|Documentary]] [[concert film]]\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[One Direction: Where We Are \u2013 The Concert Film]]''\n| Concert film\n|}\n\n==Tours==\n{{Col-begin}}\n{{Col-2}}\n'''Headlining'''\n*[[Up All Night Tour]] (2011\u201312)\n*[[Take Me Home Tour (One Direction)|Take Me Home Tour]] (2013)\n*[[Where We Are Tour (One Direction)|Where We Are Tour]] (2014)\n*[[On the Road Again Tour]] (2015)\n\n{{Col-2}}\n'''Opening act'''\n*[[The X Factor (British TV series)|X Factor Tour 2011]] (2011)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/newsround/33639898|title=One Direction: A look back at five years of 1D madness - CBBC Newsround|agency=BBC}}</ref>\n*[[Better with U Tour]] {{small|([[Big Time Rush (band)|Big Time Rush]])}} (2012)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1678972/big-time-rush-one-direction-tour/ |title=One Direction, Big Time Rush Talk Joint Tour |publisher=MTV |date=10 February 2012 |accessdate=9 July 2014}}</ref>\n{{Col-end}}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{{Main|List of awards and nominations received by One Direction}}\nOne Direction has received seven [[Brit Awards]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7701365/one-direction-zayn-malik-video-of-the-year-2017-brit-awards|title=One Direction Beats Out Zayn Malik for Video of the Year at 2017 Brit Awards|last=Weatherby|first=Taylor|date=22 February 2017|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=24 August 2018}}</ref> seven [[American Music Awards]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theamas.com/winners-database/?winnerKeyword=one+direction&winnerYear=&winnerCategory=|title=Winners Database|last=|first=|date=|website=[[American Music Awards]]|accessdate=24 August 2018}}</ref> six [[Billboard Music Award|''Billboard'' Music Awards]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboardmusicawards.com/winners-database/?winnerKeyword=one+direction&winnerYear=&winnerCategory=|title=Winners Database|last=|first=|date=|website=[[Billboard Music Award]]s|accessdate=24 August 2018}}</ref> five [[Billboard Touring Awards|''Billboard'' Touring Awards]], and four [[MTV Video Music Awards]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1713022/one-direction-vma-2013-song-of-the-summer/|title=One Direction: Eight Million Votes Prove The Boys Own 'Song Of The Summer'|last=Vena|first=Jocelyn|date=25 August 2013|website=[[MTV News]]|accessdate=24 August 2018}}</ref> among other awards. One Direction holds the record as the most awarded act at the [[Teen Choice Awards]] with 28 wins from 31 nominations.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Dresdale |first1=Andrea |title=It's One Direction vs. One Direction at tonight's Teen Choice Awards |url=https://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/direction-direction-tonights-teen-choice-awards/story?id=49156368 |website=[[ABC News]] |accessdate=25 August 2018 |date=13 August 2017}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n\n* [[List of Billboard Social 50 number-one artists]]\n* [[List of artists who reached number one on the UK Singles Chart]]\n* [[List of highest-grossing concert tours]]\n\n==Publications==\n*''One Direction: Forever Young'', HarperCollins (17 February 2011) {{ISBN|978-0-00-743230-1}}\n*''One Direction: The Official Annual 2012'', HarperCollins (1 September 2011) {{ISBN|978-0-00-743625-5}}\n*''Dare to Dream: Life as One Direction'', HarperCollins (15 September 2011) {{ISBN|978-0-00-744439-7}}\n*''One Direction: Where We Are: Our Band, Our Story: 100% Official'', HarperCollins (19 November 2013) {{ISBN|978-0-00-748900-8}}\n*''One Direction: Who We Are: Our Official Autobiography'', HarperCollins (25 September 2014) {{ISBN|978-0-00-757731-6}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{wikiquote}}\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{Official website}}\n* {{allmusic}}\n* {{IMDb name}}\n\n{{One Direction}}\n{{Navboxes\n|list=\n{{Niall Horan}}\n{{Zayn Malik}}\n{{Liam Payne}}\n{{Harry Styles}}\n{{Louis Tomlinson}}\n{{The X Factor (UK)}}\n{{IFPI Global Year-End}}\n{{Japan Gold Disc Award for Artist of the Year}}\n{{MTV EMA for Best UK & Ireland Act}}\n}}\n{{Good article}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:One Direction| ]]\n[[Category:ARIA Award winners]]\n[[Category:Brit Award winners]]\n[[Category:MTV EMA winners]]\n[[Category:English pop music groups]]\n[[Category:English boy bands]]\n[[Category:English pop rock music groups]]\n[[Category:English vocal groups]]\n[[Category:Bubblegum pop]]\n[[Category:Teen pop groups]]\n[[Category:Columbia Records artists]]\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 2010]]\n[[Category:Musical groups from London]]\n[[Category:Musical quartets]]\n[[Category:NME Awards winners]]\n[[Category:Syco Music artists]]\n[[Category:Sony/ATV Music Publishing artists]]\n[[Category:Sony BMG artists]]\n[[Category:Vocal quartets]]\n[[Category:The X Factor (British TV series) contestants]]\n[[Category:Vocal quintets]]\n", "name_user": "BestOnLifeform", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One_Direction"}
